\id JHN  
\h Jon 
\toc3 Jon 
\toc2 John 
\toc1 Te Rono Tauareka Jon e taataa 
\mt1 Jon 
\mt2 Te Rono Tauareka Jon e taataa 
\iot Na hakataakoto hakamattua i roto te launiu nei: 
\io1 Na tattara kaamata \ior 1.1—1.51\ior* 
\io1 Jisas e huri ake na mahi TeAtua \ior 2.1—12.50\ior* 
\io1 Na takutaku hakaoti Jisas \ior 13.1—17.26\ior* 
\io1 Jisas ku mate \ior 18.1—19.42\ior* 
\io1 Jisas ku ora muri \ior 20.1—20.29\ior* 
\io1 Na tattara hakaoti \ior 20.30—21.25\ior* 
\c 1  
\s1 Te Tattara te Ora raa ku tipu tama 
\p  
\v 1 Te Tattara raa ko na noho mai avare i mua na mee hakaatoa ni ttipu ake; te Tattara raa e nnoho laaua ma TeAtua, tena te Tattara raa ko TeAtua koi.  
\v 2 Te Tattara raa e nnoho laaua ma TeAtua i te kaamata roo.  
\v 3 TeAtua e pena na mee hakaatoa i na mahi Tama raa; ia se hai mee i roto te maarama nei ni tipu ake ma te Tattara raa se iroa.  
\v 4 Te Tattara raa ko te tahito te ora, tena te Ora raa e kou mai te Maahina i na tama hakaatoa.  
\v 5 Tena te Maahina raa e hakamaahina na kina e pouri raa, tena te pouri raa se lavaa hoki te uhi te Maahina raa ki se maahina iho. 
\p  
\v 6 TeAtua e kauna ria mai Jon\f + \fr 1.6 \ft teenei ko Jon Baptis\f* te tama hakatae na tattara Aia raa  
\v 7 ki hamai no tattara ake na tama raa i te vahi te Maahina raa, ki lavaa na tama hakaatoa e llono raa te hakattina.  
\v 8 Jon seai ma ko te Maahina raa; e meia aia e hamai ki tattara ake na tama i te vahi te Maahina raa.  
\v 9 Teenei ko te Maahina hakamaoni roo, te Maahina nei e hamai ki hakamaahina i aruna na tama hakaatoa. 
\p  
\v 10 Te Maahina raa ni noho i roto te maarama nei, ia niaina ma TeAtua e pena na mee hakaatoa i na mahi Tama raa, e meia te maarama nei hakaatoa se illoa laoi Tama raa.  
\v 11 Tama raa ni haere i te henua Aia ni matua mai raa, e meia na tama roo te matakaina Aia raa se hihai ki too Tama raa.  
\v 12 Emeia e isi na tama ni too Aia, tena ki hakattina hoki Tama raa, tena Aia ki kou ake na mahi na tama raa ki mee pera ma ni tamalliki TeAtua.  
\v 13 Na tama raa se mee pera ma ni tamalliki TeAtua i na mahi koi laatou ia ma e mee laatou e hannau mai pera ma ni tamalliki na tama i te maarama nei, e meia TeAtua Hokoia ko te Tamana na tamalliki raa. 
\p  
\v 14 Te Tattara raa e hamai no tipu tama, tena ki hamai ma na mahi hai mmahi no huri mai te hakamaoni TeAtua, tena Aia e nnoho hoki ma maatou. Maatou e kkite na mahi Aia, na mahi tera Aia ni too pera ma ko te tautahi Tama koi TeAtua. 
\p  
\v 15 Jon e tattara hoki i te Tama raa. Aia e tattara hakamaroa ma, “Teenei ko te tama Anau ni tattara atu kootou te saaita anau ni tattara ma, ‘Tama raa e me ki hamai i muri anau, e meia Aia e hakanaaniu roo i aruna anau, maitaname Aia ko na noho mai roo i mua anau ni haanau mai.’ ” 
\p  
\v 16 Taatou hakaatoa e hakatapu ria, e mee te laoi Tama raa e isi raa, tena Aia e tauhano te hakatapu taatou na vahao roo hakaatoa.  
\v 17 TeAtua e kou ake na tuaa raa iaa Moses, e meia te laoi ia ma te hakamaoni raa e hamai ma Jisas Krais.  
\v 18 Se hai tama ni kite TeAtua. Te Tamariki hokotahi raa koi, te Tama e ssau roo pera ma TeAtua tera e noho i te vahi Tamana, tena ki hakari mai taatou ki illoa TeAtua raa. 
\s1 Na tattara Jon te tama e hakoukou tapu na tama 
\r (Matiu 3.1–12; Mak 1.1–8; Luk 3.1–18) 
\p  
\v 19 Na tama hakamattua na Jiu i roto Jerusalem raa e kauna na maatua ia ma na tama i te kaha Levi raa ki oo no vahiri ake Jon ma, “Koai akoe?” 
\p  
\v 20 Ia Jon se kkaro hoki te tattara, tena aia ki tattara hakamatahua ake na tama raa ma, “Anau seai ma ko te Mesaia.” 
\p  
\v 21 Kito na tama raa ki vahiri ake hoki ma, “Tena kaa akoe koai? Akoe ko Elaija?” 
\p Tena Jon ki meake, “Seai, anau seai ma ko Elaija.” 
\p Kito na tama raa ki vahiri ake hoki ma, “Akoe ko te Profet maatou e hakattari raa?” 
\p Tena Jon ki meake, “Seai hoki.” 
\p  
\v 22 Kito na tama raa ki meake, “Tena iaa tattara mai ma akoe koai. Maatou e hihhai ki too ni tattara ki oo ma maatou no meake na tama ni kauna ria mai maatou raa. Ni tattara peehee akoe e isi ki tattara mai i te vahi akoe?” 
\p  
\v 23 Tena Jon ki meake te tattara e mmau i roto te launiu profet Aisaia ma, 
\q1 “Anau ko ‘te reo te tama e tattara i roto te kina e tuu mahoa raa ma: 
\q1 Tanattana te mateara TeAriki\f + \fr 1.23 \ft TeAriki: Na tattara nei e mmau i roto Aisaia 40.3. I roto te Old Testament se isi TeAriki e meia e isi koi Jihova\f* ki hamai vaa aruna!’ ” 
\m  
\v 24 Kito na tama na Farisi ni kauna ki oo ake raa  
\v 25 ku vahiri ake Jon ma, “Kame akoe seai ma ko te Mesaia, ia seai ma ko Elaija, ia seai ma he profet, tena kaa akoe e hakoukou tapu na tama naea?” 
\p  
\v 26 Tena Jon ki meake, “Anau e hakoukou tapu na tama ma te vai, e meia e isi te tama e tuu i roto kootou tera kootou se illoa.  
\v 27 Tama naa e me ki hamai i muri anau, e meia anau se tau hoki te ui na taka Aia e uru raa.” 
\p  
\v 28 Na tattara nei e kapihi mai i Betani i te vahi te anake i te riva Jordan raa; i te kina Jon e hakoukou tapu na tama raa. 
\s1 Te Sipsip TeAtua 
\p  
\v 29 Te aho taiao raa Jon ku kite Jisas e haere ake aia, tena ki meake, “Teenei ko te Sipsip TeAtua tera e me ki ssoro na hai sara te maarama nei raa i taha!  
\v 30 Teenei ko te Tama anau e tattara te saaita anau ni tattara atu ma, ‘E isi te tama e me ki hamai i muri anau, e meia Aia e hakanaaniu roo i aruna anau, maitaname Aia ko na noho mai roo avare i mua anau ni haanau mai.’  
\v 31 Anau se iroa hoki ma te Tama raa koai, e meia anau e hamai no hakoukou tapu kootou ma te vai ma ki lavaa kootou na tama Israel raa te illoa Tama raa.” 
\p  
\v 32 Tena Jon ki tattara ake na tama raa ma, “Anau e kite TeAnana Tapu raa e llee mai i raro pera ma he rupe no toko i aruna Tama raa.\fig TeAnana Tapu raa ku llee iho pera ma he rupe.|src="cn01656b.tif" size="col" ref="1.32" \fig* 
\v 33 Tena anau se iroa ma teeraa ko te Tama raa, e meia TeAtua, te Tama ni kauna ria mai anau ki hakoukou tapu ma te vai raa ni tattara mai anau ma, ‘Akoe e me ki kite TeAnana Tapu raa e llee mai i raro no toko i aruna he tama. Tena te Tama naa ko te tama e me ki hakoukou tapu ma TeAnana Tapu raa.’ ”  
\v 34 Tena Jon ki meake, “Anau ku kite te hakkatu nei, tena anau e meatu kootou pera ma te Tama nei ko te Tamariki TeAtua.” 
\s1 Na disaipol kaamata Jisas 
\p  
\v 35 Te aho taiao raa Jon ku tuu hoki i te kina raa ma tokorua na disaipol aia raa,  
\v 36 ia te saaita aia ni kite Jisas ku haere hakaraka, tena aia ki meake tokorua raa ma, “Teeraa ko te Sipsip TeAtua!” 
\p  
\v 37 Tokorua na disaipol raa e llono na tattara Jon raa, tena tokorua raa ki tauttari Jisas.  
\v 38 Jisas e hakatike no kite tokorua raa e tauttari Aia, tena Aia ki vahiri ake, “Koorua e sesee te aa?” 
\p Tena tokorua raa ki meake, “Rabai, Akoe e nohonoho vaa hee?” (Rabai e mee ma he “Tisa”.) 
\p  
\v 39 Tena Jisas ki meake, “Oo mai ki kkite koorua.” (Te mee raa kame ku tae te haa te hiahi.) Kito tokorua raa ki oo laatou ma Jisas no kkite te kina Tama raa e nohonoho raa, tena tokorua ki nnoho laatou ma Tama raa te aho naa hakaatoa. 
\p  
\v 40 Teeraa tama tokorua raa ko Andru, te taina Saimon Pita raa.  
\v 41 Tena Andru ki haere no ttiri Saimon Pita, tena aia ki meake, “Maaua e kkite te Mesaia.” (Te tattara nei e mee ma “Krais”.)  
\v 42 Tena aia ki too Saimon no oo laaua i te kina Jisas e noho raa. 
\p Jisas e kkira ake Saimon, tena ki meake, “Te inoa akoe raa ko Saimon te tamariki Jon, e meia akoe e me ki hui Sifas.” (Te inoa nei e mee ma “he hatu”.) 
\s1 Jisas e kanna Filip laaua ma Nataniel 
\p  
\v 43 Te aho taiao raa Jisas ku maanatu ma ki haere i Galili. Aia ku ttiri Filip, tena ki meake, “Tautari mai Anau!”  
\v 44 Filip he tama i Betsaida, te matakaina Andru laaua ma Pita raa.  
\v 45 Filip e haere no ttiri Nataniel, tena ki meake, “Maatou ku kkite te Tama Moses e taataa i roto te launiu na tuaa ia ma te tama hoki na profet raa ni tattaa mai raa. Tama raa ko Jisas te tamariki Josep, te tama i Nasaret.” 
\p  
\v 46 Kito Nataniel ki meake, “Aiea e isi te mee tauareka e lavaa te hamai i roto Nasaret?” 
\p Tena Filip ki meake, “Hamai ki kite akoe.” 
\p  
\v 47 Te saaita Jisas ni kite Nataniel e haere ake, Aia ku tattara ake i te vahi tama raa ma, “Teenei he tama hakamaoni Israel, tama nei se lavaa hoki te mariu!” 
\p  
\v 48 Kito Nataniel ki vahiri ake Jisas, “Akoe e iroa peehee anau?” 
\p Tena Jisas ki meake, “Anau e kite akoe e noho i raro te laakau fik raa i mua Filip ni haere atu no meatu akoe.” 
\p  
\v 49 Kito Nataniel ki meake, “Rabai, Akoe ko te Tamariki TeAtua! Akoe ko te Tuku Israel!” 
\p  
\v 50 Tena kito Jisas ki meake Nataniel, “Akoe ku hakatina koi e mee Anau e meatu ma Anau e kite akoe e noho i raro te laakau fik? Akoe e me ki kite na hakkatu e hakananniu i aruna te mee nei!”  
\v 51 Tena Jisas ki meake na tama raa, “Anau e tattara atu kootou te hakamaoni: kootou e me ki kkite te vaelani raa e taaraki, tena na ensel TeAtua raa e oo i aruna, tena ki oo mai i raro i aruna te Tamariki te Tama nei.” 
\c 2  
\s1 Te kai te avana i Kana 
\p  
\v 1 E isi te avana e me ki ttaohi i te matakaina i Kana i roto Galili i te aho tana hakatoru raa. Te tinna Jisas raa ku tae i te kina raa,  
\v 2 tena na tama raa e aru hoki Jisas ma na disaipol Aia raa ki oo ake i te kai te avana raa.  
\v 3 Na wain raa ku mmaha hakaatoa, tena Meri ki haere no meake Jisas ma, “Na tama raa ku se hai wain e me ki unu.” 
\p  
\v 4 Kito Jisas ki meake, “Taku tinna, akoe se tau te mee mai Anau hea Anau e me ki pena, maitaname te saaita hakamaoni Anau ki ppena na mee raa se ki tae.” 
\p  
\v 5 Tena te tinna Jisas raa ki meake na tama e hehekau te hare raa ma, “Kootou ki ppena hea Tama nei e meatu kootou.” 
\p  
\v 6 Na Jiu raa e tammaki roo na tuaa i te vahi te ssoro na tinotama laatou ia ma alaa mee hoki ki matahua, tera hea na tama raa e hakattuu na lloo vai e llahi raa ki sossoro na rima laatou raa ki tautari na tuaa raa. Te lloo hokotahi kaa pii kame e tae peeraa sanahuru ma rima, seai naa tipu rua ma rima na galon. \fig |alt="man filling water jars" src="LB00135B.TIF" size="col" ref="2.6–7" \fig* 
\v 7 Tena Jisas ki meake na tama e hehekau te hare raa, “Utu na lloo raa ki ppii na vaitea.” Na tama raa e utu na lloo raa no ppii oho roo,  
\v 8 tena Jisas ki meake na tama raa, “Ahu ni vai no kkave te tama hakamaatua te kai nei raa.” Na tama raa e ahu na vaitea  
\v 9 ku huri mo wain raa no kkave i te tama hakamaatua te kai raa, tena te tama raa ki kamata te vai raa. Te tama raa se iroa ma te wain raa e hamai i hee (e meia na tama hehekau ni ahu ake na wain raa hokolaatou koi e illoa); kito te tama raa ki kanna ake te tamatane e avana vahao nei raa ki haere ake,  
\v 10 tena aia ki meake te tama raa, “Na tama hakaatoa e taki na wain taualleka raa i mua, tena te saaita na tama hakaatoa ku vvare, tena laatou ku taki na wain se taualleka raa. Emeia akoe e hakkapi na wain taualleka nei no tae roo te saaita nei!” 
\p  
\v 11 Jisas e huri te mirakol kaamata nei i Kana i roto Galili; Aia e huri ake na mahi Aia raa i te kina raa, tena na disaipol Aia raa ku hakattina roo Tama raa. 
\p  
\v 12 I muri te kai te avana raa, Jisas ma te tinna Aia raa, na taina Aia raa, tena na disaipol Aia raa ku oo i Kaperneam no nnoho e llava na aho i te kina raa. 
\s1 Jisas e haere i roto Hare Tapu 
\r (Matiu 21.12–13; Mak 11.15–17; Luk 19.45–46) 
\p  
\v 13 Te saaita hoki te Kai te Pasova raa ku taapiri, tena Jisas ki haere i Jerusalem.  
\v 14 Jisas e haere i roto te Hare Tapu raa no kite na tama e tataui na bulmakau, na sipsip ia ma na rupe, tena na tama hoki e sesenisi na sileni raa e nnoho ma na tebol laatou raa.  
\v 15 Kito Jisas ki ssiri te maea raa, tena ki hakatui na manu raa hakaatoa i aho ma te Hare Tapu raa; na sipsip ia ma na bulmakau raa hoki, tena ki hakahuri na tebol na tama sesenisi na sileni raa no masseu na sileni na tama raa;  
\v 16 tena Aia ki hai ake na tama e nnoho ma na rupe raa, “Too na manu naa no kkave i taha ma te hare nei! Auu se mee te hare te Tamana Anau nei pera ma he maket!”  
\v 17 Na disaipol Jisas raa ku mannatu na tattara i roto te Launiu Tapu ma, “Te hihai anau i te hare Akoe nei raa e ttuni roo i roto anau pera ma he ahi.” 
\p  
\v 18 Tena na tama hakamattua na Jiu raa ku meake ma, “He mirakol peehee Akoe e lavaa te huri mai ki kkite maatou pera ma Akoe e isi na mahi hakamaoni ki hakaise na tama nei i taha?” 
\p  
\v 19 Kito Jisas ki meake, “Anau e me ki seu te Hare Tapu nei ki moe i raro, tena ku hakatuu hakaraoi te hare nei i roto e toru na aho.” \fig [caption?]|alt="temple of Herod" src="LB00250B.TIF" size="span" ref="2.19" \fig* 
\p  
\v 20 Tena na tama raa ki vahiri ake, “Akoe e me ki hakatuu hakaraoi te hare nei i roto e toru na aho? Te Hare Tapu nei e too roo tipu haa ma ono na hetau ki pena!” 
\p  
\v 21 Emeia te hare tapu Jisas e tattara raa ko te tinotama Aia.  
\v 22 Tena te saaita Jisas ni ora muri i taha ma te mate raa, na disaipol Aia raa ku mannatu na tattara Aia ni tattara ake raa, tena ki hakattina na tattara te Launiu Tapu raa ia ma na tattara Jisas ni tattara ake laatou raa. 
\s1 Jisas e iroa na tiputipu na tama hakaatoa 
\p  
\v 23 Jisas koi noho i Jerusalem te saaita te Kai te Pasova raa, tena tammaki na tama ku hakattina Tama raa, e mee na mirakol laatou e kkite Tama raa e ppena raa.  
\v 24 Emeia Jisas se huri ake roo te hakamaoni Aia i na tama raa, e mee Aia e iroa na hakataakoto na tama raa.  
\v 25 Niaina se hai tama e tattara ake Jisas na hakataakoto na tama raa, e meia Jisas ko na iroa roo avare hea i roto na hatu manava na tama raa. 
\c 3  
\s1 Jisas laaua ma Nikodimas 
\p  
\v 1 Nikodimas he tama hakamaatua na Jiu, tena aia e hukui hoki ma te kuturana na Farisi raa.  
\v 2 He poo hokotahi Nikodimas e haere ake iaa Jisas raa no vahiri ake Tama raa ma, “Rabai, maatou e illoa ma Akoe he tama TeAtua e kauna ria mai. Se hai tama e lavaa te ppena na mirakol Akoe e ppena raa kame TeAtua se hehekau i roto te tama naa.” 
\p  
\v 3 Kito Jisas ki meake, “Anau e meatu te hakamaoni: se hai tama e lavaa te tae i te Hakamaatua ana i te Vaelani raa kame aia se haanau mai hakaraoi.” 
\p  
\v 4 Tena Nikodimas ki meake, “Te tama ku matua raa e me ki haanau mai hakaraoi peehee? Te tama ku matua se lavaa te uru i roto te manava te tinna aia raa ki haanau mai hakaraoi!” 
\p  
\v 5 Kito Jisas ki meake, “Anau e tattara atu te hakamaoni, se hai tama e lavaa te tae i te Hakamaatua ana i te Vaelani raa kame aia se haanau mai ma te vai ia ma TeAnana Tapu.  
\v 6 Taatou e too na tinotama taatou nei i na maatua taatou, e meia taatou e too na anana taatou raa i TeAnana Tapu.  
\v 7 Auu se oho e mee Anau e meatu akoe pera ma kootou ki hannau mai hakaraoi.  
\v 8 Te matani raa e maairi mai te totoka hee aia e hihai ki maairi. Akoe e rono te matani raa e maairi, e meia akoe se iroa ma te matani raa e hamai i hee, ia e haere i hee. Te matani raa e ssau pera ma na tama hakaatoa e hannau mai ma TeAnana Tapu raa.” 
\p  
\v 9 Tena Nikodimas ki meake, “Te mee nei e me ki kapihi mai peehee?” 
\p  
\v 10 Kito Jisas ki meake, “Akoe he tama hakamaatua e akoako i roto Israel, e meia akoe se iroa na tattara nei?  
\v 11 Anau e tattara atu te hakamaoni: maatou e tattara atu na mee maatou e illoa raa, tena ki tattara atu hoki na mee maatou e kkite raa, e meia se hai tama kootou e hihhai ki hakallono na tattara maatou raa.  
\v 12 Kootou se hakattina Anau te saaita Anau e tattara atu na mee i te maarama nei; kaa kootou e me ki hakattina peehee kame Anau ni tattara atu na mee i te vaelani raa?  
\v 13 Se hai tama roo hokotahi ni haere i aruna i te vaelani, teeraa ko te Tamariki te Tama nei koi, te Tama ni hamai i raro i taha ma te vaelani raa.” 
\p  
\v 14 Te Tamariki te Tama nei e me ki ssau ria i aruna pera ma Moses ni ssau te lapono e pena i na katanatea raa,  
\v 15 tena na tama e hakattina Tama raa e me ki too te ora e ora tahi.  
\v 16 Maitaname TeAtua e laoi mahi roo na tama i te maarama nei, tena Aia ki kou mai te tautahi Tama Aia raa, tena na tama hakaatoa e hakattina i Tamariki raa se lavaa te mmate, e meia na tama naa e me ki too te ora e ora tahi.  
\v 17 Maitaname TeAtua se kou mai te Tamariki Aia raa i te maarama nei ki mee mo tama hakatonutonu, e meia Aia e kou mai Tamariki Aia raa ki tokonaki na tama i te maarama nei raa ki ora. 
\p  
\v 18 Na tama e hakattina i te Tamariki TeAtua raa se lavaa te hakatonutonu ria; e meia na tama se hakattina raa ko na hakatonutonu ria avare, maitaname laatou ni se hakattina i te Tamariki TeAtua raa.  
\v 19 TeAtua e me ki hakatonutonu na tama i te maarama nei raa peenei: te Maahina raa ku oti te hamai i te maarama nei, e meia na tama raa e hihhai koi te pouri raa, tena ki tiaki te Maahina raa, maitaname na tiputipu laatou raa e sakkino.  
\v 20 Na tama hakaatoa e ppena na tiputipu sakkino raa se hihhai te Maahina raa, ia se hihai hoki ki oo ake i te kina te Maahina raa, maitaname na tama raa se hihhai ma na tama ki illoa na tiputipu sakkino laatou raa.  
\v 21 Emeia na tama ni ppena na tiputipu e ttonu raa ku oo ake i te Maahina raa ma ki lavaa te Maahina raa te huri ake pera ma laatou e hakallono no tauttari hea TeAtua e hihai raa. 
\s1 Jisas laaua ma Jon Baptis 
\p  
\v 22 Tena ki oti, Jisas ma na disaipol Aia raa ku oo i te matakaina Judia raa, tena Aia ki nnoho ma na tama raa e llava na aho no hakoukou tapu na tama raa.  
\v 23 Jon hoki e hakoukou tapu na tama i Aenon, taapiri te matakaina i Salim raa, maitaname te kina raa e tammaki na vai. Na tama e oo ake iaa Jon, tena aia ki hakoukou tapu na tama raa.  
\v 24 (Te mee nei e kapihi mai i mua Jon ni ponotia i roto te hare karapusi raa.) 
\p  
\v 25 E isi na disaipol Jon e hakataukoti ma na Jiu i te vahi te tuaa ki ssoro na mee ki matahua raa.  
\v 26 Kito na disaipol Jon raa ki oo ake no meake Jon ma, “Rabai, akoe e maanatu te tanata ni ttuu koorua i te vahi te anake i te riva Jordan; te Tama akoe ni tattara mai raa? Te Tama raa ku kaamata no hakoukou tapu na tama te saaita nei, tena na tama hakaatoa ku oo ake i te Tama raa!” 
\p  
\v 27 Kito Jon ki meake, “Se hai tama e lavaa te isi na mee kame TeAtua se kou ake ni mee ma te tama raa.  
\v 28 Kootou hokkootou e llono na maihu anau te saaita anau ni tattara atu ma, ‘Anau seai ma ko te Mesaia, e meia anau e kauna ria mai koi ki hamai i mua Tama raa.’  
\v 29 Kame he taupeara e avana vahao nei, tena te hine aia e avana raa he hine aia, e meia te soa laoi roo te taupeara raa e me ki hihia roo te saaita aia e rono te reo te taupeara ku avana raa. Tera hea anau e hihia roo i roto anau.  
\v 30 Te Tama naa e me ki haere roo no hakanaaniu, tena anau e me ki haere sara no mouraro.” 
\s1 Jisas he Tama e hamai i te vaelani 
\p  
\v 31 Te Tama e hamai i te vaelani raa e hakanaaniu i aruna na tama hakaatoa. Te tama e haanau mai i roto te maarama nei raa he tama te maarama nei, tena aia e me ki tattara koi na mee i te maarama nei, e meia te Tama e hamai i te vaelani raa e hakanaaniu i aruna na mee roo hakaatoa.  
\v 32 Tama raa e me ki tattara mai na mee Aia ni kite ia ma na mee Aia ni rono raa, e meia se hai tama e hihai ki hakarono na tattara Tama raa.  
\v 33 Tena te tama e tautari na tattara Tama raa e me ki huri ake pera ma TeAtua e hakamaoni.  
\v 34 Te Tama TeAtua e kauna ria mai raa e tattara na tattara TeAtua, maitaname TeAtua e kou ake TeAnana Tapu raa ki noho i roto Tama raa.  
\v 35 TeAtua e laoi roo te Tamariki Aia raa, tena ki kou ake na mahi Tama raa ma ki rorohi na mee hakaatoa.  
\v 36 Te tama e hakatina te Tamariki TeAtua raa e me ki too te ora e ora tahi; te tama se hakatina te Tamariki TeAtua raa se lavaa te too te ora e ora tahi, e meia aia e me ki too na hakalono llihu TeAtua. 
\c 4  
\s1 Jisas ma te hine i Samaria 
\p  
\v 1 Na Farisi raa ku llono pera ma na tama Jisas e hakoukou tapu raa ku tammaki roo i aruna na tama Jon ni hakoukou tapu raa.  
\v 2 (Emeia te hakamaoni Jisas se hai tama ni hakoukou tapu, aaraa ko na disaipol Aia raa koi e hakoukou tapu na tama.)  
\v 3 Te saaita Jisas ni rono na tattara na tama raa, tena Aia ku tiaki Judia no vaakai i Galili;  
\v 4 tena ki haere vaa roto Samaria te saaita Aia ni vaakai raa. 
\p  
\v 5 Aia e haere vaa roto Samaria no tae te matakaina Saikar, se mmao hoki ma te paupaku Jekop ni kou ake ma Josep, te tamariki aia raa.  
\v 6 Te vai Jekop ni keri raa e tuu i te kina raa, tena Jisas ki haere no noho i te vahi te vai raa e mee Aia ku naenae te hahaere. Te mee raa kame ku tae te laa latea. 
\p  
\v 7 Tena he hine i Samaria ku hamai ki ahu na vai, tena Jisas ki meake te hine raa, “Ahu mai he vai ki unu Anau.”\fig Jisas e kainno ake te vai i te hine Samaria.|alt="Jesus and Samaritan woman at well" src="LB00302B.TIF" size="span" ref="4.7" \fig* 
\v 8 (Na disaipol Jisas raa e oo i roto te matakaina raa ma ki sui ni kai.) 
\p  
\v 9 Kito te hine raa ki meake, “Akoe he Jiu, tena anau he tama i Samaria. Kaa Akoe e lavaa peehee te kainno mai anau ki ahu he vai ki unu Akoe?” (Na Jiu raa e ttapu te unu na kapu, ia te kkai na parete na tama i Samaria.) 
\p  
\v 10 Tena Jisas ki meake, “Kame koi akoe e iroa na mee TeAtua e kou atu raa ia ma te Tama e kainno atu akoe ki ahu ake he vai raa, tena akoe ku kainno ake te Tama naa, tena te Tama naa e me ki kou atu te vai te ora raa.” 
\p  
\v 11 Kito te hine raa ki meake, “Akoe se isi te puu, tena te vai nei hoki e nnoto. Kaa Akoe e me ki too te vai te ora naa i hee?  
\v 12 Jekop te tipuna taatou i mua raa e kou mai te vai nei ma maatou, tena aia ma na tamalliki aia raa ia ma na manu aia raa hakaatoa ni unuunu te vai nei. Eaa Akoe e maanatu ma Akoe e hakanaaniu i aruna Jekop?” 
\p  
\v 13 Tena Jisas ki meake, “Na tama hakaatoa e unu te vai nei raa e me ki hiunu hakaraoi,  
\v 14 e meia na tama e unu te vai Anau e me ki kou ake raa se lavaa te hiunu hakaraoi. Te vai Anau e me ki kou ake raa e me ki mee pera ma he vai e tere, tena te vai te ora raa e me ki kou ake te tama naa te ora e ora tahi.” 
\p  
\v 15 Kito te hine raa ki meake, “TeAriki, kou mai te vai naa i anau! Tena anau e me ki se lavaa te hiunu hakaraoi, ia anau se lavaa hoki te hamai no ahuahu tahi na vai.” 
\p  
\v 16 Tena Jisas ki meake te hine raa, “Haere no meake te avana akoe raa, tena koorua ku oo mai.” 
\p  
\v 17 Kito te hine raa ki meake, “Anau se isi te avana.” 
\p Tena Jisas ki meake, “Akoe e tattara te hakamaoni te saaita akoe e mee mai ma akoe se isi te avana.  
\v 18 Akoe ni avana e rima na taanata i mua, tena te tanata akoe e noho ma akoe te saaita nei raa seai ma he avana akoe hakamaoni. Akoe e tattara mai Anau te hakamaoni.” 
\p  
\v 19 Kito te hine raa ki meake, “TeAriki, anau e kite pera ma Akoe he profet.  
\v 20 Na tipuna maatou i Samaria raa e lotulotu TeAtua i aruna te mouna nei, e meia kootou na Jiu raa e mee ma Jerusalem ko te kina hakamaoni maatou e tau te lotulotu ake TeAtua.” 
\p  
\v 21 Tena Jisas ki meake te hine raa, “Akoe ki hakatina Anau, e mee e isi te saaita koi hamai tera na tama se lavaa te lotulotu ake TeAtua i aruna te mouna nei ia ma i roto Jerusalem.  
\v 22 Kootou na tama i Samaria raa se illoa te Tama kootou e lotulotu raa; e meia maatou na Jiu raa e illoa te Tama maatou e lotulotu raa, maitaname te Tama e me ki tokonaki na tama ki ora raa e me ki hamai i Jerusalem.  
\v 23 Emeia te saaita e me ki hamai raa ku oti te tae mai, te saaita na tama e me ki lotulotu hakamaoni TeAtua i na mahi TeAnana Tapu raa, tena ku lotu ake TeAtua te lotulotu hakamaoni Tama raa e hihai raa.  
\v 24 TeAtua ko TeAnana Tapu, tena na tama e lavaa koi te lotu hakamaoni ake Tama raa i na mahi TeAnana Tapu.” 
\p  
\v 25 Kito te hine raa ki meake Jisas, “Anau e iroa pera ma te Mesaia raa e me ki hamai, tena te saaita Aia e hamai raa, Aia e me ki hakari mai na mee roo hakaatoa.” 
\p  
\v 26 Tena Jisas ki meake, “Teenei Anau nei, te Tama e tattara atu nei.” 
\p  
\v 27 Na disaipol raa ku ttae ake te vahao naa, tena na tama raa e oho roo e mee laatou e kkite Jisas e tattara ma te hine raa. Emeia se hai tama na tama naa e vahiri ake te hine raa ma, “Hea akoe e hihai?” iaa se hai tama e vahiri ake hoki Jisas ma, “Aiea Akoe e tattara ma te hine raa raea?” 
\p  
\v 28 Kito te hine raa ki tiaki te lloo vaitea aia raa no vaakai i te matakaina raa no tattara ake na tama i te kina raa ma,  
\v 29 “Oo mai no mata te tama e hakari mai anau na mee hakaatoa anau ni ppena i mua raa. Eaa, te tama raa seai ma ko te Mesaia raa koi?”  
\v 30 Kito na tama raa ki tiaki te matakaina laatou raa ma ki oo no mmata Jisas. 
\p  
\v 31 Te saaita naa hoki na disaipol raa ku hakorokoro ma Jisas ki too ni kai no kai. 
\p  
\v 32 Emeia Jisas e meake, “Anau e isi na kai e kai tera kootou se illoa.” 
\p  
\v 33 Kito na disaipol raa ki vahihhiri hokolaatou ma, “E isi te tama ni kou ake na kai te Tama nei no kai?” 
\p  
\v 34 Tena Jisas ki meake, “Anau ki tautari te hihai te Tama ni kauna ria mai Anau raa, tena ku hakaoti hea Aia ni kou mai Anau ki ppena raa, aanaa na kai Anau.  
\v 35 Kootou e isi te tattara ma, ‘E haa na marama koi mmoe, tena taatou ku oo no haki na hua raa.’ Emeia Anau e meatu kootou ki kkira i roto na paupaku raa; na hua raa ku lleu, tena ku tau te haki.  
\v 36 Te tama e haki no hakatau na hua raa e me ki taui ria ma te ora e ora tahi, tena te tama e ttori raa laaua ma te tama e haki raa e me ki hihhia hakaatoa.  
\v 37 Te tattara e mee ma, ‘Teeraa tama e ttori, tena teeraa tama ku haki raa,’ e hakamaoni roo.  
\v 38 Anau e kauna kootou ki oo no haki na hua i roto na paupaku kootou se anaana raa; alaa tama ni hehekau i te paupaku naa, tena kootou e me ki too te laoi i na kahota na tama naa.” 
\p  
\v 39 Tammaki na tama i roto Samaria ku hakattina iaa Jisas e mee te hine raa ni tattara ake laatou ma, “Tama raa e hakari mai anau na mee hakaatoa anau ni ppena i mua raa.”  
\v 40 Tena te saaita na tama i Samaria raa ni ttiri Jisas, na tama raa ku meake Tama raa ma ki nnoho laatou, tena Jisas ki noho ma na tama raa e rua na aho. 
\p  
\v 41 Ia tammaki roo na tama ku hakattina e mee na tattara Tama raa,  
\v 42 kito na tama raa ki meake te hine raa, “Teenei maatou ku hakattina, ia maatou se mee ma e hakattina e mee na tattara akoe ni tattara mai raa, e meia maatou e hakattina e mee maatou hokomaatou roo ku llono na tattara Tama raa, tena maatou ku illoa pera ma Tama raa ko te Tokonaki na tama te maarama nei.” 
\s1 Jisas e tokonaki te tamariki te tama hakamaatua 
\p  
\v 43 Jisas e noho te matakaina raa e rua na aho no oti, tena Aia ki haere i Galili.  
\v 44 Maitaname Jisas Hokoia ni tattara ma, “Te profet e me ki se hihai ria i te matakaina roo aia.”  
\v 45 Te saaita Aia ni tae i Galili raa, na tama te matakaina raa ku too hakaraoi roo Tama raa, maitaname laatou ni oo i te Kai te Pasova i Jerusalem raa no kkite na mee hakaatoa Jisas ni ppena te saaita te kai raa. 
\p  
\v 46 Kito Jisas ki vaakai i Kana i roto Galili i te kina Aia ni huri te vai raa mo wain. Tena he tama hakamaatua te taumani, te tamariki aia raa e laavea i Kaperneam, e noho i te kina raa.  
\v 47 Te saaita aia ni rono ma Jisas ku tae ake i Galili, te tama raa ku haere ake iaa Jisas no meake Tama raa ma ki oo laaua i Kaperneam no tokonaki te tamariki aia ku taapiri ki mate raa ki tauareka.  
\v 48 Tena Jisas ki meake tama raa, “Kootou e hihhai ki kkite na mirakol ia ma na mee taualleka, tena kootou ki hakattina.” 
\p  
\v 49 Tena te tama hakamaatua raa ki meake, “TeAriki, hamai ki oo taaua i mua te tamariki anau raa e mate.” 
\p  
\v 50 Kito Jisas ki meake, “Haere, te tamariki akoe naa e me ki tauareka!” 
\p Te tama raa e hakatina na tattara Jisas raa, tena aia ki haere.  
\v 51 Te tama raa koi haere atu koi, tena na tama hehekau aia raa ku oo ake no ttiri te tama raa i aruna te mateara, tena ki meake, “Te tamariki akoe raa ku tauareka!” 
\p  
\v 52 Kito te tamana te tamariki raa ki vahiri ake ma te tamariki raa e kaamata vahao hee no tauareka. Tena na tama raa ki meake, “Te vvela te tamariki raa e hopo te tahi te hiahi te aho raa.” 
\p  
\v 53 Tena te tamana te tamariki raa ku maanatu ma teenaa ko te saaita roo Jisas ni meake aia ma, “Te tamariki akoe raa e me ki tauareka.” Tena aia ma na tama te hare aia raa hakaatoa ku hakattina. 
\p  
\v 54 Teenei ko te mirakol hakarua Jisas ni ppena te saaita Aia ni tiaki Judia no haere i Galili raa. 
\c 5  
\s1 Jisas e tokonaki te tama no tauareka i te kina te vai 
\p  
\v 1 Tena ki oti roo Jisas ku haere i Jerusalem e mee te kai e rahi na Jiu raa e me ki ttaohi raa.  
\v 2 Tena he vai i te kina raa e tuu taapiri te Totoka na Sipsip tera e isi e rima na paaro raa; te vai raa e hui ma Betesda i na tattara na Hibru.  
\v 3 4 E tammaki na tama lavvea e moemmoe vaa raro na paaro raa: na tama e sseni, na tama na vae e mmate ia ma na tama se lavaa te hahaere. [Na tama raa e mmoe no hakattari te vai raa ki mmioo, maitaname e isi roo na saaita te ensel TeAriki raa e me ki haere iho no mee te vai raa ki mmioo, tena te tama laavea kaamata roo e llee i roto te vai raa e me ki tauareka ma te maahana aia raa.]  
\v 5 Tena he tanata e laavea i roto tipu toru ma varu na hetau e moe i te kina raa.  
\v 6 Jisas e kite te tanata raa e moe i te kina raa, tena Aia e iroa ma te tanata raa e laavea te saaita roroa roo; kito Jisas ki meake te tanata raa, “Akoe e hihai ki tauareka?” 
\p  
\v 7 Kito te tanata e laavea raa ki meake, “TeAriki, se hai tama e me ki tokonaki ki kkave anau te saaita te vai raa e mmioo; te saaita anau koi hahaivi atu koi, teeraa tama ku tae koi i mua.” 
\p  
\v 8 Kito Jisas ki meake te tanata raa, “Mahike i aruna no too te moena akoe naa no haere.”  
\v 9 Te saaita naa koi te tanata raa ku tauareka, tena aia ki too te moena aia raa no haere. 
\p Te aho Jisas e mee te tama raa no tauareka raa he aho te Sabat,  
\v 10 tena na tama hakamattua na Jiu raa ku meake te tanata ku tauareka raa ma, “Teenei he aho te Sabat, tena na tuaa raa e mee ma e tapu akoe te amo te moena akoe naa i te aho nei.” 
\p  
\v 11 Kito te tanata raa ki meake, “Te tama e tokonaki anau no tauareka raa e mee mai ma anau ki too te moena anau nei no haere.” 
\p  
\v 12 Kito na tama raa ki vahiri ake te tama raa, “Koai te tama e meatu ma akoe ki too te moena akoe naa no haere naa?” 
\p  
\v 13 Emeia te tanata ku tauareka raa se iroa ma Jisas koai, maitaname te kina raa e tammaki roo na tama, tena Jisas e haere uru koi vaa roto na tama raa no haere i taha. 
\p  
\v 14 Tena ki oti Jisas ku ttiri te tama raa i roto te Hare Tapu, tena Aia ki meake, “Hakarono, akoe ku tauareka vahao nei, tena hakaoti te ppena na mee sakkino, kaa seai na mee sakkino roo e me ki ttae atu akoe.” 
\p  
\v 15 Tena te tanata raa ki haere no tattara ake na tama hakamattua na Jiu raa ma teeraa ko Jisas ni tokonaki aia no tauareka.  
\v 16 Kito na tama raa ki kaamata no tattara sakkino roo iaa Jisas, e mee Tama raa e tokonaki te tanata raa no tauareka i te aho te Sabat.  
\v 17 Tena Jisas ki meake na Jiu raa, “Te Tamana Anau raa se hai vahao e hamaroroo, tera hea Anau e uata tahi koi.” 
\p  
\v 18 Te tattara nei e mee roo na hakataakoto na tama hakamattua na Jiu raa no mmaha ma ki taa Jisas ki mate, e mee Jisas se mee ma e seu koi na tuaa te Sabat raa, e meia Tama raa e tattara hoki pera ma TeAtua ko te Tamana Aia, tena na tattara Aia raa e huri ake pera ma laaua ma TeAtua e hokotahi. 
\s1 Na mahi te Tamariki TeAtua 
\p  
\v 19 Kito Jisas ki meake na Jiu raa, “Anau e tattara atu te hakamaoni: Te Tamariki TeAtua raa se lavaa te ppena na mee i te hakataakoto koi Aia; Aia e ppena koi na mee Aia e kite te Tamana Aia raa e ppena raa. Hea te Tamana raa e ppena, te Tamariki raa hoki e me ki pena.  
\v 20 Maitaname te Tamana raa e laoi roo te Tamariki Aia raa, tena ki huri ake na mee hakaatoa Aia e ppena raa. Tama raa e me ki huri ake te Tamariki Aia raa ki ppena na mee e llahi roo i aruna na mee nei, tena kootou e me ki mahharo.  
\v 21 E ssau koi pera ma te Tamana raa e hakamahike na tama ku mmate raa, tena ki kou ake na ora na tama raa, tena te Tamariki raa hoki e me ki kou ake na ora na tama Aia ni hirihiri raa.  
\v 22 Te Tamana se hakatonutonu na tama, e meia Aia e kou ake na mahi hakaatoa te Tamariki Aia raa ki hakatonutonu na tama,  
\v 23 ki lavaa na tama hakaatoa te hakammaha te Tamariki raa e ssau pera ma laatou e hakammaha te Tamana raa. Koai te tama se hakammaha te Tamariki raa, se hakammaha hoki te Tamana tera ni kauna ria mai Tama raa. 
\p  
\v 24 “Anau e tattara atu te hakamaoni: na tama e llono na tattara Anau, tena ki hakattina i te Tama ni kauna ria mai Anau raa e me ki too te ora e ora tahi. Na tama raa se lavaa te hakatonutonu ria, e meia na tama raa ku hhiti i taha ma na mahi te mate no ora.  
\v 25 Anau e tattara atu te hakamaoni: e isi te saaita koi hamai, e meia te saaita naa ku oti te tae mai, te saaita na tama ku oti te mmate raa e me ki llono te reo te Tamariki TeAtua raa, tena na tama e llono te reo raa e me ki ora.  
\v 26 Te Tamana raa ko te tahito te ora, ia tena Aia e kou ake hoki na mahi te Tamariki Aia raa ki tahito te ora e ssau pera ma Aia raa hoki.  
\v 27 Tena Aia ki kou ake na mahi te Tamariki Aia raa ki hakatonutonu na tama, maitaname Tama raa ko te Tamariki te Tama nei.  
\v 28 Auu se oho i na tattara Anau e mee ma; e isi te saaita koi hamai, te saaita na tama hakaatoa ni mmate raa e me ki llono te reo Anau,  
\v 29 tena ku oo iho i taha ma na taruma laatou raa, tena na tama ni ppena na mee taualleka raa e me ki mahhike no ora, ia na tama e ppena na mee sakkino raa e me ki mahhike no too na hakalono llihu. 
\s1 Jisas ko te Tama TeAtua 
\p  
\v 30 “Anau se lavaa te ppena he mee i na mahi Anau Hokonnau; Anau e hakatonutonu koi tautari hea TeAtua e mee mai Anau raa, tena te hakatonutonu Anau raa e tonu, maitaname Anau se hahaivi ma ki ppena hea Anau e hihai, e meia Anau e ppena hea te Tama ni kauna ria mai Anau raa e hihai. 
\p  
\v 31 “Kame Anau e tattara koi i te vahi Anau Hokonnau, tena na tattara Anau e tattara raa se isi te hakamaoni.  
\v 32 Emeia e isi te tama e me ki tattara i te vahi Anau, tena Anau e iroa pera ma na tattara te tama raa e tattara i te vahi Anau raa e hakamaoni.  
\v 33 Kootou ni kauna na tama kootou raa iaa Jon, tena tama raa ki tattara atu i te vahi te hakamaoni raa.  
\v 34 Anau se tau hoki te ssee he tama i te maarama nei ki tattara atu kootou i te vahi Anau; Anau e tattara atu koi ma ki tokonaki kootou ki ora.  
\v 35 Jon e ssau pera ma he lamu e ura ki hakamaahina atu kootou, tena kootou e hihhai ma ki hihhia paa saaita koi i te maahina tama raa.  
\v 36 Emeia e isi na mee e tattara i te vahi Anau tera e hakanaaniu i aruna na tattara Jon raa: na mee anau e ppena raa, aanaa ko na mee te Tamana ni kou mai Anau ki ppena raa, tena na mee nei e tattara i te vahi Anau, tena ki huri atu hoki pera ma te Tamana e kauna ria mai Anau.  
\v 37 Tena te Tamana ni kauna ria mai Anau raa e tattara hoki i te vahi Anau. Kootou se hai vahao e llono te reo Tama raa, ia se kkite na karemata Tama raa,  
\v 38 tena kootou ki se ttaohi mmau na tattara Tama raa i roto na hatu manava kootou, maitaname kootou se hakattina i te Tama Tama raa ni kauna ria mai raa.  
\v 39 Kootou e paupau te Launiu Tapu raa, maitaname kootou e mannatu ma kootou e me ki lave te ora e ora tahi raa i roto te launiu raa. Tena te Launiu Tapu kootou e paupau raa e tattara i te vahi Anau!  
\v 40 Emeia kootou se hihhai ki oo mai Anau no too te ora e ora tahi raa. 
\p  
\v 41 “Anau se mee ma na tama te maarama nei raa ki hakammaha Anau.  
\v 42 Emeia Anau e iroa na tiputipu kootou, tena Anau e iroa hoki pera ma kootou se laoi hakamaoni TeAtua i roto na hatu manava kootou.  
\v 43 Anau e hamai ma na mahi te Tamana Anau raa, e meia kootou se hihai ki too Anau; ia tena kame he tama e hamai i te vahi aia hokoia, kootou e hihai roo ki too tama raa.  
\v 44 Kootou e hihhai roo kame alaa tama e hakammaha kootou, e meia kootou se hahaivi ma ki mee TeAtua ki hakammaha kootou. Tena, kaa kootou e me ki hakattina peehee Anau?  
\v 45 Tena auu se mannatu ma Anau ko te tama e me ki ppau atu na hai sara kootou raa i mua te Tamana Anau raa. Moses te tama kootou e hakattina raa ko te tama e me ki ppau atu na hai sara kootou ni ppena raa.  
\v 46 Kame kootou ni hakattina hakamaoni Moses, kootou e me ki hakattina hoki Anau, maitaname tama raa ni taataa atu hoki i te vahi Anau.  
\v 47 Emeia kootou se hakattina hea Moses ni taataa raa, tena kaa kootou e me ki hakattina peehee na tattara Anau raa?” 
\c 6  
\s1 Jisas e haanai te kanohenua e tammaki roo 
\r (Matiu 14.13–21; Mak 6.30–44; Luk 9.10–17) 
\p  
\v 1 Tena ki oti Jisas ku tere no tae teeraa vahi te Namo Galili raa (te Namo nei alaa tama e kanna ma te Namo Taiberias).\fig Te Namo Galili e kannoo hoki ma te Namo Taiberias.|alt="Sea of Galilee" src="HK00340B.TIF" size="span" ref="6.1" \fig* 
\v 2 Tena he kanohenua e rahi roo e tauttari Jisas, maitaname laatou ni kkite na mahi Tama raa ni tokonaki na tama e lavvea raa no taualleka.  
\v 3 Jisas e kake te paa mouna no nnoho ma na disaipol Aia raa.  
\v 4 Te saaita naa te Kai te Pasova raa ku taapiri hoki.  
\v 5 Jisas e kkira hakataka no kite te kanohenua e rahi roo ku oo ake Aia, tena Aia ki kanna ake Filip, “Te kina hee taatou e lavaa te sui ni kai e llava ki haanai te kanohenua nei?”  
\v 6 (Jisas e meake koi ma ki haaite Filip; e meia te hakamaoni, Aia ko na iroa roo avare hea Aia e me ki pena.) 
\p  
\v 7 Kito Filip ki meake, “Na tama nei hakaatoa se lavaa te isi na kai ki kkai kame taatou e too rua huitarau na siliva ma ki sui ni kai ki hannai na tama nei.” 
\p  
\v 8 Tena teeraa disaipol hoki, Andru te taina Saimon Pita raa ki meake,  
\v 9 “He tamariki tanata i te kina nei e isi e rima na haraoa e pena i na bali ia ma e rua na ika. Emeia na mee nei e me ki se tau roo ma te kanohenua nei.” 
\p  
\v 10 Kito Jisas ki meake na tama raa, “Meake te kanohenua raa ki nnoho i raro” (Te kina raa e hhomo na veve roo hakaatoa.) Kito te kanohenua raa ki nnoho i raro, tena te kooina na taanata raa hakaatoa kame e ttae rima simata.  
\v 11 Tena Jisas ki too na haraoa raa no lotu ake TeAtua, tena ki vaevae ake i na tama e nnoho i te kina raa. Jisas e mee peeraa hoki na ika raa. Tena na tama raa hakaatoa e kkai roo no ppohu. 
\p  
\v 12 Na tama raa e kkai roo no ppohu hakaatoa, tena Jisas ki meake na disaipol Aia raa ma, “Hakanaopo na kai e ttoe raa, taatou ki se kkai puamu.”  
\v 13 Kito na tama raa ki haere koko na muri haraoa ia ma na ika na tama raa ni kkai no ttoe raa no sasao sanahuru ma rua na kete no ppii. 
\p  
\v 14 Te kanohenua raa ku kkite te mirakol Jisas ni ppena raa, tena na tama raa ki tattara ma, “Hakamaoni, teenei ko te Profet: te Tama te Launiu Tapu raa e tattara ma e me ki hamai i te maarama nei raa!”  
\v 15 Jisas e iroa pera ma na tama raa ku mee ma ki oo ake no ttaohi Aia ki mee mo tuku, tena Aia ki tiaki na tama raa no haere Hokoia koi i te kina na mouna raa. 
\s1 Jisas e haere vaa aruna te lottai 
\r (Matiu 14.22–33; Mak 6.45–52) 
\p  
\v 16 Te saaita te mee raa ku hiahi, na disaipol Jisas raa ku oo i tai  
\v 17 no kakke te vaka raa no tere peeraa i Kaperneam, he matakaina e tuu i teeraa vahi te namo raa. Te mee raa ku poo, tena Jisas se ki tae ake roo i laatou.  
\v 18 Te saaita naa te matani raa ku kaamata no maairi, tena te moana raa hoki ku pepeau.  
\v 19 Na disaipol raa e aro no mmao roo i taha ma te henua raa\f + \fr 6.19 \ft English e hahaaite na mael ki haaite te mmao te kina, tena na tama raa kame ku mmao peeraa e rima seai naa e ono na mael\f*, tena laatou ku kkite Jisas e haere ake vaa aruna te lottai no haere hakataapiri ake roo te vaka raa, tena na disaipol raa ku mattaku roo.  
\v 20 Kito Jisas ki meake, “Auu se mattaku, teenei ko Nau!”  
\v 21 Na disaipol raa ku mee koi ma ki hakkake Tama raa i roto te vaka raa, tena te saaita naa koi te vaka raa ku tae i te kina laatou e tere raa. 
\s1 Te kanohenua raa ku sesee Jisas 
\p  
\v 22 Te aho taiao raa te kanohenua ni nnoho teeraa vahi raa ku illoa ma teeraa he vaka hokotahi koi ni tautau i te kina raa. Na tama raa e illoa ma Jisas ni se kakke laatou ma na disaipol raa i roto te vaka raa; na disaipol raa ni tiaki Tama raa i te kina raa no tere.  
\v 23 Tena alaa vaka e huro mai peeraa i Taiberias ku hakauu ake i te kina raa; te kina te kanohenua raa ni kkai na haraoa TeAriki ni hakatapu raa.  
\v 24 Te saaita te kanohenua raa ku illoa pera ma Jisas ku seai i te kina raa ma na disaipol Aia raa, na tama raa ku kakke na vaka raa no huro peeraa i Kaperneam no sesee Jisas. 
\s1 Jisas ko te Haraoa te Ora 
\p  
\v 25 Te kanohenua raa ku kkite Jisas i teeraa vahi te namo raa, tena na tama raa ki vahiri ake Tama raa ma, “Rabai, Akoe ni tae mai i te kina nei vahao hee?” 
\p  
\v 26 Kito Jisas ki meake, “Anau e tattara atu te hakamaoni: kootou e sesee Anau raa e mee kootou ni kkai na haraoa raa no ppohu roo kootou, ia te sesee kootou raa se mee ma kootou e illoa na mirakol Anau raa.  
\v 27 Auu se hakatettere mahi i na kai tera e me ki ppara raa, e meia hakatettere i na kai tera e me ki kou atu te ora e ora tahi raa. Aanei ko na kai te Tamariki te Tama nei e me ki kou atu kootou, maitaname TeAtua Tamana raa ku oti te tuku te hakamaatino Aia raa i aruna Tama raa.” 
\p  
\v 28 Kito na tama raa ki vahiri ake, “Kaa hea maatou e me ki ppena ki lavaa maatou te ppena na mee TeAtua e hihai ma maatou ki ppena raa?” 
\p  
\v 29 Tena Jisas ki meake, “Teenei hea TeAtua e hihai ma kootou ki ppena: kootou ki hakattina i te Tama Aia ni kauna ria mai raa.” 
\p  
\v 30 Kito na tama raa ki meake, “He mirakol peehee Akoe e lavaa te ppena ki hakattina maatou i Akoe? Hea Akoe e me ki ppena?  
\v 31 Na tipuna maatou raa e kkai na ‘mana’ i te kina e tuu mahoa raa, ia pera ma te Launiu Tapu raa e tattara ma, 
\q1 ‘Tama raa e kou ake na haraoa i te vaelani raa no kkai na tama raa.’ ” 
\m  
\v 32 Tena Jisas ki meake, “Anau e tattara atu te hakamaoni, te haraoa Moses e kou atu raa seai ma ko te haraoa i te vaelani raa; teeraa ko te Tamana Anau raa e kou atu kootou te haraoa hakamaoni i te vaelani raa.  
\v 33 Maitaname te haraoa TeAtua e kou atu raa ko te tama e hamai i taha ma te vaelani ki kou atu te ora hakamaoni i na tama te maarama nei raa.” 
\p  
\v 34 Kito na tama raa ki meake, “Rabai, tauhano te kou mai te haraoa naa na vahao hakaatoa.” 
\p  
\v 35 Tena Jisas ki meake na tama raa, “Anau ko te Haraoa te Ora, na tama e oo mai Anau raa se lavaa te hikkai, tena na tama e hakattina Anau raa se lavaa te hiunu.  
\v 36 Teenei Anau ku meatu kootou te saaita nei pera ma kootou e kite Anau, e meia kootou se lavaa te hakattina Anau.  
\v 37 Na tama hakaatoa te Tamana e kou mai Anau raa e me ki oo mai Anau. Anau se lavaa te hakaise he tama na tama e oo mai Anau raa i taha,  
\v 38 maitaname Anau se hamai i taha ma te vaelani ki ppena hea Anau e hihai, e meia Anau e hamai ki ppena te hihai te Tama e kauna ria mai Anau raa.  
\v 39 Tena te Tama raa e hihai ma Anau ki se lavaa te hakaise he tama na tama Aia e kou mai Anau raa, e meia ma Anau ki hakaora muri na tama raa hakaatoa i te aho hakaoti raa.  
\v 40 Maitaname te Tamana Anau raa e hihai ma na tama hakaatoa e kkite te Tamariki Aia raa no hakattina raa e me ki too te ora e ora tahi. Tena Anau e me ki hakaora muri na tama raa i te aho hakaoti raa.” 
\p  
\v 41 Tena te kanohenua raa ku kaamata no tamumu iaa Jisas, e mee na tattara Tama raa ma, “Anau ko te haraoa e hamai i te vaelani.”  
\v 42 Kito na tama raa ki meake, “Te tama nei ko Jisas te tamariki Josep raa, kaa seai? Taatou e illoa te tamana ia ma te tinna Aia raa. Kaa Aia e tattara peehee ma Aia e hamai i te vaelani?” 
\p  
\v 43 Kito Jisas ki meake, “Auu se tamumu hokkootou.  
\v 44 Se hai tama e lavaa te hamai Anau kame te Tamana se hakattaki mai tama naa iaa Anau, tena Anau e me ki hakaora muri tama naa i te aho hakaoti raa.  
\v 45 Na profet raa e tattaa ma, 
\q1 ‘TeAtua e me ki poroporo na tama hakaatoa.’ 
\m Na tama e llono no illoa na tattara Tama raa e me ki oo mai Anau.  
\v 46 Te tattara nei se mee pera ma e isi te tama ni kite te Tamana, te Tama e hamai TeAtua raa ko te Tama hokotahi koi tera ni kite te Tamana raa.  
\v 47 Anau e meatu te hakamaoni: te tama e hakatina raa e me ki too te ora e ora tahi.  
\v 48 Anau ko te haraoa te ora.  
\v 49 Na tipuna kootou raa e kkai na mana i te kina e tuu mahoa raa, e meia na tama raa e mmate koi.  
\v 50 Emeia te haraoa e hamai i te vaelani raa e kee, e mee te tama e kai te haraoa naa se lavaa te mate.  
\v 51 Anau ko te haraoa e ora tera e hamai i te vaelani. Kame he tama e kai te haraoa nei, tena aia e me ki noho tahi roo. Te haraoa Anau e me ki kou ake raa ko te tinotama Anau tera Anau e me ki hoki atu ki lavaa na tama te maarama nei raa te ora.” 
\p  
\v 52 Te tattara nei e mee te kanohenua raa no hakatauttau hokolaatou. Na tama raa e vahihhiri ma, “Te Tama nei e me ki kou mai peehee te tinotama Aia raa ki kkai taatou?” 
\p  
\v 53 Tena Jisas ki meake na tama raa, “Anau e tattara atu te hakamaoni: kame kootou se kkai te tinotama, ia se unu te toto te Tamariki te Tama nei; kootou se lavaa te isi na ora i roto kootou.  
\v 54 Na tama e kkai te tinotama Anau raa, tena ki unu te toto Anau raa e me ki too te ora e ora tahi, tena Anau e me ki hakaora muri na tama naa i te aho hakaoti raa.  
\v 55 Maitaname te tinotama Anau raa ko te kai hakamaoni, tena te toto Anau raa ko te vai hakamaoni.  
\v 56 Na tama e kkai te tinotama Anau, tena ki unu te toto Anau raa e nnoho i roto Anau, tena Anau e noho i roto na tama naa.  
\v 57 Te Tamana e ora raa ni kauna ria mai Anau, tena Anau e ora e mee te Tama raa. Ia e ssau peeraa hoki, te tama e kai te tinotama Anau raa e me ki ora e mee Anau e noho.  
\v 58 Ia teenei ko te haraoa e hamai i te vaelani; te haraoa nei e kee ma te haraoa na tipuna kootou raa ni kkai raa. Na tama raa e nnoho roo no oti, tena ki mmate, e meia na tama e kkai te haraoa e hamai i te vaelani raa e me ki nnoho tahi roo.” 
\p  
\v 59 Jisas e tattara na tattara nei te saaita Aia ni akoako i roto te hare lotu na Jiu i Kaperneam raa. 
\s1 Na tattara te ora e ora tahi 
\p  
\v 60 Tammaki na tama e tauttari Jisas raa e llono na tattara nei, tena ki meake, “Na akoako nei e hainattaa roo. Koai na tama e lavaa te hakallono na tattara nei?” 
\p  
\v 61 Se hai tama e meake, e meia Jisas e iroa pera ma na disaipol Aia raa e tamumu i na tattara Aia raa, tena Aia ki meake na tama raa, “Eaa, na tattara nei e mee kootou no se hihhai ki tauttari Anau?  
\v 62 Kaa hea kootou e me ki mee, kame kootou e kkite te Tamariki te Tama nei e vaakai i aruna i te kina Aia ni noho i mua raa?  
\v 63 TeAnana Tapu TeAtua raa e kou atu te ora, tena na mahi na tama te maarama nei raa ni mahi vare koi. Na tattara Anau e tattara atu raa e kou atu kootou TeAnana Tapu TeAtua tera e kou atu te ora raa.  
\v 64 Emeia alaa tama kootou se hakattina.” (Jisas e iroa i te kaamata roo na tama tera e me ki se hakattina ia ma te tama e me ki kou ake Aia i na tama haeo raa.)  
\v 65 Tena Aia ki meake hoki, “Teenei te hakataakoto Anau ni tattara atu kootou pera ma se hai tama e lavaa te hamai Anau kame te Tamana se hakattaki mai te tama naa iaa Anau.” 
\p  
\v 66 Tena tammaki na tama ni tauttari Jisas raa ku huri no vakkai muri, na tama raa ku se tauttari hoki Tama raa he saaita.  
\v 67 Kito Jisas ki vahiri ake te sanahuru ma rua na disaipol Aia raa, “Kaa kootou, kootou e hihhai ki tiaki Anau hoki?” 
\p  
\v 68 Tena Saimon Pita ki meake, “TeAriki, kaa maatou e me ki oo iaa aii? Akoe e hahaere ma na tattara te ora e ora tahi.  
\v 69 Tena te saaita nei maatou ku illoa no hakattina pera ma Akoe ko te Tama e Tapu TeAtua.” 
\p  
\v 70 Kito Jisas ki meake, “Anau ni hirihiri kootou te sanahuru ma rua na tama nei, kaa seai? Emeia he tama kootou he tipua sakkino!”  
\v 71 Jisas e tattara iaa Judas, te tama Saimon Iskariot raa. Maitaname Judas e me ki kou ake Jisas i na tama haeo raa, niaina ma aia he tama i roto te sanahuru ma rua na disaipol raa. 
\c 7  
\s1 Na taina Jisas raa se hakattina Tama raa 
\p  
\v 1 Tena ki oti Jisas ku haere peeraa i Galili, tena Aia se hihai hoki ma ki haere vaa roto Judia, maitaname na tama hakamattua na Jiu i te kina raa e hihhai ma ki taa Aia ki mate.  
\v 2 Te saaita hoki te Kai na Paa hare raa ku taapiri,  
\v 3 kito na taina Jisas raa ki meake Tama raa, “Tiaki te kina nei no haere i Judia ki kkite na tama e tauttari Akoe raa na mee Akoe e me ki ppena raa.  
\v 4 Se hai tama e lavaa te huu he mee, kame aia e hihai ma na tama hakaatoa ki illoa aia. E mee Akoe e haere ppena na mee nei, tena ki huri ake na mee nei ma ki illoa na tama hakaatoa te maarama nei raa Akoe!”  
\v 5 (Na taina roo Jisas raa se hakattina hoki Tama raa.) 
\p  
\v 6 Tena Jisas ki meake na tama raa, “Te saaita hakamaoni Anau ki ppena na mee nei raa se ki ttae mai, e meia na saaita hakaatoa ni saaita kootou.  
\v 7 Te maarama nei se lavaa te kiri lloto kootou, e meia te maarama nei e kiri lloto Anau, maitaname Anau e tattara tahi ake pera ma na tiputipu laatou raa e sakkino.  
\v 8 Kootou ki oo i te kina te Kai raa. Anau se lavaa te haere atu, maitaname te saaita hakamaoni Anau raa se ki tae.”  
\v 9 Jisas e tattara ake peenei, tena ki noho koi i Galili. 
\s1 Jisas ku tae i te kina te Kai na Hare taporo 
\p  
\v 10 Tena ki oti na taina Jisas raa ku oo i te kina te Kai raa, tena Jisas hoki e haere; e meia Aia e haere hemuu koi ma ki se illoa na tama raa.  
\v 11 Na tama hakamattua na Jiu raa e sesee Jisas i te kina te Kai raa. Na tama raa e vahihhiri ma, “Teehee Aia naa?” 
\p  
\v 12 Te kanohenua raa e tattara hemuu hokolaatou. Alaa tama e tattara ma, “Te Tama raa he tama tauareka.” Tena alaa tama ki meake ma, “Seai, te Tama naa e mariu ake koi na tama.”  
\v 13 Emeia se hai tama e tattara hakamaroa, maitaname na tama raa e mattaku i na tama hakamattua na Jiu raa. 
\p  
\v 14 Te Kai raa ku tae lottonu ma te hakaoti, tena Jisas ki haere i roto te Hare Tapu raa no kaamata no takutaku.  
\v 15 Na tama hakamattua na Jiu raa ku mahharo roo, tena ki meake, “Te Tama nei e iroa roo peehee na mee hakaatoa ma Aia se skul raa?” 
\p  
\v 16 Kito Jisas ki meake, “Na mee Anau e akoako raa seai ma ni akoako Anau, e meia aaraa ni akoako TeAtua, te Tama ni kauna ria mai Anau raa.  
\v 17 Te tama e hihai ki ppena hea TeAtua e hihai raa e me ki iroa i te vahi na akoako Anau raa pera ma na akoako raa ni akoako e oo mai TeAtua ma ni akoako koi Anau e tattara i te vahi Anau Hokonnau.  
\v 18 Te tama e tattara i te vahi aia hokoia raa e hahaivi koi ki hakammaha te inoa aia hokoia. Emeia te Tama e hihai ki hakammaha te inoa te Tama ni kauna ria mai Aia raa e hakamaoni, tena Aia Hokoia e tonu tahi.  
\v 19 Moses ni kou atu na tuaa raa, kaa seai? Emeia se hai tama kootou e tauttari na tuaa raa. Kaa kootou e hahaivi ma ki taa Anau ki mate naea?” 
\p  
\v 20 Tena te kanohenua raa ki meake, “Akoe e isi te tipua sakkino e tau i roto Akoe. Koai na tama e hahaivi ma ki taa Akoe ki mate naa?” 
\p  
\v 21 Kito Jisas ki meake, “Anau ni ppena te mirakol hokotahi\f + \fr 7.21 \ft teenei ko te mirakol Jisas ni tokonaki te tama no tauareka i te Sabat\f* koi, tena kootou hakaatoa roo e mahharo.  
\v 22 Moses ni meatu kootou ki tuu te hakamaatino e tapu raa i na tamalliki kootou (e meia Moses seai ma ko te tama e kaamata te mee nei, aaraa ko na tipuna kootou raa e kaamata), tena kootou ki ttuu te hakamaatino e tapu raa i na tamalliki kootou raa i te aho te Sabat raa.  
\v 23 Kootou e ttuu te hakamaatino e tapu na tamalliki kootou raa i te aho te Sabat raa ma ki tautari na tuaa Moses raa, kaa kootou e lloto ma Anau e tokonaki te tama raa no tauareka i te aho te Sabat naea?  
\v 24 Auu se hakatonutonu tautari hea kootou e kkite, e meia hakatonutonu tautari na tiputipu e ttonu.” 
\s1 Eaa, Jisas ko te Mesaia? 
\p  
\v 25 E isi na tama i Jerusalem e tattara ma, “Teenei seai ma ko te tama na tama hakamattua raa e hahaivi ma ki taa ki mate?  
\v 26 Kira ake! Tama raa ku tuu roo i mua na tama raa no tattara, tena laatou se hai tattara e meake te Tama raa! Eaa, na tama raa ku illoa hakamaoni ma teeraa ko te Mesaia!  
\v 27 Emeia te saaita te Mesaia raa e hamai raa, se hai tama e me ki iroa ma te Mesaia raa e hamai te matakaina hee. Emeia taatou hakaatoa kaa e illoa koi ma te Tama nei he tama i hee.” 
\p  
\v 28 Jisas e akoako i roto te Hare Tapu raa, tena Aia ki meake hakamaroa roo ma, “Kootou e illoa hakamaoni roo Anau, tena e illoa hoki ma Anau e hamai i hee? Anau se hamai i te vahi Anau Hokonnau. Emeia te Tama e kauna ria mai Anau raa e tonu tahi. Kootou se illoa Tama raa,  
\v 29 e meia Anau e iroa Tama raa, maitaname Anau e hamai Tama raa, tena Tama raa e kauna ria mai Anau ki hamai.” 
\p  
\v 30 Tena na tama raa ku tattara ma ki hakapiki Tama raa, e meia se hai tama e ttaohi Tama raa, maitaname te saaita hakamaoni Aia raa se ki tae.  
\v 31 Emeia tammaki na tama i roto te kanohenua raa ku hakattina iaa Jisas, tena ki meake, “Te saaita te Mesaia raa e hamai raa, eaa Aia e me ki ppena tammaki na mirakol peenei ma te Tama nei e ppena nei?” 
\s1 Na soldia raa ku oo ma ki hakapiki Jisas 
\p  
\v 32 Na Farisi raa e llono na tattara te kanohenua raa e tattara hemuu iaa Jisas raa, tena laatou hakapaa ma na maatua hakananniu raa ku kauna na soldia e lollohi te Hare Tapu raa ki oo no hakapiki Jisas.  
\v 33 Kito Jisas ki meake, “Anau e me ki nnoho ma kootou paa saaita koi, tena ki oti Anau ku vaakai i te Tama ni kauna ria mai Anau raa.  
\v 34 Kootou e me ki sesee Anau, e meia kootou se lavaa ki kkite Anau, maitaname kootou se lavaa te oo i te kina Anau e me ki noho raa.” 
\p  
\v 35 Na tama hakamattua na Jiu raa ku tattara hokolaatou ma, “Tama raa e mee ma Aia e me ki haere i hee ki se kkite taatou Aia raa? Aia e me ki haere na matakaina na tama taatou raa e nnoho i roto Grik raa no akoako ake na tama raa?  
\v 36 Tama raa e mee ma taatou e me ki sesee Aia, e meia taatou se lavaa te kkite Aia, tena ma taatou se lavaa hoki te oo i te kina Aia e me ki noho raa. Tama raa e tattara maea?” 
\s1 Te vai te ora e ora tahi 
\p  
\v 37 Te aho hakaoti te Kai raa he aho e rahi roo, tena Jisas ki mahike i aruna no tattara hakamaroa roo ma, “Te tama e hiunu raa ki hamai Anau,  
\v 38 tena te tama e hakatina Anau raa e me ki hamai no unu.” E ssau pera ma te Launiu Tapu raa e tattara ma, “Te vai te ora raa e me ki tere iho i taha ma te vahi manava Tama raa.”  
\v 39 Jisas e tattara peenei i te vahi TeAnana Tapu tera na tama e hakattina raa e me ki too raa. Te saaita naa Aia se ki kou ake TeAnana Tapu raa, maitaname Aia se ki haere no too na mahi Aia. 
\s1 Te kanohenua raa ku hakatauttau hokolaatou 
\p  
\v 40 E isi na tama i roto te kanohenua raa e llono na tattara Jisas raa, tena ki meake, “Te Tama nei ko te Profet TeAtua raa hakamaoni!” 
\p  
\v 41 Alaa tama e tattara ma, “Tama nei ko te Mesaia!” 
\p Emeia alaa tama e tattara ma, “Te Mesaia raa se lavaa te hamai i Galili!  
\v 42 Te Launiu Tapu raa e tattara ma te Mesaia raa he mokopuna te Tuku Devit raa, tena Aia e me ki haanau mai i Betlehem, te matakaina Devit ni noho i mua raa.”  
\v 43 Tena te kanohenua raa ku hakatauttau hokolaatou e mee Jisas.  
\v 44 Alaa tama e hihhai ki hakapiki Tama raa, e meia se hai tama e kapake no ttaohi Tama raa. 
\s1 Na tama hakamattua na Jiu raa se hakattina iaa Jisas 
\p  
\v 45 Na soldia raa ku vakkai ake, tena na maatua hakananniu ia ma na Farisi raa ku vahiri ake na tama raa ma, “Kootou se too Tama raa no oo mai kootou raea?” 
\p  
\v 46 Kito na soldia raa ki meake, “Se hai tama roo e tattara na tattara te Tama nei e tattara raa!” 
\p  
\v 47 Kito na Farisi raa ki meake, “Eaa, Tama raa e mee kootou no vvare hoki?  
\v 48 Kootou e illoa raa e isi te tama na tama hakamattua ia ma he Farisi ni hakatina Tama raa?  
\v 49 Te kanohenua raa se illoa laoi na tuaa Moses raa, tena na tama raa e me ki too na hakalono llihu TeAtua raa!” 
\p  
\v 50 Tena he Farisi e noho i te kina raa, te inoa aia raa ko Nikodimas, teenaa ko te tama ni haere ake no mmata Jisas i mua raa. Tama raa e tattara ake na tama raa ma,  
\v 51 “I te vahi na tuaa taatou raa; taatou se lavaa te kou ake na hakalono llihu te tama kame taatou se vahiri tama raa ki too taatou te hakamaoni na mee tama raa e ppena e ssara raa.” 
\p  
\v 52 Kito na tama raa ki meake, “Eaa, akoe he tama hoki i Galili? Paupau te Launiu Tapu raa ki iroa akoe pera ma se isi te profet e me ki haanau mai i Galili.” 
\c 8  
\s1 Te hine e pena te mee sakkino 
\p [ 
\v 1 Tena na tama hakaatoa ku vakkai i na hare laatou raa, e meia Jisas e haere i te Mouna e hhomo na Oliv raa.  
\v 2 Te tahata roo te aho taiao raa Jisas ku vaakai ake i te Hare Tapu. Na tama hakaatoa ku muimui ake Tama raa, tena Aia ki noho i raro no akoako ake te kanohenua raa.  
\v 3 Kito na tama poroporo na tuaa raa laatou ma na Farisi raa ku kou ake te hine e laavea ria e pena te mee sakkino no hakatuu i mua na tama raa hakaatoa.  
\v 4 Kito na tama raa ki meake Jisas, “Rabai, na tama raa e laavea te hine nei e pena te mee sakkino.  
\v 5 Na tuaa Moses raa e mee mai taatou ma kame he hine e pena te mee sakkino peenei, tena na tama ku maka te hine naa na hatu ki mate. Tena kaa Akoe e maanatu maea?”  
\v 6 Na tama raa e vahiri ake peenei ma ki taaiki Jisas, ki lavaa laatou te mmau tattara i Tama raa. Emeia Jisas e huru koi i raro no sisi te mata rima Aia raa i aruna te kerekere. 
\p  
\v 7 Na tama raa e ttuu koi no vahihhiri ake Jisas na vahiri, tena Jisas ki hamatakkau i aruna no meake na tama raa, “Koai te tama kootou se isi na hai sara e ppena raa ku too te hatu kaamata raa no ppehi te hine nei.”  
\v 8 Tena Aia ki huru hakaraoi i raro no sisi i aruna te kerekere.  
\v 9 Te saaita na tama raa ni llono na tattara raa, na tama raa ku hakaatoa ku haere uhu taki ttahi no oo; kaamata ma na tama mattua raa. Tena Jisas Hokoia koi ku ttoe, tena te hine raa hoki e tuu i te kina raa.  
\v 10 Kito Jisas ki hamatakkau no tuu i aruna, tena ki meake te hine raa, “Na hee na tama naa? E isi te tama e ttoe ki mee mai ni tattara i te vahi akoe?” 
\p  
\v 11 Tena te hine raa ki meake, “TeAriki, se hai tama e ttoe.” 
\p Kito Jisas ki meake, “Tena Anau hoki se hai tattara i te vahi akoe. Haere, tena auu se ppena hoki na mee sakkino.”] 
\s1 Jisas ko te Maahina te maarama nei 
\p  
\v 12 Tena Jisas ki tattara ake na Farisi raa hakaraoi. Jisas e meake ma, “Anau ko te Maahina te maarama nei. Koai te tama e tautari Anau e me ki too te Maahina te ora, tena aia hoki se lavaa te hahaere i roto te pouri.” 
\p  
\v 13 Kito na Farisi raa ki meake Jisas, “Tena te saaita nei Akoe ku tattara mai maatou i te vahi Akoe Hokkoe, e meia na tattara Akoe raa se isi roo te hakamaoni.” 
\p  
\v 14 Tena Jisas ki meake, “Niaina Anau e tattara i te vahi Anau Hokonnau, hea Anau e meatu raa e hakamaoni, maitaname Anau e iroa te kina Anau ni hamai ia ma te kina Anau e me ki haere raa. Kootou se illoa te kina Anau ni hamai ia ma te kina Anau e me ki haere raa.  
\v 15 Kootou e hakatonutonu na mee hakaatoa tautari te hakataakoto te tama, e meia Anau se hai tama ni hakatonutonu.  
\v 16 Emeia peeraa Anau ki hakatonutonu na tama raa, tena te hakatonutonu Anau raa e me ki hakamaoni, maitaname Anau se mee ma Anau e hakatonutonu Hokonnau; te Tamana ni kauna ria mai Anau raa e noho ma Anau.  
\v 17 E mmau i roto na tuaa kootou raa pera ma, kame tokorua na tama e hakattina te hakataakoto hokotahi, tena hea laaua e tattara raa e hakamaoni.  
\v 18 Anau e tattara i te vahi Anau Hokonnau, tena te Tamana ni kauna ria mai Anau raa e tattara hoki i te vahi Anau.” 
\p  
\v 19 Kito na tama raa ki vahiri ake, “Teehee te Tamana Akoe naa?” 
\p Tena Jisas ki meake, “Kootou se illoa Anau ia ma te Tamana Anau raa hoki. Ia peeraa kootou ki illoa Anau; kootou e me ki illoa hoki te Tamana Anau raa.” 
\p  
\v 20 Jisas e tattara ake na tattara nei hakaatoa i te kanohenua raa te saaita Aia ni akoako i roto te Hare Tapu i te kina na tama raa e tukutuku na hoki raa. Ia se hai tama e hakapiki Tama raa e mee te saaita Aia e me ki taia ria no mate raa se ki tae. 
\s1 Kootou se lavaa te oo i te kina Anau e me ki haere 
\p  
\v 21 Tena Jisas ki meake hakaraoi na tama raa pera ma, “Anau e me ki haere i taha; kootou e me ki sesee Anau, tena kootou e me ki mmate i na hai sara kootou. Kootou se lavaa te oo i te kina Anau e me ki haere raa.” 
\p  
\v 22 Kito na tama hakamattua na Jiu raa ki tattara ma, “Tama raa e tattara ma taatou se lavaa te oo i te kina Aia e me ki haere raa. Eaa, Aia e maanatu ma ki taa Aia Hokoia ki mate?” 
\p  
\v 23 Tena Jisas ki meake, “Kootou ni tama te maarama i raro nei, e meia Anau e hamai i aruna. Kootou ni tama te maarama nei, e meia Anau seai ma he tama te maarama nei.  
\v 24 Tera hea Anau e meatu ma kootou e me ki mate i na hai sara kootou raa. Tena kootou e me ki mmate i na hai sara kootou raa kame kootou se hakattina pera ma, ‘Anau ko Nau koi’.” 
\p  
\v 25 Kito na tama raa ki meake, “Koai Akoe?” 
\p Tena Jisas ki meake, “Anau e me ki tattara atu kootou peehee?  
\v 26 Anau e tammaki na tattara ki tattara atu i te vahi kootou, ia tammaki hoki na tattara ki hai atu na haeo kootou raa. Te Tama ni kauna ria mai Anau raa e hakamaoni, tena Anau e tattara ake te maarama nei na mee Anau e rono Aia e tattara mai Anau raa.” 
\p  
\v 27 Na tama raa se illoa ma Jisas e tattara ake laatou i te vahi te Tamana.  
\v 28 Kito Jisas ki meake na tama raa, “Te saaita kootou e ssau te Tamariki te Tama nei i aruna raa, tena kootou e me ki illoa pera ma ‘Anau ko Nau koi’, tena kootou e me ki illoa pera ma Anau se ppena na mee i na mahi Anau Hokonnau, e meia Anau e tattara koi hea te Tamana e tattara mai Anau ki tattara atu raa.  
\v 29 Tena te Tama e kauna ria mai Anau raa e noho ma Anau; Tama raa se hai vahao e tiaki Anau, maitaname Anau e ppena tahi hea Aia e hihai raa.” 
\p  
\v 30 Tammaki na tama e llono na tattara Jisas raa ku hakattina Tama raa. 
\s1 Te Hakamaoni raa e me ki hakattana kootou 
\p  
\v 31 Kito Jisas ki meake na tama e hakattina i Aia raa, “Kame kootou e tauttari na akoako Anau nei, tena kootou ni disaipol hakamaoni Anau;  
\v 32 kootou e me ki illoa te hakamaoni raa, tena te hakamaoni raa e me ki hakattana kootou.” 
\p  
\v 33 Kito na tama raa ki meake, “Maatou ni mokopuna Abraham, tena maatou se hai vahao e hehekau ma na tama. Kaa he hakataakoto peehee Akoe e tattara ma, ‘Kootou e me ki hakattana ria naa’?” 
\p  
\v 34 Tena Jisas ki meake na tama raa, “Anau e meatu kootou te hakamaoni: na tama hakaatoa e isi na hai sara raa e nnoho i raro na mahi na hai sara raa.  
\v 35 Te tama hehekau raa seai ma he tama hakamaoni i roto te hare, e meia te tamariki raa he tama hakamaoni e noho tahi i roto te hare.  
\v 36 Kame te Tama TeAtua raa e tokonaki kootou ki ttana, tena kootou e me ki ttana hakamaoni.  
\v 37 Anau e iroa kootou ni mokopuna Abraham. Emeia kootou e hahaivi ma ki taa Anau ki mate, maitaname kootou se hihhai ki tauttari na akoako Anau raa.  
\v 38 Anau e tattara hea te Tamana Anau raa e huri mai Anau raa, e meia kootou e ppena hea te tamana kootou raa ni tattara atu kootou raa.” 
\p  
\v 39 Kito na tama raa ki meake Jisas, “Te tamana maatou raa ko Abraham.” 
\p Tena Jisas ki meake, “Kame kootou ni tamalliki hakamaoni Abraham, tena kootou e me ki ppena na mee aia ni ppena raa.  
\v 40 Anau na vahao hakaatoa e tattara atu kootou te hakamaoni Anau e rono i TeAtua raa, e meia kootou e hahaivi ma ki taa Anau ki mate. Abraham se ppena na tiputipu peenei!  
\v 41 Kootou e ppena hea te tamana kootou raa ni ppena.” 
\p Kito na tama raa ki meake, “TeAtua Hokoia koi ko te Tamana maatou e isi, tena maatou ni tamalliki hakamaoni Aia.” 
\p  
\v 42 Tena Jisas ki meake na tama raa, “Kame TeAtua he Tamana kootou hakamaoni, kootou e me ki laoi Anau, maitaname TeAtua e kauna ria mai Anau, tera hea te aho nei Anau e noho i te kina nei. Anau se hamai te hihai Anau, e meia TeAtua e kauna ria mai Anau.  
\v 43 Aiea kootou se illoa hea Anau e tattara atu raea? E mee kootou se hihhai ki hakallono na tattara Anau raa.  
\v 44 Kootou ni tamalliki Satan te tamana kootou raa, tena kootou e hihhai ki tauttari hea te tamana kootou raa e hihai. Te tama naa he tama taa tama kaamata mai roo i te kaamata, tena aia se hai vahao e tuu te vahi te hakamaoni, maitaname aia hokoia se isi te hakamaoni i roto aia. Te saaita aia e tattara te tattara mariu raa, aia e ppena koi hea e tau ma aia raa, maitaname aia he tama tattara mariu, tena aia ko te tamana na tama hakaatoa e tattara malliu raa.  
\v 45 Emeia Anau e tattara te hakamaoni tera hea kootou se hihhai ki hakattina Anau.  
\v 46 Koai te tama kootou e lavaa te mee mai te hakamaoni hea Anau e ppena e sara? Kame Anau e tattara atu te hakamaoni, tena kaa kootou se hakattina Anau naea?  
\v 47 Te tama e hamai TeAtua raa e hakarono na tattara TeAtua. Emeia kootou seai ma ni tamalliki TeAtua, tera hea kootou se hihhai ki hakallono.” 
\s1 Jisas ia ma Abraham 
\p  
\v 48 Kito na tama raa ki vahiri ake Jisas, “Eaa, maatou e sara te saaita maatou ni meatu pera ma Akoe he tama i Samaria, tena ma Akoe e isi te tipua i roto Akoe?” 
\p  
\v 49 Tena Jisas ki meake, “Anau se isi te tipua i roto Anau, tena Anau e hakammaha te Tamana Anau raa, e meia kootou se hakammaha Anau.  
\v 50 Anau se hihai ki ssau Anau Hokonnau i aruna. Emeia e isi te Tama e hihai ki ssau Anau, tena Aia ko te Tama e me ki hakatonutonu.  
\v 51 Anau e meatu kootou te hakamaoni: koai te tama e tautari na tattara Anau raa se lavaa te mate.” 
\p  
\v 52 Kito na tama raa ki meake, “Te saaita nei maatou ku illoa te hakamaoni pera ma Akoe e isi te tipua i roto Akoe! Abraham e mate, tena na profet raa hoki e mmate, e meia Akoe e mee ma na tama e tauttari na akoako Akoe raa se lavaa te mmate.  
\v 53 Abraham, te tamana maatou raa e mate; eaa Akoe e mee ma Akoe e hakanaaniu i aruna Abraham? Na profet raa hoki e mmate. Akoe e maanatu ma Akoe he tama peehee?” 
\p  
\v 54 Kito Jisas ki meake, “Kame Anau e hakammaha Anau Hokonnau, tena te hakammaha Anau raa he mee vare koi. Te Tama e hakammaha Anau raa ko te Tamana Anau raa, te Tama kootou e mee ma he Atua kootou raa.  
\v 55 Kootou se illoa roo Tama raa, e meia Anau e iroa Tama raa. Kame Anau e tattara pera ma Anau se iroa Tama raa, tena Anau he Tama tattara mariu peenaa ma kootou. Emeia Anau e iroa Tama raa, tena Anau e tautari na tattara Tama raa.  
\v 56 Abraham te tamana kootou raa e hihia ma aia e me ki kite te saaita Anau e hamai raa, tena aia ni kite no hihia roo.” 
\p  
\v 57 Kito na tama raa ki meake Jisas, “Akoe se tae tipu rima na hetau te matua Akoe, tena Akoe e mee pera ma Akoe ni kite Abraham?” 
\p  
\v 58 Tena Jisas ki meake, “Anau e meatu kootou te hakamaoni roo. I mua Abraham ni haanau mai, ‘Teenei Anau’.” 
\p  
\v 59 Tena na tama raa ki too na hatu raa ma ki maka Jisas, e meia Jisas e hakalluu Aia Hokoia, tena ki haere i taha ma te Hare Tapu raa. 
\c 9  
\s1 Jisas e tokonaki te tama e haanau iho na karemata e sseni 
\p  
\v 1 Jisas ku haere, tena Aia ki kite te tama na karemata e sseni kaamata mai roo te saaita aia ni haanau iho raa.  
\v 2 Tena na disaipol Jisas raa ki vahiri ake Tama raa, “Rabai, ni hai sara aii e mee te tama nei no sseni raa? Ni hai sara aia ma ni hai sara na maatua aia raa?” 
\p  
\v 3 Kito Jisas ki meake, “Seai ma ni hai sara te tama nei ia ma ni hai sara na maatua aia raa tera e mee na karemata tama nei no sseni. Tama nei e sseni ma ki kkite kootou na mahi TeAtua tera e me ki huri ake i roto te tama nei.  
\v 4 Tena taatou ki tauhano te ppena na uata te Tama ni kauna ria mai Anau raa te saaita te mee raa koi maarama; te poo e me ki tae mai te saaita taatou ku se hai tama e uata.  
\v 5 Anau ko te Maahina te maarama nei te saaita Anau e noho i roto te maarama nei.” 
\p  
\v 6 Jisas e tattara no oti, kito Aia ki saavare i aruna te kerekere raa, tena ki murumuru na saavare Aia raa ma na kerekere raa no pelapela, tena Aia ki mmuru na karemata te tama raa,  
\v 7 tena ki meake, “Haere no huhui na karemata akoe raa i roto te Vai i Siloam.” (Te tattara nei e mee ma “Kauna”.) Kito te tama raa ki haere no huhui na karemata Aia, tena ki vaakai ake na karemata aia raa ku kkite. 
\p  
\v 8 Na tama te kauhare raa ia ma na tama ni kkite tama ni noho no kainonno i mua raa ku vahihhiri ma, “Teenei seai ma ko te tama kame e noho no kainonno raa?” 
\p  
\v 9 Tena alaa tama ki meake ma, “Teenaa ko te tama naa koi,” e meia alaa tama e mee ma, “Seai, te tama naa e ssau roo pera ma te tama raa.” 
\p Kito te taupeara raa ki meake hokoia ma, “Teenei ko nau koi.” 
\p  
\v 10 Kito na tama raa ki vahiri ake te taupeara raa, “Kaa akoe ku kite vahao nei naea?” 
\p  
\v 11 Tena te tama raa ki meake, “Te tama e hui ma ko Jisas raa e murumuru na peela raa, tena ki mmuru na karemata anau raa, tena Aia ki mee mai ma anau ki haere no huhui na karemata anau i Siloam. Kito anau ki haere, ia te saaita koi anau ni huhui raa, anau ku lavaa te kite.” 
\p  
\v 12 Kito na tama raa ki vahiri ake ma, “Teehee te Tama naa?” 
\p Tena te tama raa ki meake, “Anau se iroa.” 
\s1 Na Farisi raa ku lahulahu i te tama ku kite raa 
\p  
\v 13 Tena te kanohenua raa ki too te tama ku kite raa no kkave i na Farisi raa.  
\v 14 Te aho Jisas ni mee na peela raa no mmuru na karemata te tama raa no kite raa he aho te Sabat.  
\v 15 Tena na Farisi raa ki vahiri ake hakaraoi te tama ku kite raa ma aia ku lavaa te kite peehee. Kito te tama raa ki meake na Farisi raa, “Tama raa e mmuru na karemata anau raa ma na peela, tena ki oti anau ki huhui na karemata anau raa; teenei hea anau ku kite.” 
\p  
\v 16 Tena e isi na Farisi ki meake, “Te tama e pena te mee nei raa seai ma he tama e hamai TeAtua, maitaname Aia se tautari na tuaa te Sabat raa.” 
\p Emeia alaa tama e tattara ma, “Te tama hai sara e lavaa peehee te ppena na mirakol peenei?” Tena na tama raa ku hakataukoti hokolaatou. 
\p  
\v 17 Kito na Farisi raa ki vahiri ake hakaraoi te tama ku kite raa ma, “Akoe e mee ma Tama raa e tokonaki akoe no kite, tena kaa akoe e maanatu ma Aia koai?” 
\p Tena te tama raa ki meake, “Te Tama raa he Profet.” 
\p  
\v 18 Na tama hakamattua na Jiu raa se hihhai ki hakattina pera ma te tama raa i mua raa e sseni, tena te saaita nei ma aia ku kite hakaraoi. Kito na tama raa ki kanna ake na maatua te tama raa  
\v 19 no vahiri ake tokorua raa ma, “Teenei he tama koorua? Koorua e mee ma te tama nei e sseni te saaita aia ni haanau mai raa; kaa te tama nei ku lavaa peehee te kite te saaita nei?” 
\p  
\v 20 Kito na maatua te tama raa ki meake, “Maaua e illoa ma teenei he taupeara maaua, tena maaua e illoa ma na karemata aia raa e sseni te saaita aia ni haanau iho raa.  
\v 21 Emeia maaua se illoa ma aia ku kite peehee te saaita nei, iaa maaua se illoa hoki te tama ni tokonaki te tama nei no kite raa. Vahiri ake te tama nei; aia ku matua, tena aia hokoia e lavaa te tattara atu kootou!”  
\v 22 Na maatua te tama raa e tattara peenei raa e mee laaua e mattaku i na tama hakamattua na Jiu raa, maitaname na tama raa ku oti te tattara no tonu ma kame he tama e hakatina ma Jisas ko te Mesaia, tena te tama naa e me ki hakatuu ria i taha ma te hare lotu.  
\v 23 Tera hea na maatua te tama raa e meake ma, “Vahiri ake te tama nei; aia ku matua, tena aia e me ki tattara atu hokoia!” 
\p  
\v 24 Kito na tama hakamattua na Jiu raa ki kanna ake te taupeara raa ki haere ake hakaraoi, tena laatou ki meake, “Tattara mai te hakamaoni i mua TeAtua pera ma akoe e me ki tattara te hakamaoni! Maatou e illoa ma te Tama e tokonaki akoe no kite raa he tama hai sara.” 
\p  
\v 25 Kito te taupeara raa ki meake, “Anau se iroa, Aia he tama hai sara ma seai, e meia te mee hokotahi koi anau e iroa raa: anau e iroa pera ma anau ni mee raa e sseni, tena te saaita nei anau ku kite.” 
\p  
\v 26 Tena na tama raa ki vahiri ake, “Kaa Tama naa e mee peehee akoe? Aia e mee peehee akoe no kite?” 
\p  
\v 27 Kito te taupeara raa ki meake, “Anau ku oti te meatu kootou, tena kootou se hihhai ki hakallono. Aiea kootou e hihhai ki llono hakaraoi naea? Kame ko kootou hoki e hihhai ki mee pera ma ni disaipol Tama raa?” 
\p  
\v 28 Kito na tama raa ku hai ake hakasakkino roo i te taupeara raa, tena ki meake, “Akoe avare he disaipol Tama raa; e meia maatou ni disaipol Moses.  
\v 29 Maatou e illoa ma TeAtua ni tattara ake Moses; e meia maatou se illoa ma te Tama naa e hamai i hee!” 
\p  
\v 30 Kito te taupeara raa ki meake, “Anau e mahharo i na tattara naa! Kootou se illoa ma te Tama naa e hamai i hee, e meia Aia e tokonaki anau no kite!  
\v 31 Maatou e illoa TeAtua se hakarono na tama hai ssara; Tama raa e hakarono na tama e hakammaha Aia raa, tena ki ppena hea Aia e hihai ma na tama raa ki ppena raa.  
\v 32 Taatou se hai vahao roo ni llono i mua te saaita te maarama nei ni tipu ake ma he tama ni tokonaki te tama karemata sseni peenei no kite.  
\v 33 Kame te Tama naa seai ma he tama TeAtua e kauna ria mai, tena te Tama naa se lavaa hoki te ppena he mee.” 
\p  
\v 34 Kito na tama raa ki meake, “Akoe e haanau no matua mai ma na hai sara, tena akoe e hihai ma ki akoako mai maatou?” Tena na tama raa ki hakatuu te taupeara raa i taha ma te hare lotu. 
\s1 Na tama e sseni 
\p  
\v 35 Te saaita Jisas ni rono hea ni kapihi ake te taupeara raa, tena Aia ki haere no mmata te taupeara raa, tena ki vahiri ake te taupeara raa, “Akoe e hakatina i te Tamariki te Tama nei?” 
\p  
\v 36 Tena te taupeara raa ki meake, “Hakari mai te Tama naa ki iroa anau, ki lavaa anau te hakatina Tama naa!” 
\p  
\v 37 Tena Jisas ki meake, “Akoe ku oti te kite te Tama naa, teenei Aia nei e tattara ma akoe te saaita nei.” 
\p  
\v 38 Kito te taupeara raa ki meake, “TeAriki, anau ku hakatina,” tena aia ki tuturi i mua Jisas. 
\p  
\v 39 Tena Jisas ki meake, “Anau e hamai i te maarama nei ki hakatonutonu, ki lavaa na tama e sseni raa te kkite, tena na tama e kkite raa ki sseni.” 
\p  
\v 40 E isi na Farisi e ttuu i te kina raa no llono na tattara Jisas raa, tena na tama raa ki vahiri ake Jisas ma, “Hakamaoni Akoe kame e tattara ma maatou hoki e sseni nee?” 
\p  
\v 41 Kito Jisas ki meake, “Kame kootou e sseni, tena na hakataakoto kootou raa se lavaa te haeo ma kootou e ssara, e meia kame kootou e mee ma kootou e kkite, tena na hakataakoto kootou raa e me ki haeo ma kootou e ssara.” 
\c 10  
\s1 Te tattara hurihuri te tama rorohi na sipsip 
\p  
\v 1 Tena Jisas ki meake, “Anau e tattara atu kootou te hakamaoni: te tama se uru tonu te totoka raa, tena ki kake na vahi te hare na sipsip e moemmoe raa he tama kairarao, iaa he tama sakkino.  
\v 2 Te tama e uru tonu te totoka raa ko te tama e rorohi na sipsip raa.  
\v 3 Te tama e tuu te totoka raa e me ki taaraki te totoka raa ki uru te tama raa; na sipsip raa e llono te reo tama raa te saaita aia e kakanna na inoa na sipsip raa, tena ku hakattaki na manu raa i aho.  
\v 4 Te saaita na sipsip raa ku ttae i aho hakaatoa, te tama raa e me ki haere i mua na sipsip raa, tena na sipsip raa e me ki tauttari aia, maitaname na manu raa e illoa te reo tama raa.  
\v 5 Na sipsip raa se lavaa te tauttari he tama peeraa hoki; e meia na manu raa e me ki huro i taha ma te tama raa, maitaname laatou se illoa te reo te tama raa.” 
\p  
\v 6 Jisas e tattara ake te tattara hurihuri nei, e meia na tama raa se illoa te hakataakoto te tattara hurihuri raa. 
\s1 Jisas te Tama hakamaoni e rorohi na sipsip 
\p  
\v 7 Kito Jisas ki meake hakaraoi, “Anau e meatu te hakamaoni: Anau ko te totoka te hare na sipsip.  
\v 8 Na tama hakaatoa ni oo mai i mua raa ni tama kailallao, ia ni tama sakkino, e meia na sipsip raa se hihhai ki hakallono na tama raa.  
\v 9 Anau ko te totoka. Na tama e oo mai Anau raa e me ki ora; na tama raa e me ki oo mai i hare, tena ku oo i aho no sesee na kai.  
\v 10 Na tama kailallao raa e oo mai koi ki kailallao, ki taa ki mmate, tena ku seu kootou. Anau e hamai ma ki tokonaki kootou ki too te ora; te ora tera e pii na mee taualleka raa. 
\p  
\v 11 “Anau ko te Tama tauareka te rorohi na sipsip, Anau e tanattana ki mate ma na sipsip raa.  
\v 12 Te saaita te tama na tama raa ni too ma ki rorohi na sipsip raa e kite te poi kai tama raa ku haere ake, te tama raa e me ki tiaki na sipsip raa no tere i taha, tena te poi kai tama raa e me ki oho ake na sipsip raa, tena na sipsip raa hakaatoa ku maaseu no huro.  
\v 13 Te tama na tama raa e too ki rorohi na sipsip raa e tere i taha e mee aia seai ma ko te tama hakamaoni ki rorohi na sipsip raa.  
\v 14 15 Tena Anau ko te Tama tauareka te rorohi na sipsip raa. E ssau pera ma te Tamana e iroa Anau, tena Anau e iroa te Tamana, ia e ssau hoki pera ma Anau e iroa na sipsip Anau raa, tena na sipsip Anau raa e illoa Anau. Tena Anau e tanattana ki mate ma na sipsip raa.  
\v 16 E isi alaa sipsip Anau seai i roto te hare nei. Anau e me ki kou mai laatou hoki; na manu naa e me ki hakallono te reo Anau raa, tena laatou e me ki oo mai no hakapaa hakaatoa, tena he tama hokotahi koi e me ki rorohi laatou. 
\p  
\v 17 “Te Tamana e laoi Anau, maitaname Anau e tanattana ki hoki atu te ora Anau raa ma ki lavaa Anau te too muri te ora Anau raa hakaraoi.  
\v 18 Se hai tama e me ki too te ora Anau raa i taha ma Anau. Anau e hoki atu te ora Anau i te hihai Anau. Anau e isi na mahi ki hoki te ora Anau raa, tena Anau e isi na mahi hoki ki too muri te ora Anau raa. Teenei hea te Tamana e tattara mai Anau ki ppena.” 
\p  
\v 19 Tena na tama raa ku hakataukoti hokolaatou, e mee na tattara Jisas raa.  
\v 20 Tammaki na tama e tattara ma, “Tama naa e isi te tipua! Tama naa ku vvare! Aiea kootou e hakallono Tama naa naea?” 
\p  
\v 21 Emeia alaa tama e tattara ma, “Te tama e isi te tipua i roto aia se lavaa te tattara peenei! Te tipua se lavaa te mee na tama karemata sseni raa ki kkite!” 
\s1 Te kanohenua raa se hihai ki hakattina Jisas 
\p  
\v 22 Teenaa ko te saaita te haumallii, tena te kanohenua Jerusalem raa ku kkai te Kai na Jiu raa e tataohi ki mannatu te Hakatapu te Hare Tapu.  
\v 23 Jisas e hahaere vaa te kina te Paaro Solomon i roto te Hare Tapu raa,  
\v 24 tena te kanohenua raa ki hakkutu ake iaa Jisas, tena ki vahiri ake Tama raa ma, “Akoe e mee roo maatou ki hakattari te saaita roroa roo. Tattara mai te hakamaoni: Akoe ko te Mesaia?” 
\p  
\v 25 Kito Jisas ki meake, “Anau ku oti te meatu kootou, e meia kootou se hihhai ki hakattina Anau. Na mee Anau e ppena i na mahi te Tamana Anau raa e huri atu ki illoa kootou koai Anau,  
\v 26 e meia kootou se hihhai ki hakattina Anau, maitaname kootou seai ma ni sipsip Anau.  
\v 27 Na sipsip Anau raa e hakallono te reo Anau; Anau e iroa laatou, tena laatou e tauttari Anau.  
\v 28 Anau e kou ake laatou te ora e ora tahi, tena laatou se lavaa roo te mmate. Se hai tama e lavaa te too laatou i taha ma Anau.  
\v 29 Hea te Tamana e kou mai Anau raa e hakanaaniu i aruna na mee hakaatoa, tena se hai tama e lavaa te too laatou i taha ma na rima te Tamana.  
\v 30 Anau ma te Tamana e hokotahi roo.” 
\p  
\v 31 Tena te kanohenua raa ki too hoki na hatu raa ma ki maka Jisas.  
\v 32 Tena Jisas ki meake na tama raa, “Anau e ppena tammaki roo na mee taualleka tera te Tamana raa e kou mai Anau ki ppena i mua na karemata kootou; kaa hea Anau e ppena tera kootou e hihhai ki maka Anau ma na hatu naa?” 
\p  
\v 33 Kito na tama raa ki meake, “Maatou se hihhai ki maka Akoe na hatu e mee na mee taualleka Akoe e ppena raa, e meia e mee Akoe e tattara haeo TeAtua! Akoe he tama koi, e meia Akoe e hihai ki mee ma Akoe ko TeAtua!” 
\p  
\v 34 Tena Jisas ki meake, “E mmau i roto na tuaa kootou raa pera ma TeAtua e mee ma, ‘Kootou ni atua.’  
\v 35 Taatou e illoa pera ma hea e mmau i roto te Launiu Tapu raa e hakamaoni, tena TeAtua e kanna na tama tera Aia ni kou ake na tattara Aia raa ma ni atua.  
\v 36 Ia i te vahi Anau, te Tamana e hirihiri Anau, tena ki kauna ria mai Anau ki hamai i te maarama nei. Kaa kootou e tattara ma Anau e tattara haeo TeAtua peehee, e mee Anau e tattara ma Anau he Tamariki TeAtua?  
\v 37 Kame Anau se ppena hea te Tamana e hihai Anau ki ppena raa, tena auu se hakattina Anau.  
\v 38 Emeia kame Anau e ppena na mee raa, niaina kootou se hakattina Anau, kootou e tau te hakattina hea Anau e ppena raa ki lavaa kootou te illoa na vahao hakaatoa pera ma te Tamana e noho i roto Anau, tena Anau e noho i roto te Tamana.” 
\p  
\v 39 Tena na tama raa ku hahaivi hoki ma ki hakapiki Jisas, e meia Aia hakalliha i taha ma na tama raa no haere. 
\p  
\v 40 Jisas ku vaakai hakaraoi i teeraa vahi te riva Jordan raa, i te kina Jon ni hakoukou tapu na tama raa, tena Aia ki noho i te kina raa.  
\v 41 Tammaki na tama e oo ake iaa Jisas no meake ma, “Jon se hai mirakol e huri mai, e meia na tattara hakaatoa aia e tattara i te Tama nei raa e hakamaoni.”  
\v 42 Tena tammaki na tama i te kina raa ku hakattina iaa Jisas. 
\c 11  
\s1 Te mate Lasarus 
\p  
\v 1 He tama e laavea e noho i roto Betani, te inoa aia raa ko Lasarus. Betani ko te matakaina te haanau Meri laaua ma Marta e nnoho.  
\v 2 (Te Meri nei ko te hine tera ni nnini te lloo manoni raa i aruna na tapuvae TeAriki raa, tena ki hakapakupaku na tapuvae Tama raa ma na rouru aia. Tena Lasarus te tama e laavea raa he kave Meri.)  
\v 3 Te haanau hhine raa e kkave te tattara iaa Jisas ma, “TeAriki, te soa laoi Akoe raa ku laavea.” 
\p  
\v 4 Te saaita Jisas ni rono na tattara raa, tena Aia ki tattara ake ma, “Te hakaotioti te maahana Lasarus nei seai ma ko te mate; te mee nei e kapihi mai ma ki lavaa TeAtua te huri mai na mahi hai mmahi, tena na mahi naa e me ki huri ake pera ma te Tamariki TeAtua raa e me ki too na mahi hai mmahi.” 
\p  
\v 5 Jisas e laoi te hai taina Marta laaua ma Meri ia ma Lasarus te kave laaua raa,  
\v 6 ia niaina ma Aia e rono ma Lasarus e laavea, e meia Aia e noho koi i te kina raa no tae e rua na aho.  
\v 7 Tena Aia ki meake na disaipol Aia raa, “Taatou ki vakkai i Judia.” 
\p  
\v 8 Kito na disaipol raa ki meake, “Rabai, paa saaita raa koi na tama i te matakaina raa e hihhai ma ki maka Akoe na hatu, tena Akoe ku maanatu ma ki vaakai hoki i te kina raa?” 
\p  
\v 9 Tena Jisas ki meake, “Te laa raa e hopo ake te tahata, tena ki huru te hiahi, kaa seai? Tena te tama e hahaere te ao raa se lavaa te ppaku na mee no hhina, maitaname laatou e kkite te maahina te maarama nei raa.  
\v 10 Emeia kame na tama raa e hahaere te poo, tena laatou e me ki ppaku no hhina, maitaname laatou se kkite te maahina te maarama nei raa.” 
\p  
\v 11 Jisas e tattara peenei, tena ki hakapaa ake hoki ma, “Lasarus te soa taatou raa ku moe heiroa, e meia Anau e me ki haere no hakaaraa aia ki maahuru.” 
\p  
\v 12 Kito na disaipol raa ki meake, “TeAriki, kame aia e moe, tama naa e me ki tauareka.” 
\p  
\v 13 Jisas e tattara pera ma Lasarus ku mate, e meia na disaipol raa e kkahu ma Lasarus e moe heiroa koi.  
\v 14 Kito Jisas ki tattara hakamatahua ake ma, “Lasarus ku mate,  
\v 15 e meia Anau e hihia e mee Anau se noho i te kina raa, tena Anau e hihai ma kootou ki kkite ki lavaa kootou te hakattina. Taatou ki oo no mmata aia.” 
\p  
\v 16 Tena Tomas e hui ma te Kokoa raa ku meake na disaipol laatou raa, “Taatou hakaatoa ki oo ma te Rabai raa ki mmate taatou ma Tama raa!” 
\s1 Jisas ko te Ora muri ia ma te Ora e ora tahi 
\p  
\v 17 Te saaita Jisas ni tae i Betani raa, tena Aia ku rono pera ma Lasarus ku oti te tanu e haa na aho ku llaka raa.  
\v 18 Betani e rua na mael se mmao hoki i taha ma Jerusalem,  
\v 19 tena tammaki na tama i Judia ni oo ake no mmata Marta laaua ma Meri ma ki hakatatarahia tokorua raa i te mate Lasarus raa. 
\p  
\v 20 Te saaita Marta ni rono ma Jisas ku tae ake, tena aia ki haere no mmata Tama raa, e meia Meri e noho koi i hare.  
\v 21 Kito Marta ki meake Jisas ma, “TeAriki, peeraa koi Akoe ki noho i te kina nei, te kave anau raa se lavaa te mate!  
\v 22 Emeia anau e iroa pera ma TeAtua e me ki kou atu Akoe hea Akoe e kainno ake Aia raa.” 
\p  
\v 23 Kito Jisas ki meake, “Te kave akoe raa e me ki ora muri.” 
\p  
\v 24 Tena Marta ki meake, “Anau e iroa pera ma aia e me ki ora muri i te aho hakaoti raa.” 
\p  
\v 25 Kito Jisas ki meake Marta, “Anau ko te ora muri ia ma te ora e ora tahi. Na tama e hakattina Anau raa e me ki ora, niaina laatou ku mmate;  
\v 26 tena na tama hakaatoa e ora tera e hakattina Anau raa se lavaa te mmate. Akoe e hakatina te tattara nei?” 
\p  
\v 27 Tena Marta ki meake, “Hakamaoni roo, TeAriki! Anau e hakatina pera ma Akoe ko te Mesaia, te Tamariki TeAtua tera ni hamai i te maarama nei raa.” 
\s1 Jisas ku tani te aroha 
\p  
\v 28 Marta e tattara ake no oti, tena aia ki vaakai i hare no kanna hemuu ake Meri te taina aia raa. Tena Marta ki meake Meri ma, “Te Rabai raa ku tae mai, tena Aia e vahiri akoe.”  
\v 29 Te saaita Meri ni rono na tattara nei, aia ku mahike no haere hakavave no mmata Jisas.  
\v 30 (Jisas se ki tae roo i roto te matakaina, e meia Aia e noho koi i te kina Marta ni ttiri Aia raa.)  
\v 31 Na tama e nnoho i hare ma Meri no hakatatarahia te tama raa ku tauttari Meri te saaita laatou ni kkite aia ni mahike i aruna no haere hakavave i aho raa. Na tama raa e kkahu ma Meri ku haere i te kava no tanitani. 
\p  
\v 32 Meri ku tae i te kina Jisas e noho raa, tena te saaita koi aia ni kite Jisas, aia ku hina atu i mua na vae Jisas. Tena Meri ki meake, “TeAriki, peeraa Akoe ki noho i te kina nei, te kave anau raa se lavaa te mate!” 
\p  
\v 33 Jisas e kite Meri e tani, tena ki kite hoki na tama e ttuu vaa raa e tanittani laatou ma Meri, tena te aroha Aia raa ku haere ake roo.  
\v 34 Kito Jisas ki vahiri ake na tama raa, “Kootou e tanu Lasarus i hee?” 
\p Tena na tama raa ki meake, “TeAriki, Hamai no mmata.” 
\p  
\v 35 Jisas ku tani. 
\p  
\v 36 Na tama raa ku tattara ma, “Kira ake, Jisas e aroha mahi roo Lasarus!” 
\p  
\v 37 Emeia alaa tama e tattara ma, “Tama raa e mee na tama karemata sseni raa no kkite, kaa seai? Kaa Aia se lavaa peehee te mee Lasarus ki se mate?” 
\s1 Jisas e hakaora Lasarus no ora 
\p  
\v 38 Te aroha Jisas raa ku haere ake hakaraoi, tena Aia ki haere i te taruma. Te taruma raa he rua e tuu te vahi te mouna, tena te hatu raa e ppui te totoka te taruma raa.  
\v 39 Tena Jisas ki meake, “Hakatupe te hatu raa i taha!” 
\p Tena Marta te kave Lasarus raa ki meake, “TeAriki, te kina nei e me ki purau roo. Tama naa e tanu e haa na aho ku llaka raa!” 
\p  
\v 40 Kito Jisas ki meake Marta, “Anau ni mee raa se meatu ma akoe e me ki kite na mahi hai mmahi TeAtua raa kame akoe e hakattina?” 
\p  
\v 41 Kito na tama raa ki hakatupe te hatu raa i taha. Tena Jisas ki kkira i aruna no meake, “Tamana, Anau e hakammaha Akoe e mee Akoe e hakarono Anau.  
\v 42 Anau e iroa pera ma Akoe e hakarono Anau na vahao roo hakaatoa, e meia Anau e tattara peenei ki mee na tama e ttuu i te kina nei raa ki hakattina pera ma Akoe e kauna ria mai Anau.”  
\v 43 Jisas e lotu ake peenei no oti, tena Aia ki kanna ake hakamaroa roo ma, “Lasarus, hamai i aho!”\fig Jisas e hakaora Lasarus.|src="wa03869b.tif" size="col" ref="11.43" \fig* 
\v 44 Kito Lasarus ki hamai i aho, e meia na paamaro na tama raa ni mmini na rima ia ma na vae aia raa e mmau koi, hakapaa ma te paamaro e uhi na karemata aia raa. Tena Jisas ki meake na tama raa, “Vvete na paamaro raa i taha ma te tama raa, tena ku tiaki aia ki haere.” 
\s1 Na tama hakamattua na Jiu raa e tattara no tonu ki taa Jisas ki mate 
\r (Matiu 26.1–5; Mak 14.1–2; Luk 22.1–2) 
\p  
\v 45 Tammaki na tama ni oo ake no mmata Meri raa e kkite hea Jisas ni ppena raa, tena na tama raa ku hakattina iaa Jisas.  
\v 46 Emeia e isi na tama e vakkai no meake na Farisi raa hea Jisas ni ppena raa.  
\v 47 Kito na Farisi raa laatou ma na maatua hakananniu raa ku kkutu ma na tama hakamattua na Jiu raa no tattara ma, “Hea taatou e me ki ppena? Kira ake na mirakol hakaatoa te Tama nei ni ppena raa!  
\v 48 Kame taatou e tiaki Tama nei ki tauhano no ppena na mee nei, tena na tama hakaatoa e me ki hakattina Tama nei, tena na tama hakamattua i Rom raa e me ki oo mai no seu te Hare Tapu ia ma te henua taatou nei!” 
\p  
\v 49 He tama hokotahi na tama raa, te inoa aia raa ko Kaiafas, tena aia ko te pohouru hakanaaniu na maatua te hetau naa. Tama raa e meake ma, “Kootou ni vvare hakaatoa!  
\v 50 Kootou se isi na hakataakoto pera ma e tauareka kootou te tiaki he tama hokotahi ki mate ma na tama hakaatoa, ki se lavaa na tama te henua raa te taaia ria no mmate hakaatoa?”  
\v 51 Te hakamaoni, Kaiafas se tattara peenei i te hakataakoto koi aia; e meia e mee aia ko te pohouru hakanaaniu na maatua te hetau naa, tena aia ki tattara ake pera ma Jisas e me ki mate ma na Jiu hakaatoa,  
\v 52 ia se mee ma na Jiu raa koi, e meia ki hakkutu mai hakaatoa na tama TeAtua tera e nnoho maseu raa ki mee pera ma he kanohenua hokotahi. 
\p  
\v 53 Kaamata te aho naa, na tama hakamattua na Jiu raa ku penapena na hakataakoto ma ki taa Jisas ki mate.  
\v 54 Tena Jisas ku se hahaere ki kkite na tama i Judia raa, e meia Aia e haere i te kina e tuu taapiri te kina e tuu mahoa i te matakaina e hui ma ko Efraim raa, tena Aia ki nnoho ma na disaipol Aia raa i te kina raa. 
\p  
\v 55 Te saaita te Kai te Pasova raa ku taapiri, tena tammaki na tama ku tiaki na matakaina laatou raa no oo i Jerusalem ki mee na ora laatou raa ki matahua i mua na maihu TeAtua.  
\v 56 Na tama raa ku sesee Jisas, tena te saaita laatou ni kkutu hakaatoa i roto te Hare Tapu raa, na tama raa ku vahihhiri hokolaatou ma, “Kootou e mannatu maea? Tama naa kame se lavaa te hamai te Kai nei!”  
\v 57 Na maatua hakananniu raa laatou ma na Farisi raa e kou ake te tattara ma kame he tama e iroa te kina Jisas e noho raa, tena te tama naa ku haere ake no meake laatou ki oo laatou no hakapiki Tama raa. 
\c 12  
\s1 Te hine e amuhi Jisas i Betani 
\r (Matiu 26.6–13; Mak 14.3–9) 
\p  
\v 1 Ia e ono na aho i mua te Kai te Pasova raa, Jisas ku vaakai i Betani i te hare Lasarus, te tama Aia ni hakaora raa.  
\v 2 Na tama raa e tanattana na kai ki kai Jisas i te hare raa, kito Marta e parepare ake na kai raa, tena Lasarus e noho hoki i te tebol raa ma Jisas.  
\v 3 Tena Meri ku too te lloo manoni e sui mmaha tera e hakauru ma te nad\f + \fr 12.3 \ft teenei he laakau e homo i na mouna i roto North India; na patiaka ma te tinotama te laakau raa e manoni roo\f* raa, tena ki nnini te lloo raa i aruna na tapuvae Jisas raa, tena ki hakapakupaku ma te rouru aia raa. Te manoni te lloo raa ku taakai vaa roto te hare raa hakaatoa.  
\v 4 Judas Iskariot, he disaipol hoki Jisas, ia te tama e me ki oti ku hakari ake Jisas i na tama hakamattua raa ku meake ma,  
\v 5 “Aiea te lloo nei se kou ake alaa tama ki taui e toru huitarau na sileni\f + \fr 12.5 \ft teenei ko te kooina te sui te tama i roto te hetau hakaatoa\f*, tena na sileni naa ku mee ki tokonaki na tama hakaalloha raea?”  
\v 6 Judas e tattara peenei se mee ma aia e maanatu na tama hakaalloha raa, e meia e mee aia he tama kairarao. Judas e hahaere ma te muri kopu na sileni, tena aia e kairarao hoki na sileni raa. 
\p  
\v 7 Emeia Jisas e meake ma, “Tiaki te hine naa! Te hine naa e tataohi roo te lloo raa ki tanattana te aho Anau e me ki tanu raa.  
\v 8 Na tama hakaalloha raa e me ki nnoho tahi ma kootou, e meia Anau se lavaa te noho tahi ma kootou.” 
\s1 Te kanohenua raa e hihhai ki kkite Lasarus 
\p  
\v 9 Tammaki na Jiu ku llono ma Jisas ku tae i Betani, tena laatou ki oo i te matakaina raa, ia laatou se oo koi e mee Jisas e noho i te kina raa, e meia laatou e oo e mee laatou e hihai hoki ki kkite Lasarus, te tama ni mate raa, tena Jisas ki hakaora aia no ora raa.  
\v 10 Kito na maatua hakananniu raa ki tattara ma ki taa hoki Lasarus ki mate,  
\v 11 maitaname te tattara te ora muri Lasarus raa e mee na Jiu raa no se hakattina laatou, tena ki hakattina koi iaa Jisas. 
\s1 Jisas ku haere i Jerusalem pera ma he tuku 
\r (Matiu 21.1–11; Mak 11.1–11; Luk 19.28–40) 
\p  
\v 12 Te aho taiao raa, na tama ni oo ake i te Kai te Pasova raa ku llono ma Jisas ku haere ake i Jerusalem.  
\v 13 Kito na tama raa ki tuutuu na raraa na laakau raa, tena ki oo ake ma ki ttiri Jisas; na tama raa e haere vavaa ma, 
\q1 “Hakammaha TeAtua! 
\q1 TeAtua e hakatapu te Tama e hamai i te inoa TeAriki raa! 
\q1 TeAtua e hakatapu te Tuku Israel!” 
\m  
\v 14 Jisas e kite te donki, tena ki kake i aruna te manu raa no tere, e ssau pera ma hea e mmau i roto te Launiu Tapu ma, 
\q1  
\v 15 “Te matakaina e rahi Saion, auu se mattaku! 
\q1 Teenei te Tuku kootou nei ku hamai, 
\q1 ia e tere atu i aruna te donki.” 
\m  
\v 16 Na disaipol raa se illoa te mee nei i te kaamata; e meia te saaita Jisas ni ora muri ma na mahi hai mmahi raa, tena laatou ku mannatu na tattara e mmau i roto te Launiu Tapu tera e tattara i te vahi Jisas raa, tena laatou se ppena hoki te mee nei ma ki hakammaha Tama raa. 
\p  
\v 17 Te kanohenua ni ttuu i te kina raa ma Jisas te saaita Aia ni kanna ake Lasarus ki hamai i aho ma te taruma raa, tena ki hakaora tama raa ku tattara ake hea ni kapihi ake raa.  
\v 18 Tera hea te kanohenua raa e oo ma ki ttiri laatou ma Jisas, maitaname laatou e llono ma teeraa ko Jisas e ppena te mirakol raa.  
\v 19 Kito na Farisi raa ki tattara hokolaatou ma, “Kootou e kkite, taatou ku seai i na mee roo hakaatoa! Kira ake, te maarama nei hakaatoa ku tauttari Tama raa!” 
\s1 Na tama i Grik raa ku sesee Jisas 
\p  
\v 20 E isi na Grik hoki i roto na tama e oo i Jerusalem ma ki lotu te saaita te Kai raa.  
\v 21 Na tama raa e oo iaa Filip raa (teenei he tama i Betsaida i roto Galili) no meake, “Tama hakamaatua, maatou e hihhai ki kkite Jisas.” 
\p  
\v 22 Kito Filip ki haere no meake Andru, tena tokorua raa ki oo no meake Jisas.  
\v 23 Tena Jisas ki meake tokorua raa, “Te saaita te Tamariki te Tama nei e me ki too na mahi hai mmahi raa ku tae mai.  
\v 24 Anau e tattara atu te hakamaoni: te hua te wit raa e me ki se lavaa te tammaki na kai kame aia se tteiho i aruna te kerekere raa no mate. Kame te hua raa e mate, tena na hua aia e hua raa e me ki tammaki roo.  
\v 25 Na tama e hakasessere na ora laatou raa e me ki llano i taha ma te ora hakamaoni raa, tena na tama se mannako na ora laatou i te maarama nei raa e me ki too te ora e ora tahi.  
\v 26 Te tama e hihai ki hehekau ma Anau raa ki tautari Anau, ki lavaa na tama hehekau Anau raa te nnoho ma Anau i te kina Anau e noho raa. Tena te Tamana Anau raa e me ki hakammaha na tama e hehekau ma Anau raa. 
\s1 Jisas e tattara i te mate Aia 
\p  
\v 27 “Te saaita nei Anau ku tipuaina haeo roo i roto Anau. Kaa hea Anau e me ki meake? Eaa, Anau ki meake ma, ‘Tamana, Auu se tiaki te saaita raa ki tae mai’? Emeia, kaa teenaa kaa hea Anau e hamai naa. Anau e hamai ki hakalono llihu te saaita naa.  
\v 28 Tamana, kou mai na mahi hai mmahi i te inoa Akoe!” 
\p Tena te reo raa ki tattara iho i te vaelani ma, “Anau ku oti te kou atu na mahi hai mmahi i te inoa Anau, tena Anau e me ki kou atu hakaraoi na mahi naa.” 
\p  
\v 29 Te kanohenua e ttuu i te kina raa e llono te reo raa, tena alaa tama ki tattara ma teeraa he hatturi, ia alaa tama e mee ma, “Teeraa he ensel e tattara ake Tama raa!” 
\p  
\v 30 Emeia Jisas e tattara ake na tama raa ma, “Te reo raa se tattara iho ma ki rono Anau, e meia ki llono kootou.  
\v 31 Te saaita nei ko te saaita e me ki hakatonutonu te maarama nei; te saaita nei te tama hakamatua i te maarama nei raa e me ki hakattuu ria i taha ma te kakkake aia raa.  
\v 32 Te saaita Anau e me ki ssau ria i aruna no haere i taha ma te maarama nei raa, Anau e me ki hakattaki mai na tama hakaatoa i te maarama nei raa ki haere Anau.”  
\v 33 Jisas e tattara ake peenei ki huri ake te mate ia ma na hakalono llihu Aia. 
\p  
\v 34 Kito te kanohenua raa ki meake, “Na tuaa taatou raa e tattara mai ma te Mesaia raa e me ki noho tahi roo. Kaa Akoe e tattara peehee ma te Tamariki te Tama nei e me ki ssau ria i aruna? Tena kaa koai te Tamariki te Tama nei naa?” 
\p  
\v 35 Kito Jisas ki meake, “Te Maahina raa e me ki nnoho ma kootou paa saaita koi. Kootou ki hahaere te saaita te Maahina raa e nnoho ma kootou, ki se lavaa te pouri raa te haere atu no uhi kootou; maitaname te tama e hahaere i roto te pouri raa se iroa te kina aia e haere raa.  
\v 36 Hakattina i te Maahina raa, te saaita te Maahina raa e nnoho ma kootou, tena kootou e me ki mee pera ma ni tama te maahina.” 
\s1 Na Jiu raa se hakattina 
\p Jisas e tattara ake na tattara nei no oti, tena Aia ki haere no mmuni i taha ma na tama raa.  
\v 37 Niaina roo ma Jisas e ppena na mirakol nei i mua na karemata na tama raa, e meia na tama raa se hakattina koi iaa Jisas,  
\v 38 tena hea profet Aisaia ni tattara raa ku huri mai no hakamaoni ma: 
\q1 “TeAriki, koai te tama e hakatina na tattara maatou e tattara ake raa? 
\q1 TeAriki e huri ake na mahi Aia raa aii?” 
\m  
\v 39 Tena na tama raa se lavaa te hakattina e mee Aisaia e tattara hoki ma: 
\q1  
\v 40 “TeAtua e mee na karemata na tama raa no sseni, 
\q1 tena ki ppui na hakataakoto na tama raa, 
\q1 ki se lavaa na karemata na tama raa te kkite, 
\q1 tena na kapuroro na tama raa se lavaa te illoa, 
\q1 tena TeAtua e mee ma na tama raa se lavaa te oo ake Aia, 
\q1 ma ki tokonaki Tama raa na tama raa.” 
\m  
\v 41 Aisaia e tattara peenei, maitaname aia e kite na mahi hai mmahi Jisas; tera hea aia e tattara i te vahi Tama raa. 
\p  
\v 42 Niaina ma e tammaki na tama hakamattua na Jiu raa e hakattina iaa Jisas, e meia laatou se hihhai ki tattara ma ki llono na tama e mee laatou e mattaku na Farisi raa; ma ka oti na tama raa ku hakatuu laatou i taha ma te hare lotu.  
\v 43 Na Farisi raa e mannatu ma na tama ki hakammaha koi laatou, tena laatou se mannatu hoki ma TeAtua ki hakammaha laatou. 
\s1 Na tattara hakatonutonu Jisas 
\p  
\v 44 Jisas e tattara ake hakamaroa ma, “Te tama e hakatina Anau raa se mee ma e hakatina koi Anau, e meia aia e hakatina hoki te Tama e kauna ria mai Anau raa.  
\v 45 Ia te tama e kite Anau raa e kite hoki te Tama e kauna ria mai Anau raa.  
\v 46 Anau e hamai i roto te maarama nei pera ma he maahina, ki se lavaa na tama hakaatoa e hakattina Anau raa te nnoho koi i roto te pouri raa.  
\v 47 Kame he tama e rono na tattara Anau raa no se tautari; Anau se lavaa te hakatonutonu te tama naa. Anau se hamai ki hakatonutonu te maarama nei, e meia Anau e hamai ki tokonaki te maarama nei.  
\v 48 Na tama se hihhai Anau, ia se hihhai hoki ki too na tattara Anau raa e isi te Tama hokotahi e me ki hakatonutonu laatou. Na tattara Anau e tattara raa ko na tattara tera e me ki hakatonutonu laatou i te aho hakaoti raa!  
\v 49 Te tattara nei e hakamaoni, maitaname Anau se tattara i na mahi Anau Hokonnau, e meia te Tamana ni kauna ria mai Anau raa e tattara mai hea Anau e me ki tattara atu raa.  
\v 50 Tena Anau e iroa pera ma na tattara Aia raa e kou mai te ora e ora tahi. Tena na tattara Anau e tattara raa, ni tattara Tamana e tattara mai Anau ki tattara atu.” 
\c 13  
\s1 Jisas e huhui na tapuvae na disaipol Aia 
\p  
\v 1 Teenaa ko te aho i mua te Kai te Pasova raa. Jisas e iroa pera ma te saaita Aia ku mee ki tiaki te maarama nei no vaakai te Tamana raa ku tae mai. Aia na vahao hakaatoa e laoi na tama i roto te maarama nei tera e mee pera ma ni tama roo Aia raa, tena Aia e laoi na tama raa haere no tae roo te hakaoti. 
\p  
\v 2 Jisas ma na disaipol Aia raa e nnoho ma ki kkai te hiahi. Emeia Satan ku oti te kou ake te hakataakoto iaa Judas Iskariot, te tama Saimon raa ma ki hakari ake Jisas i na tama hakamattua raa.  
\v 3 Jisas e iroa pera ma te Tamana e kou ake na mahi hakaatoa Aia, tena Aia e iroa pera ma Aia e hamai i TeAtua, tena e me ki vaakai i TeAtua.  
\v 4 Kito Jisas ki mahike i taha ma te tebol raa no ui te kaukahu Aia raa, tena ki nnoa te muri maro raa areha na paioro Aia.  
\v 5 Kito Aia ki nnini na vai raa i roto te paa kumete, tena ki kaamata no huhui na tapuvae na disaipol raa, tena Aia ki hakapakupaku na tapuvae na tama raa ma te muri maro Aia e nnoa areha na paioro Aia raa. 
\p  
\v 6 Jisas e haere huhui na tapuvae na tama raa no tae ake Saimon Pita, tena Saimon Pita ki meake, “TeAriki, Akoe e me ki huhui na tapuvae anau?” 
\p  
\v 7 Tena Jisas ki meake Pita, “Te saaita nei akoe se iroa hea Anau e ppena nei, e meia i muri akoe e me ki iroa.” 
\p  
\v 8 Kito Pita ki meake, “Akoe se lavaa roo te huhui na tapuvae anau he saaita!” 
\p Tena Jisas ki meake, “Kame Anau se huhui na tapuvae akoe naa, tena akoe se lavaa te mee pera ma he disaipol Anau.” 
\p  
\v 9 Kito Saimon Pita ki meake, “TeAriki, kame peenaa Akoe se lavaa te huhui koi na tapuvae anau nei! Huhui hoki na rima ia ma te pohouru anau raa.” 
\p  
\v 10 Tena Jisas ki meake, “Na tama e koukou hakaatoa raa ku matahua roo, tena laatou ku se tau hoki te koukkou, e meia na tapuvae laatou raa e kkere koi. Kootou hakaatoa e matahua, e meia he tama hokotahi se matahua.” 
\p  
\v 11 (Jisas ko na iroa roo avare te tama e me ki hakari ake Aia i na tama hakamattua raa; tera hea Aia e tattara ma, “Kootou hakaatoa e matahua, e meia he tama hokotahi koi se matahua.”) 
\p  
\v 12 Jisas e huhui na tapuvae na disaipol raa no oti, tena Aia ki uru hakaraoi te kaukahu Aia raa, tena ki vaakai no noho te kina Aia ni noho raa. Kito Aia ki meake, “Kootou e illoa hea Anau e ppena i kootou te saaita nei?  
\v 13 Kootou e kakanna Anau Rabai ia ma TeAriki, tena e tonu kootou te ppena peenaa, maitaname teenei Anau nei.  
\v 14 Anau TeAriki ia ma te Rabai kootou nei e huhui vahao nei koi na tapuvae kootou raa. Tena kootou hoki ki huhui na tapuvae kootou hokkootou.  
\v 15 Anau e huri atu hea kootou e me ki ppena raa, tena kootou e me ki ppena hea Anau ni ppena i kootou te saaita nei raa.  
\v 16 Anau e tattara atu te hakamaoni: te tama hehekau raa se hakamaatua i aruna te tama hakamaatua aia raa, tena na tama e kavekave na tattara raa se hakamattua i aruna te tama e kauna laatou raa.  
\v 17 Teenei kootou ku illoa te hakamaoni nei te saaita nei, tena kootou e me ki hihhia roo kame kootou e tauttari na mee nei. 
\p  
\v 18 “Anau se tattara kootou hakaatoa; Anau e iroa na tama Anau e hirihiri raa. Emeia na tattara i roto te Launiu Tapu nei e me ki hakamaoni, 
\q1 ‘Te tama e kaikkai hakapaa maaua na kai anau raa e me ki huri no haeo anau.’ 
\m  
\v 19 Anau e tattara atu na mee nei i mua na mee nei e kapihi atu, tena te saaita na mee nei e kapihi atu raa, kootou e me ki hakattina pera ma, ‘Anau ko Nau koi’.  
\v 20 Anau e tattara atu te hakamaoni; koai te tama e too hakaraoi te tama Anau e kauna raa e too hakaraoi hoki Anau, tena koai e too hakaraoi Anau e too hakaraoi hoki te Tama e kauna ria mai Anau raa.” 
\s1 Judas e me ki hakari ake Jisas i na tama hakamattua raa 
\r (Matiu 26.20–25; Mak 14.17–21; Luk 22.21–23) 
\p  
\v 21 Jisas e tattara ake peenei no oti, tena Aia ku tipuaina haeo roo, kito Aia ki meake tahi koi na tama raa ma, “Anau e meatu te hakamaoni: he tama kootou e me ki hakari ake Anau i na tama hakamattua raa.” 
\p  
\v 22 Tena na disaipol raa ku oho no kirakira huri hokolaatou ma Jisas e tattara aii.  
\v 23 Tena he disaipol hokotahi, te tama Jisas e hihai mahi raa, e noho taapiri ake Jisas.  
\v 24 Kito Saimon Pita ki auna ake te tama raa, tena ki meake, “Vahiri atu Tama raa ma Aia e tattara aii.” 
\p  
\v 25 Kito te disaipol raa ki hakapare atu te vahi Jisas raa no vahiri ake ma, “TeAriki, koai te tama naa?” 
\p  
\v 26 Tena Jisas ki meake, “Anau e me ki ttoki ni haraoa i roto te hakamomoa raa, tena ku kou ake te tama naa; teenaa ko te tama Anau e tattara.” Kito Jisas ki too te muri haraoa raa no ttoki te hakamomoa raa, tena ki kou ake Judas, te tama Saimon Iskariot raa.  
\v 27 Te saaita koi Judas ni too te haraoa raa, Satan ku tau i roto aia. Kito Jisas ki meake tama raa, “Akoe ki vave ma hea akoe e me ki ppena raa!”  
\v 28 Iaa se hai tama na disaipol raa e illoa ma Jisas e meake peeraa iaa Judas raea.  
\v 29 E mee Judas ko te tama e rorohi te muri kopu na sileni raa, tena e isi na disaipol e mannatu ma Jisas e meake Judas ki haere no sui hea laatou e hihhai ki mee te kai raa, ia seai naa ku kou ake ni mee ma na tama hakaalloha raa. 
\p  
\v 30 Judas e too te haraoa raa, tena ki haere i aho te saaita naa koi. Te mee raa ku poo. 
\s1 Te tuaa vahao nei 
\p  
\v 31 Judas ku oti te haere, tena Jisas ki meake, “Te saaita nei kootou e me ki kkite na mahi hai mmahi te Tamariki te Tama nei; te saaita nei Aia e me ki huri ake na mahi hai mmahi TeAtua raa i roto Aia.  
\v 32 Tena kame Aia e huri ake na mahi hai mmahi TeAtua raa i roto Aia, TeAtua e me ki huri ake hoki na mahi te Tamariki te Tama nei i roto Aia, tena Aia e me ki ppena koi peenei te vahao hokotahi nei.  
\v 33 Aku tamalliki, Anau se lavaa te nnoho ma kootou saaita roroa hoki. Kootou e me ki sesee Anau; e meia Anau e meatu kootou te saaita nei hea Anau ni meake na tama hakamattua na Jiu raa ma, ‘Kootou se lavaa te oo i te kina Anau e me ki haere raa.’  
\v 34 Tena te saaita nei Anau e me ki kou atu te tuaa vahao nei: laoi te tama ma te tama. Tena kootou ki laoi te tama ma te tama e ssau pera ma Anau e laoi kootou.  
\v 35 Kame kootou e laoi te tama ma te tama, tena na tama hakaatoa e me ki illoa pera ma kootou ni disaipol Anau.” 
\s1 Pita e kore e toru na vahao ma aia se iroa Jisas 
\r (Matiu 26.31–35; Mak 14.27–31; Luk 22.31–34) 
\p  
\v 36 Kito Saimon Pita ki vahiri ake Jisas, “TeAriki, Akoe e me ki haere i hee?” 
\p Tena Jisas ki meake, “Akoe se lavaa te tautari mai Anau te saaita nei, e meia i muri akoe e me ki tautari mai Anau.” 
\p  
\v 37 Kito Pita ki meake, “TeAriki, aiea anau se lavaa te tautari Akoe te saaita nei naea? Anau e tanattana ki mate ma Akoe!” 
\p  
\v 38 Tena Jisas ki meake, “Akoe e tanattana hakamaoni ki mate ma Anau? Anau e meatu te hakamaoni: i mua te manu tane raa e tani te poo nei, akoe e me ki kore e toru na vahao pera ma akoe se iroa Anau.” 
\c 14  
\s1 Jisas ko te mateara e haere te Tamana 
\p  
\v 1 Tena Jisas ki meake na disaipol raa, “Kootou ki se tipuaina no mamannatu tammaki. Kootou ki hakattina TeAtua, tena ku hakattina hoki Anau.  
\v 2 E tammaki roo na rum i roto te hare te Tamana Anau raa, tena Anau e me ki haere no tanattana ni kina ma kootou. Anau se lavaa te tattara atu peenei kame te mee nei se hakamaoni.  
\v 3 I muri Anau ku oti te haere no tanattana na kina kootou raa, tena Anau e me ki vaakai mai no too kootou ki oo taatou; ki nnoho kootou ma Anau i te kina Anau e noho raa.  
\v 4 Kootou e illoa te mateara e haere i te kina tera Anau e haere raa?” 
\p  
\v 5 Kito Tomas ki meake Jisas, “TeAriki, maatou se illoa te kina Akoe e haere naa; kaa maatou e me ki illoa peehee te mateara e haere no tae i te kina naa?” 
\p  
\v 6 Tena Jisas ki meake Tomas, “Anau ko te Mateara, te Hakamaoni ia ma te Ora; Anau ko te mateara, tena se hai mateara peeraa hoki te tama e lavaa te tae Tamana.  
\v 7 Teenei kootou ku illoa Anau te saaita nei, tena kootou e me ki illoa hoki te Tamana, tena kaamata te saaita nei kootou ku illoa Tama raa, ia kootou ku oti te kkite Tama raa.” 
\p  
\v 8 Kito Filip ki meake Jisas, “TeAriki, huri mai te Tamana ki kkite maatou; teenaa koi hea maatou e hihhai.” 
\p  
\v 9 Tena Jisas ki meake, “Filip, Anau e nnoho ma kootou taku saaita e roroa roo, tena kootou se ki illoa roo Anau? Na tama e kkite Anau raa e kkite Tamana. Tena, kaa kootou e mee mai ma, ‘Huri mai Tamana naea’?  
\v 10 Filip, akoe se hakatina pera ma Anau e noho i roto Tamana, tena Tamana e noho i roto Anau?” Tena Jisas ki meake na disaipol Aia raa ma, “Na tattara Anau e tattara atu kootou raa seai ma ni tattara koi Anau. Te Tamana e noho tahi i roto Anau raa e ppena hea Aia e maanatu ki ppena raa.  
\v 11 Kootou ki hakattina Anau te saaita Anau e meatu pera ma Anau e noho i roto Tamana, tena Tamana e noho i roto Anau. Kaa seai kootou ku hakattina e mee kootou e kkite na mee e llahi Anau ni ppena raa.  
\v 12 Anau e tattara atu te hakamaoni: na tama e hakattina Anau raa e me ki ppena na mee Anau ni ppena raa. Hakamaoni, na tama naa e me ki ppena na mee e llahi roo, maitaname Anau e me ki vaakai no nnoho Maaua ma Tamana.  
\v 13 Tena Anau e me ki ppena he mee peehee kootou e kainno mai i te inoa Anau, ki kkite na tama hakaatoa na mahi hai mmahi TeAtua tera te Tamariki Aia raa e isi.  
\v 14 Kame kootou e kainno mai ni mee peehee i te inoa Anau, tena Anau e me ki ppena hea kootou e kainno mai raa. 
\s1 Jisas e mee ma TeAnana Tapu e me ki hamai 
\p  
\v 15 “Kame kootou e laoi Anau, kootou e me ki tauttari na tuaa Anau raa.  
\v 16 Anau e me ki kainno ake te Tamana Anau raa, tena Aia e me ki kou atu teeraa Tokonaki, te Tama naa e me ki nnoho tahi roo ma kootou.  
\v 17 Te Tama naa ko TeAnana Tapu tera e me ki hakari atu te hakamaoni TeAtua raa. Te maarama nei se lavaa te too Tama raa, e mee te maarama nei se lavaa te kkite, ia te illoa Tama raa. Emeia kootou e illoa Tama raa, maitaname Aia e noho ma kootou, ia e noho hoki i roto kootou. 
\p  
\v 18 “Te saaita Anau e haere raa, Anau se lavaa te tiaki kootou ki nnoho hokkootou; Anau e me ki vaakai mai kootou.  
\v 19 Se roroa te maarama nei ku se lavaa te kkite Anau, e meia kootou e me ki kkite Anau; e mee Anau e ora, tena kootou hoki e me ki ora.  
\v 20 Te saaita te aho naa e tteiho mai raa, kootou e me ki illoa pera ma Anau e noho i roto Tamana, tena kootou e nnoho i roto Anau, e ssau pera ma Anau e noho i roto kootou. 
\p  
\v 21 “Na tama e hakallono na tuaa Anau raa, tena ki tauttari na tuaa raa ko na tama e laoi Anau. Te Tamana Anau raa e me ki laoi na tama tera e laoi Anau raa; Anau hoki e me ki laoi na tama raa, tena ku huri ake Anau Hokonnau i na tama raa.” 
\p  
\v 22 Tena Judas (seai ma ko Judas Iskariot) ki meake, “TeAriki, Akoe e me ki huri mai Akoe Hokkoe i maatou, kaa na tama i te maarama nei raa e me ki seai?” 
\p  
\v 23 Kito Jisas ki meake te tama raa, “Te tama e laoi Anau raa e me ki tauttari na akoako Anau. Te Tamana Anau raa e me ki laoi aia, tena Anau ma te Tamana Anau raa e me ki oo mai no nnoho ma te tama naa.  
\v 24 Te tama se laoi Anau raa se lavaa te tautari na akoako Anau. Tena na akoako kootou ni llono raa seai ma ni akoako Anau, e meia na akoako raa e oo mai Tamana, te Tama ni kauna ria mai Anau raa. 
\p  
\v 25 “Anau ku oti te tattara atu na mee nei te saaita Anau ni nnoho ma kootou raa.  
\v 26 TeAnana Tapu, te Tokonaki kootou tera te Tamana e kauna ria atu kootou i te inoa Anau raa e me ki akoako atu kootou na mee roo hakaatoa, tena ku mee kootou ki mannatu na mee roo hakaatoa Anau ni tattara atu raa. 
\p  
\v 27 “Te noho laoi nei ko te mee Anau e tiaki ki nnoho ma kootou; teenei he noho laoi Anau tera Anau e kou atu kootou. Anau se kou atu pera ma na tiputipu te maarama nei kame e kou atu na mee raa. Auu se tipuaina no mamannatu tammaki; ia auu se mattaku.  
\v 28 Kootou e llono Anau e tattara atu kootou, ‘Anau e me ki haere, e meia Anau e me ki vaakai mai kootou.’ Kame kootou e laoi Anau, tena kootou e me ki hihhia, maitaname Anau e me ki haere te Tamana Anau raa, e mee Aia e hakanaaniu i aruna Anau.  
\v 29 Anau e tattara atu kootou na mee nei vahao nei i mua na mee nei e me ki kapihi atu raa, tena te saaita na mee nei e kapihi atu raa, kootou e me ki hakattina.  
\v 30 Anau se lavaa te tattara ma kootou ki roroa hoki, maitaname te tama hakamaatua te maarama nei raa ku hamai. Tama raa se isi na mahi aia i aruna Anau,  
\v 31 e meia te maarama nei e tau te illoa pera ma Anau e laoi te Tamana; tera hea Anau e ppena na mee hakaatoa Aia e mee mai Anau ki ppena raa. 
\p “Oo mai, taatou ki oo i taha ma te kina nei. 
\c 15  
\s1 Jisas ko te laakau vain hakamaoni 
\p  
\v 1 “Anau ko te laakau vain hakamaoni, tena te Tamana Anau raa ko te Tama te paupaku raa.\fig |src="HK00112B.TIF" size="col" ref="15.1" \fig* 
\v 2 Tama raa e me ki ttuu i taha na raraa Anau tera se hhua na hua raa, tena ku verevere hakaraoi na raraa tera e hhua na hua raa ki attea ki hhua tammaki na hua.  
\v 3 Kootou ku oti te matahua e mee na akoako Anau ni kou atu kootou raa.  
\v 4 Hukui tahi ma Anau, tena Anau e me ki hukui tahi ma kootou. Te raraa hokoia se lavaa te hua na hua, te raraa raa e me ki hua koi kame aia e mmau ma te laakau vain raa. Tena kootou hoki se lavaa te hhua na hua kame kootou se hukui ma Anau. 
\p  
\v 5 “Anau ko te laakau vain, tena kootou ko na raraa. Na tama tera e hukkui ma Anau, tena Anau e hukui ma laatou raa e me ki hhua tammaki na hua; maitaname kootou se lavaa te ppena ni mee kame Anau seai.  
\v 6 Te tama se hukui ma Anau raa e me ki peesia ria pera ma he raraa ki moe no pakupaku; na raraa peenei raa e me ki hakkutu ria no lletu i roto te ahi ki vvela raa.  
\v 7 Kame kootou e hukui ma Anau, tena na uata Anau raa e mmoe i roto kootou, tena kootou e lavaa te kainno mai ni mee peehee kootou e hihhai, tena kootou e me ki too na mee naa.  
\v 8 Na hua kootou e hhua raa e huri ake na mahi hai mmahi te Tamana Anau raa; tera hea kootou e mee pera ma ni disaipol Anau. 
\p  
\v 9 “Anau e laoi kootou pera ma te Tamana e laoi Anau; hukui tahi ma Anau ki laoi Anau kootou.  
\v 10 Kame kootou e tauttari na tattara Anau raa, tena kootou e me ki nnoho i roto te laoi Anau raa, e ssau pera ma Anau e tautari na tattara te Tamana Anau raa, tena Anau e noho i roto te laoi Aia. 
\p  
\v 11 “Anau e tattara atu na mee nei ma ki moe te hihia Anau raa i roto kootou, tena kootou e me ki hihhia hakamaoni.  
\v 12 Te tuaa Anau raa e mee peenei: laoi te tama ma te tama, e ssau pera ma Anau e laoi kootou raa.  
\v 13 Te laoi e rahi roo te tama e lavaa te isi ki tokonaki na soa aia raa ko te ora aia.  
\v 14 Tena kootou e me ki mee pera ma ni soa Anau kame kootou e ppena hea Anau ni tattara atu raa.  
\v 15 Anau ku se lavaa hoki te kanna kootou pera ma ni tama hehekau, maitaname na tama hehekau raa se illoa hea te tama hakamaatua laatou raa e hihai. Emeia Anau e kanna kootou pera ma ni soa Anau, maitaname Anau ku oti te tattara atu na mee hakaatoa Anau e rono te Tamana Anau raa e tattara mai.  
\v 16 Kootou se hirihiri Anau; Anau ni hirihiri kootou, tena ki tini kootou ki oo no hhua tammaki na hua, na hua tera e me ki mmoe tahi raa. Tena te Tamana e me ki kou atu kootou niaa kootou e kainno ake Aia i te inoa Anau.  
\v 17 Teenei te tuaa Anau e meatu kootou: laoi te tama ma te tama. 
\s1 Te kiri lloto na tama te maarama nei 
\p  
\v 18 “Kame na tama te maarama nei e kiri lloto kootou, tena kootou ki mannatu pera ma laatou e kiri lloto Anau i mua.  
\v 19 Kame kootou e tauttari na tiputipu te maarama nei raa, tena na tama te maarama nei raa e me ki hihai roo kootou pera ma ni tama roo laatou. Emeia Anau ni hirihiri kootou ki oo mai i taha ma te maarama nei, tena kootou seai ma ni tama te maarama nei; tera hea na tama te maarama nei raa e kiri lloto kootou.  
\v 20 Mannatu hea Anau ni tattara atu kootou raa: ‘Na tama hehekau raa se hakamattua i aruna na tama hakamattua laatou raa.’ Kame na tama raa e kou mai na hakalono llihu Anau, tena na tama raa e me ki kou atu hoki na hakalono llihu kootou; kame laatou e hakallono na akoako Anau raa, tena na tama raa e me ki hakallono hoki na akoako kootou raa.  
\v 21 Emeia na tama raa e me ki ppena na mee nei hakaatoa i kootou, e mee kootou ni tama Anau, tena laatou hoki se illoa te Tama ni kauna ria mai Anau raa.  
\v 22 Na tama raa se lavaa te mannatu ma laatou e hai ssara, ia peeraa Anau ki se hamai no tattara ake na tama raa, peeraa vahao nei na tama raa se lavaa te tattara huhu na hai sara laatou raa.  
\v 23 Na tama e kiri lloto Anau raa e kiri lloto hoki te Tamana Anau raa.  
\v 24 Na tama raa se lavaa te mannatu ma laatou e hai sara peeraa Anau ki se hamai no ppena i mua na karemata laatou raa na mee tera se hai tama hoki ni ppena raa, tena na tama raa ni kkite na mee Anau ni ppena raa, tena laatou ku kiri lloto Anau ma te Tamana Anau raa.  
\v 25 Emeia na mee nei e me ki kapihi atu ki mee na tattara e mmau i roto na tuaa nei raa ki hakamaoni: ‘Na tama raa e lloto vare koi Anau.’ 
\p  
\v 26 “Te Tokonaki e me ki hamai, teenaa ko TeAnana Tapu tera e hamai i TeAtua raa, tena Aia e me ki hakari mai te hakamaoni Tamana. Anau e me ki kauna ria atu TeAnana Tapu e nnoho laaua ma Tamana raa, tena Aia e me ki tattara atu kootou i te vahi Anau.  
\v 27 Tena kootou hoki e me ki tattara i te vahi Anau, maitaname kootou ni nnoho ma Anau i te kaamata roo. 
\c 16  
\p  
\v 1 “Anau ku oti te tattara atu na mee nei, ki se lavaa kootou te tiaki na hakattina kootou raa.  
\v 2 Kootou e me ki hakattuu ria i taha ma na hare lotu, tena e isi te saaita koi hamai tera na tama e me ki taa kootou no mmate raa e me ki mannatu ma laatou e ppena hea TeAtua e hihai.  
\v 3 Na tama e me ki ppena na mee nei i kootou, maitaname laatou se illoa Anau ia ma te Tamana Anau raa.  
\v 4 Emeia Anau ku oti te tattara atu kootou, maitaname e isi te saaita e me ki tae atu, tena kootou e me ki kkite na tama raa e ppena na mee nei, tena kootou e me ki mannatu hea Anau ni tattara atu kootou raa. 
\s1 Na uata TeAnana Tapu 
\p “Anau ni se tattara atu na mee nei i te kaamata roo e mee Anau e nnoho ma kootou.  
\v 5 Emeia te saaita nei, Anau e me ki vaakai i te Tama tera ni kauna ria mai Anau raa, e meia se hai tama kootou e vahiri mai Anau ma Anau e me ki haere i hee.  
\v 6 Emeia teenei Anau ku oti te tattara atu kootou nei, tena kootou e me ki alloha roo i roto kootou.  
\v 7 Emeia Anau e tattara atu te hakamaoni: e me ki tauareka ma kootou kame Anau e haere i taha, maitaname kame Anau se haere i taha, te Tokonaki raa se lavaa te hamai. Emeia kame Anau e haere i taha, tena Anau e me ki kauna ria mai te Tokonaki raa ki hamai no nnoho ma kootou.  
\v 8 Tena te saaita Aia e hamai raa, Aia e me ki huri ake na tama hakaatoa te maarama nei raa te hakamaoni pera ma laatou e ssara i te vahi na hai ssara ia ma hea e tonu ia ma te hakatonutonu TeAtua i na tama raa.  
\v 9 Na tama raa e ssara i te vahi na hai sara, maitaname na tama raa se hakattina i Anau;  
\v 10 na tama raa e ssara i te vahi na mee e ttonu, maitaname Anau e me ki vaakai i te Tamana Anau raa, tena kootou se lavaa hoki te kkite Anau;  
\v 11 tena na hakataakoto na tama raa e ssara i te vahi na tama TeAtua e me ki hakatonutonu raa, maitaname TeAtua ku oti te hakatonutonu te tama hakamaatua i te maarama nei raa. \f + \fr 16.11 \ft te tama hakamaatua i te maarama nei raa ko Satan\f* 
\p  
\v 12 “Anau e isi tammaki roo na mee ki tattara atu kootou, e meia na mee nei e me ki tammaki roo ma kootou te amo te saaita nei.  
\v 13 Tena te saaita TeAnana Tapu raa e hamai raa, Aia e me ki huri atu te hakamaoni TeAtua, tena Aia e me ki hakattaki kootou ki illoa te hakamaoni na mee roo hakaatoa. Tama raa se lavaa te tattara i na mahi Aia Hokoia, e meia Tama raa e me ki tattara atu kootou hea Aia e rono raa, tena Aia e me ki tattara atu kootou na mee tera e me ki oo mai i muri raa.  
\v 14 Tama raa e me ki huri atu kootou na mahi hai mmahi Anau, maitaname Aia e me ki too hea Anau ni tattara ake Aia raa no tattara atu kootou.  
\v 15 Na mee hakaatoa te Tamana Anau raa e isi raa ni mee Anau; tera hea Anau e tattara atu pera ma TeAnana Tapu raa e me ki too hea Anau e tattara ake Aia ki tattara atu kootou raa. 
\s1 Te alloha ia ma te hihhia 
\p  
\v 16 “Se roroa kootou e me ki se lavaa te kkite Anau, tena se roroa hoki kootou e me ki kkite Anau.” 
\p  
\v 17 Tena e isi na disaipol ku vahihhiri hokolaatou ma, “Te hakataakoto te tattara nei raa e mee maea? Tama raa e tattara mai taatou ma se roroa taatou e me ki se kkite Aia, tena se roroa hoki taatou e me ki kkite Aia, tena Aia e tattara hoki ma, ‘Na mee nei e mee raa e mee Anau e me ki haere te Tamana Anau raa.’  
\v 18 Te tattara ma ‘se roroa raa’ e mee maea? Taatou se illoa hea Tama raa e tattara mai taatou raa.” 
\p  
\v 19 Jisas e iroa ma na disaipol raa e mee ma ki vahiri ake Aia, kito Aia ki meake na tama raa, “Anau e meatu kootou, ‘Se roroa kootou e me ki se kkite Anau, tena se roroa hoki kootou e me ki kkite Anau.’ Teenei hea kootou e vahihhiri hokkootou?  
\v 20 Anau e tattara atu te hakamaoni: kootou e me ki alloha no tanittani hakamaroa roo, e meia na tama te maarama nei raa e me ki hihhia; kootou e me ki alloha, e meia ki oti na alloha naa ku huri no hihhia.  
\v 21 Te hine ku taapiri ki mamaoha raa e me ki aroha aia hokoia, maitaname te saaita te hakalono llihu aia raa ku tae ake; e meia te saaita te tamariki raa e hopo raa, te hine raa e me ki ssiri na hakalono llihu aia raa hakaatoa, maitaname aia ku hihia e mee te tamariki raa ku haanau iho i te maarama nei.  
\v 22 Teenei hea e nnoho ma kootou te aho nei: kootou e me ki alloha, e meia Anau e me ki kite kootou hakaraoi, tena kootou e me ki hihhia roo i roto na hatu manava kootou, teenei ko te hihia tera se hai tama e lavaa te ui i taha ma kootou. 
\p  
\v 23 “Te saaita te aho naa e tae mai raa, kootou e me ki se lavaa te kainno mai Anau ni mee peehee. Anau e tattara atu te hakamaoni: Te Tamana e me ki kou atu niaa kootou e kainno ake Aia i te inoa Anau.  
\v 24 I mua, kootou se hai tama e kainno ake TeAtua i te inoa Anau niaa kootou e hihhai, ia kainno tena kootou e me ki too ki lavaa kootou te too te hihia hakamaoni. 
\s1 Na mahi Jisas e raka i aruna na mahi te maarama nei 
\p  
\v 25 “Anau e tattara atu kootou na mee nei i na tattara hurihuri. Emeia e isi te saaita e me ki tae mai, tena Anau se lavaa te tattara atu na tattara hurihuri, e meia Anau e me ki tattara hakamatahua atu kootou i te vahi te Tamana.  
\v 26 Te saaita te aho naa e tae mai raa, kootou e me ki kainno ake Tama raa na mee i te inoa Anau, tena Anau se tattara atu ma Anau e me ki kainno ake Tama raa ma kootou,  
\v 27 maitaname te Tamana Hokoia e laoi kootou. Aia e laoi kootou maitaname kootou e laoi Anau, tena ki hakattina pera ma Anau e hamai TeAtua.  
\v 28 Anau e hamai Tamana no tae mai i te maarama nei. Tena vahao nei Anau e me ki tiaki te maarama nei no vaakai muri te Tamana Anau raa.” 
\p  
\v 29 Tena na disaipol Aia raa ki meake Jisas ma, “Te saaita nei Akoe ku tattara hakamatahua mai, tena Akoe ku se tattara na tattara hurihuri.  
\v 30 Te saaita nei maatou ku illoa pera ma Akoe e iroa roo na mee hakaatoa; Akoe e iroa na hakataakoto na tama hakaatoa niaina laatou se vahiri atu Akoe. Te mee nei e mee maatou no hakattina pera ma Akoe e hamai TeAtua.” 
\p  
\v 31 Kito Jisas ki meake na tama raa, “Kootou ku hakattina roo te saaita nei?  
\v 32 E isi te saaita e me ki tae mai, tena te saaita naa ku tae mai, teenaa ko te saaita kootou hakaatoa e me ki maaseu huri no huro na matakaina kootou raa, tena ku tiaki Anau ki noho Hokonnau. Emeia Anau se mee ma Anau e noho Hokonnau, maitaname Tamana e noho i roto Anau.  
\v 33 Anau e tattara te mee nei ki lavaa kootou te nnoho taravare e mee kootou e hukui ma Anau. Na tama te maarama nei raa e me ki mee kootou ki hakalono llihu. Emeia kootou ki se mattaku! Anau ku oti te seu na mahi te maarama nei!” 
\c 17  
\s1 Jisas e lotu ki tokonaki na disaipol Aia 
\p  
\v 1 Jisas e tattara ake na tattara Aia raa no oti, tena Aia ki kkira i te vaelani no lotu ma, “Tamana, te saaita Anau e me ki hakalono llihu raa ku tae mai. Huri ake na mahi hai mmahi te Tamariki Akoe raa, ki lavaa te Tamariki Akoe raa te huri ake na mahi hai mmahi Akoe raa.  
\v 2 Maitaname Akoe e kou mai Anau na mahi ki hakamaatua i aruna na tama roo hakaatoa ma ki lavaa Anau te kou ake te ora e ora tahi raa i na tama Akoe ni kou mai Anau raa.  
\v 3 Tena te hakataakoto te ora e ora tahi raa e mee na tama ki illoa Akoe; TeAtua hokotahi tera e hakamaoni raa, ia ki illoa hoki Jisas Krais, te Tama Akoe ni kauna ria mai raa.  
\v 4 Anau ku oti te huri ake na mahi hai mmahi Akoe raa i te maarama nei; Anau ku oti te ppena na uata hakaatoa Akoe ni kou mai Anau ki ppena raa.  
\v 5 Tamana! Kou mai na mahi hai mmahi Akoe raa vahao nei Akoe koi noho ma Anau, kou mai na mahi e ssau pera ma na mahi Anau ni isi te saaita Anau ni noho ma Akoe i mua te maarama nei ni tipu ake raa. 
\p  
\v 6 “Anau e tattara ake na tama Akoe ni kou mai i roto te maarama nei raa no illoa mai Akoe. Na tama raa ni tama Akoe, tena Akoe e kou mai na tama raa i Anau. Na tama raa e hakallono roo na tattara Akoe raa,  
\v 7 tena te saaita nei laatou ku illoa pera ma na mee hakaatoa Akoe ni kou mai Anau raa ni mee e oo mai Akoe.  
\v 8 Anau e tattara ake no llono na tama raa na tattara Akoe ni kou mai Anau raa, tena na tama raa ku too na tattara raa; na tama raa e illoa pera ma Anau e hamai Akoe, tena laatou e hakattina hoki pera ma Akoe e kauna ria mai Anau. 
\p  
\v 9 “Anau e lotu ma na tama raa. Anau se lotu ma na tama te maarama nei hakaatoa, e meia Anau e lotu ma na tama koi Akoe ni kou mai Anau raa, maitaname na tama raa ni tama Akoe.  
\v 10 Na mee hakaatoa Anau e isi raa ni mee Akoe, tena na mee hakaatoa Akoe e isi raa ni mee Anau, tena na mee raa e me ki huri ake na mahi Anau.  
\v 11 Tena te saaita nei Anau e me ki vaakai atu Akoe; Anau ku se lavaa hoki te noho i roto te maarama nei, e meia na tama raa e me ki nnoho i te maarama nei. Tamana e Tapu! Rorohi laoi na tama raa i na mahi te inoa Akoe, teenaa ko te inoa Akoe ni kou mai Anau ma ki lavaa na tama raa te nnoho pera ma he kanohenua hokotahi, e ssau pera ma Taaua e hokotahi raa.  
\v 12 Te saaita Anau e nnoho ma na tama raa, Anau e rorohi hakaraoi na tama raa i na mahi te inoa Akoe, teenaa ko te inoa Akoe ni kou mai Anau raa. Anau e rorohi hakappuru na tama raa, tena se hai tama na tama raa ni llano, e meia te tama koi e tau te rano raa e me ki rano, ki mee na tattara te Launiu Tapu raa ki hakamaoni.  
\v 13 Tena te saaita nei, Anau ku haere atu Akoe, tena Anau e tattara na tattara nei i te maarama nei ki lavaa na tama raa te hihhia hakamaoni roo i roto na hatu manava laatou.  
\v 14 Anau e kou ake na tattara Akoe raa no llono na tama raa, tena na tama te maarama nei raa ku se hihhai na tama raa, maitaname na hakataakoto na tama raa se hakanatahi pera ma na hakataakoto na tama te maarama nei raa, e ssau pera ma na hakataakoto Anau raa se hakanatahi ma na hakataakoto na tama te maarama nei raa.  
\v 15 Anau se kainno atu Akoe ki too na tama raa i taha ma te maarama nei, e meia Anau e kainno atu Akoe ki rorohi laoi na tama raa i taha ma na mahi Satan.  
\v 16 Na tama raa seai ma ni tama te maarama nei, e ssau pera ma Anau seai ma he tama te maarama nei.  
\v 17 Na tattara Akoe raa e hakamaoni, tena Akoe ku hakatapu na ora na tama raa i na mahi na tattara hakamaoni Akoe raa.  
\v 18 Anau e kauna na tama raa ki oo vaa roto te maarama nei, e ssau pera ma Akoe ni kauna ria mai Anau ki hamai i te maarama nei raa.  
\v 19 Tena ku tokonaki na tama raa. Anau e hoki atu te ora Anau raa ki hehekau ma Akoe, ki lavaa na tama raa te hoki atu hoki na ora laatou raa ki hehekau ma Akoe. 
\p  
\v 20 “Anau se lotu atu ma ki tokonaki koi na tama nei, e meia ki tokonaki hoki na tama tera e hakattina Anau i na tattara laatou raa.  
\v 21 Anau e lotu ma na tama raa ki nnoho pera ma he kanohenua hokotahi. Tamana! Tokonaki na tama raa ki nnoho i roto Taaua, ki lavaa na tama te maarama nei raa te hakattina pera ma Akoe e kauna ria mai Anau.  
\v 22 Anau e kou ake na tama raa na mahi pera ma na mahi Akoe ni kou mai Anau raa, ia ki lavaa hoki na tama raa te hukui no hokotahi, e ssau pera ma Taaua e hokotahi raa:  
\v 23 Anau e noho i roto na tama raa, tena Akoe e noho i roto Anau ki tokonaki na tama raa ki hukui hakamaoni no hokotahi, ia ki lavaa na tama te maarama nei raa te illoa pera ma Akoe e kauna ria mai Anau, tena ki illoa hoki pera ma Akoe e laoi laatou pera ma Akoe e laoi Anau raa. 
\p  
\v 24 “Tamana! Akoe e kou mai na tama raa i Anau, tena Anau e hihai ma na tama raa ki nnoho i te kina Anau e noho raa ki lavaa na tama raa te kkite na mahi hai mmahi Anau raa, teenaa ko na mahi hai mmahi Akoe ni kou mai Anau raa, maitaname Akoe e laoi Anau i mua te maarama nei ni tipu ake. 
\p  
\v 25 “Tamana e Tonu tahi! Na tama te maarama nei raa se illoa Akoe, e meia Anau e iroa Akoe, tena na tama Akoe e kou mai Anau raa e illoa ma Akoe e kauna ria mai Anau.  
\v 26 Anau e tattara ake na tama raa no illoa Akoe, tena Anau e me ki tauhano te ppena peenei, ki lavaa te laoi Akoe Anau raa te moe i roto na tama raa, tena Anau hoki ki noho i roto na tama raa.” 
\c 18  
\s1 Jisas ku hakapiki ria 
\r (Matiu 26.47–56; Mak 14.43–50; Luk 22.47–53) 
\p  
\v 1 Te saaita Jisas ni lotu no oti, Aia ku haere ma na disaipol Aia raa i teeraa vahi te Riva Kidron. Tena e isi te paupaku e hhomo na oliv e tuu i te kina raa, tena Jisas ma na disaipol Aia raa ki oo i roto te paupaku raa. 
\p  
\v 2 Judas, te tama e me ki hakari ake Jisas raa e iroa te paupaku raa, maitaname Jisas e kkutu tammaki na vahao ma na disaipol Aia raa i te kina raa.  
\v 3 Kito Judas ki haere ake ma na soldia i Rom raa hakapaa ma na soldia e lollohi te Hare Tapu tera na maatua hakananniu ia ma na Farisi raa ni kauna ria ki oo ake raa, tena na tama raa e oo ake ma na haana laatou raa, na lamu ia ma na laiti.  
\v 4 Jisas e iroa na mee roo hakaatoa tera e me ki kapihi ake Aia te poo naa, tena Jisas ki haere atu no vahiri ake na tama raa, “Koai te tama kootou e sesee naa?” 
\p  
\v 5 Kito na tama raa ki meake, “Jisas te tama i Nasaret raa.” 
\p Tena Jisas ki meake, “Teenei Anau nei.” 
\p Judas te tama sakkino raa e tuu i te kina raa ma na soldia raa.  
\v 6 Te saaita Jisas ni meake ma, “Teenei Anau nei,” na tama raa ku horo muri no hhina i raro.  
\v 7 Tena Jisas ki vahiri ake hakaraoi hoki ma, “Koai te tama kootou e sesee naa?” 
\p Kito na tama raa ki meake, “Jisas te tama i Nasaret raa.” 
\p  
\v 8 Tena Jisas ki meake, “Anau ku oti te meatu pera ma teenei Anau nei. Tena kame kootou e sesee koi Anau, kootou ku tiaki na tama nei ki oo.”  
\v 9 (Jisas e tattara ake peenei ma ki mee na tattara Aia ni tattara ake i mua raa ki hakamaoni: “Tamana, se hai tama na tama Akoe ni kou mai Anau raa e me ki llano.”) 
\p  
\v 10 Tena Saimon Pita, te tama e isi te paraamoa raa ku uhu te paraamoa raa no ttuu te katarina te vahi laaua te tama hehekau te pohouru hakanaaniu na maatua raa no hopo. Te inoa te tama hehekau raa ko Malkus.  
\v 11 Kito Jisas ki meake Pita, “Tuku te paraamoa naa i te kina Akoe ni too raa! Akoe e maanatu ma Anau ki se lavaa te unu te kapu na hakalono llihu te Tamana raa ni kou mai Anau?” 
\s1 Jisas e tuu i mua Anas 
\p  
\v 12 Tena na soldia i Rom raa hakapaa ma te soldia hakamaatua ia ma soldia na Jiu raa ku hakapiki Jisas no haihai,  
\v 13 tena ki too Tama raa no kkave ia Anas raa i mua. Anas ko te hinaona tanata Kaiafas, te pohouru hakanaaniu na maatua te hetau naa.  
\v 14 Teeraa ko Kaiafas ni tattara ake na tama hakamattua na Jiu raa ma e tauareka te tama hokotahi ki mate ma na tama hakaatoa raa. 
\s1 Pita e kore ma aia se iroa Jisas 
\r (Matiu 26.69–70; Mak 14.66–68; Luk 22.55–57) 
\p  
\v 15 Saimon Pita laaua ma teeraa disaipol ku tauttari Jisas. Te pohouru hakanaaniu na maatua raa e iroa laoi roo teraa disaipol, kito te disaipol raa ki haere i hare ma Jisas i te kina te hare te pohouru hakanaaniu na maatua raa,  
\v 16 e meia Pita e hakattari mai i aho. Tena teeraa disaipol ki vaakai i aho no tattara ake te taukupu e tuu te totoka raa, tena aia ki too Pita no kkave i hare.  
\v 17 Kito te taukupu e tuu te totoka raa ki meake Pita, “Akoe hoki he disaipol te Tama raa kaa seai?” 
\p Tena Pita ki meake, “Seai, anau seai.” 
\p  
\v 18 Te poo naa e haumallii, tena na tama hehekau raa e hakaura te ahi, tena ki ttuu alleha te ahi raa no hakamamahana. Kito Pita ki haere atu no ttuu ma na tama raa no hakamamahana hoki. 
\s1 Te pohouru hakanaaniu na maatua raa ku lahulahu Jisas 
\r (Matiu 26.59–66; Mak 14.55–64; Luk 22.66–71) 
\p  
\v 19 Te pohouru hakanaaniu na maatua raa ku vahiri ake Jisas i te vahi na disaipol ia ma na akoako Aia raa.  
\v 20 Tena Jisas ki meake, “Anau na vahao tahi e tuu i mua na tama hakaatoa no tattara; Anau e mee na akoako Anau raa i roto na hare lotu na Jiu ia ma te Hare Tapu, tena i na kina na tama hakaatoa e kkutu tahi raa. Anau se hai vahao e tattara hemuu na tattara Anau raa.  
\v 21 Aiea, kaa kootou e vahiri mai Anau naea? Vahiri atu na tama tera e llono na tattara Anau raa. Vahiri ake na tama raa ma ni tattara peehee Anau e tattara raa, maitaname na tama raa e illoa hea Anau e tattara ake laatou raa.” 
\p  
\v 22 Te saaita Jisas ni meake peenei raa, tena he soldia hokotahi ku ppaa na patikauvae Tama raa, tena ki meake, “Akoe e lavaa roo te tattara ake peenaa i te pohouru hakanaaniu na maatua raa?” 
\p  
\v 23 Kito Jisas ki meake, “Kame Anau e isi te tattara sakkino ni ppehi, tena akoe ku meake ki llono na tama nei hakaatoa te tattara naa. Emeia kame na tattara Anau raa e ttonu koi, tena kaa akoe e ppaa Anau naea?” 
\p  
\v 24 Jisas koi haihai ria koi, tena Anas ki kkave Jisas iaa Kaiafas, te pohouru hakanaaniu na maatua raa. 
\s1 Pita ku kore hakaraoi hoki ma aia se iroa Jisas 
\r (Matiu 26.71–75; Mak 14.69–72; Luk 22.58–62) 
\p  
\v 25 Pita koi tuu koi i te kina te ahi raa no hakamamahana. Kito alaa tama ki meake, “Akoe seai ma he disaipol hoki te Tama raa?” 
\p Emeia Pita e kore hoki, tena ki meake, “Seai, anau seai.” 
\p  
\v 26 He tama hehekau te pohouru hakanaaniu na maatua raa, ia he tama hoki e lave te tama Pita ni ttuu te katarina no hopo raa ku meake, “Aiea anau se kite akoe ni tuu ma te Tama raa i roto te paupaku?” 
\p  
\v 27 Kito Pita ki kore hakaraoi hoki, tena ki meake, “Seai.” Te saaita naa koi te manu tane raa ku tani. 
\s1 Jisas e tuu i mua Pailat 
\r (Matiu 27.1–2; 27.11–14; Mak 15.1–5; Luk 23.1–5) 
\p  
\v 28 Te tahata roo na soldia raa ku too Jisas i te hare Kaiafas raa no kkave i te hare te tama hakamaatua te taumani i Rom raa. Na tama hakamattua na Jiu raa se oo i hare, maitaname laatou se hihai ma laatou ki isi na hai sara i te vahi na tuaa raa, ma ki lavaa laatou te kkai te Kai te Pasova raa.  
\v 29 Kito Pailat ki haere i aho no vahiri ake na tama raa, “Kootou ki tattara mai hea te Tama nei e ppena e ssara naa.” 
\p  
\v 30 Kito na tama raa ki meake, “Maatou se lavaa te kou mai te Tama nei iaa Akoe kame Aia ni se hai sara e ppena.” 
\p  
\v 31 Tena Pailat ki meake na tama raa, “Tena kootou hokkootou ki too Tama nei no hakatonutonu i te vahi na tuaa kootou raa.” 
\p Kito na tama raa ki vaakai ake ma, “Maatou e tapu te taa te tama ki mate.”  
\v 32 (Na mee nei e kapihi mai ki mee na tattara Jisas raa ki hakamaoni; na tattara Aia ni tattara ake na tama raa i te vahi te mate Aia raa.) 
\p  
\v 33 Kito Pailat ki vaakai i hare no kanna ake Jisas, tena ki vahiri ake Tama raa, “Akoe ko te Tuku na Jiu?” 
\p  
\v 34 Tena Jisas ki vahiri ake ma, “Te vahiri naa he vahiri koi akoe ma e isi na tama e tattara atu akoe i te vahi Anau?” 
\p  
\v 35 Kito Pailat ki meake, “Akoe e maanatu ma anau he Jiu? Teenaa ko na tama roo kootou naa ia ma na maatua hakananniu raa e kou mai Akoe i anau. Hea Akoe ni ppena?” 
\p  
\v 36 Tena Jisas ki meake, “Te Hakamaatua ana Anau raa se tuu i te maarama nei; ia peeraa te Hakamaatua ana Anau raa ki tuu i te maarama nei, peera na tama tauttari Anau raa e me ki ppuhu ki se lavaa kootou te too Anau no kkave i na tama hakamattua na Jiu raa. Te Hakamaatua ana Anau raa se tuu i te maarama nei.” 
\p  
\v 37 Kito Pailat ki vahiri ake Jisas, “Tena, kaa Akoe he tuku?” 
\p Kito Jisas ki meake, “Akoe e vahiri mai ma Anau he tuku. Anau e haanau mai i roto te maarama nei ma te hakataakoto hokotahi nei; ki tattara i te vahi te hakamaoni raa. Na tama e tauttari te hakamaoni raa e me ki hakallono Anau.” 
\p  
\v 38 Kito Pailat ki meake, “Kaa te hakamaoni raa hea?” 
\s1 Jisas ku mee ki taia ria ki mate 
\r (Matiu 27.15–31; Mak 15.6–20; Luk 23.13–25) 
\p Kito Pailat ki vaakai hakaraoi i aho no meake te kanohenua raa, “Anau se isi te mee e sara e lave ma ki taa Tama nei ki mate.  
\v 39 Emeia i te vahi na tuaa tera kootou e isi raa, na vahao na Kai na Pasova hakaatoa, anau e me ki hakattana he tama karapusi hokotahi ma kootou. Kootou e hihhai ma anau ki hakattana ma kootou te Tuku na Jiu raa?” 
\p  
\v 40 Kito te kanohenua raa ki vaa ake ma, “Seai, seai ma ko Tama naa! Maatou e hihhai Barabas!” (Barabas he tama taa tama.) 
\c 19  
\p  
\v 1 Tena Pailat ki kou ake Jisas i na soldia raa ki riki.  
\v 2 Na soldia raa e pena te hau i na laakau e tutuia raa, tena ki hakatau ake i aruna te pohouru Tama raa, tena na tama raa ki hakauru ake Jisas te kaukahu e ttea pouri raa,\fig |alt="Jesus with crown of thorns" src="LB00321B.TIF" size="col" ref="19.2" \fig* 
\v 3 tena laatou ki oo ake no meake Tama raa ma, “Hakammaha te Tuku na Jiu!” Tena na tama raa ki oo ake no ppaa na maihu Tama raa. 
\p  
\v 4 Kito Pailat ki vaakai ake hakaraoi i aho no meake te kanohenua raa, “Kira ake, anau e me ki kou mai Tama raa i aho ki kkite kootou pera ma anau se isi te mee e sara e lave ki taa Tama raa ki mate.”  
\v 5 Kito Jisas ki hamai i aho, tena Aia ku hau te hau manamana, tena ki uru hoki te kaukahu e ttea pouri. Kito Pailat ki meake na tama raa, “Kira ake! Teenei te Tama nei!” 
\p  
\v 6 Te saaita na maatua hakananniu raa laatou ma na soldia e lollohi te Hare Tapu raa ni kkite Jisas, na tama raa ku vaa ake ma, “Tii Tama naa i aruna te kros! Tii Tama naa i aruna te kros!” 
\p Kito Pailat ki meake te kanohenua raa, “Kame peenaa; kootou hokkootou ku too Tama nei no ttii i aruna te kros. Anau se lave hea Tama nei e ppena e sara.” 
\p  
\v 7 Tena te kanohenua raa ki meake hakaraoi, “Maatou e isi te tuaa tera e mee ma te Tama nei e tau te mate, maitaname Aia e tattara ma Aia he Tamariki TeAtua.” 
\p  
\v 8 Te saaita Pailat ni rono na tattara nei, Aia ku mataku roo.  
\v 9 Tena aia ki vaakai i hare no vahiri ake Jisas, “Akoe he tama e hamai i hee?” 
\p Emeia Jisas e tuu hemuu koi se tattara.  
\v 10 Kito Pailat ki meake Aia, “Akoe se hihai ki tattara mai Anau? Maanatu, anau e isi na mahi ki hakattana Akoe ki haere ia ma ki ttii Akoe i aruna te kros.” 
\p  
\v 11 Tena Jisas ki meake, “Akoe e isi koi na mahi i aruna Anau e mee TeAtua e kou atu na mahi naa i akoe. Emeia te tama e kou atu Anau i na rima kootou raa e ppena te mee e haeo roo.” 
\p  
\v 12 Te saaita Pailat ni rono na tattara nei, aia ku sesee he ara ma ki hakattana Tama raa ki haere. Emeia te kanohenua raa e vaa ake ma, “Kame akoe e hakattana Tama naa ki haere, tena akoe e huri mai pera ma akoe seai ma he soa te tuku i Rom raa! Te tama e tattara ma aia he tuku raa e hakataukaa ma te tuku i Rom!” 
\p  
\v 13 Te saaita Pailat ni rono na tattara nei, aia ku too Jisas no kkave i aho no hakanoho i aruna te tuai e hakatonutonu na tama tera e kanna ma, “Te Papa Hatu raa”. (Na Hibru raa e kanna te kina nei ma “Gabata”.)  
\v 14 Te mee raa ku taapiri ki tae te laa latea te aho naa, te aho i mua te aho te Kai te Pasova raa. Tena Pailat ki meake te kanohenua raa, “Teenei te Tuku kootou!” 
\p  
\v 15 Tena na tama raa ki vaa ake ma, “Taa Tama naa ki mate! Taa Tama naa ki mate! Ttii Tama naa i aruna te kros!” 
\p Kito Pailat ki meake te kanohenua raa, “Kootou e hihhai ma anau ki ttii te Tuku kootou raa i aruna te kros?” 
\p Tena na maatua hakananniu raa ki meake, “Te tuku hokotahi koi maatou e isi raa ko te tuku i Rom!” 
\p  
\v 16 Tena Pailat ki too Jisas no kou ake na tama raa ki tii i aruna te kros. 
\s1 Jisas ku ttii ria i aruna te korosi 
\r (Matiu 27.32–44; Mak 15.21–32; Luk 23.26–43) 
\p Kito na tama raa ki hakattaki Jisas.  
\v 17 Jisas e amo te kros Aia raa no haere no tae i te kina e hui ma, “Te Kina te Ivi te Pohouru.” (Na Hibru raa e kanna te kina raa ma, “Golgota”.)  
\v 18 Na soldia raa e ttii Jisas i te kina raa, tena na tama raa ki ttii hoki tokorua na tama kailallao raa i na vahi, tena te kros Jisas e tuu lottonu na kros tokorua raa. 
\p  
\v 19 Pailat e taataa na tattara nei i aruna te hono, tena ki ttii te hono raa i aruna te kros. Teenei na tattara Pailat e taataa, “Jisas te Tama i Nasaret, te Tuku na Jiu.”  
\v 20 Tammaki na tama e ppau na tattara raa, maitaname te kina na tama raa e ttii Jisas raa se mmao ma te matakaina e rahi raa. Na tattara nei e tattaa i na tattara Hibru, Latin ia ma Grik.  
\v 21 Tena na maatua hakananniu raa ki meake Pailat, “Auu se taataa ma ‘Te Tuku na Jiu’, e meia taataa pera ma, ‘Te Tama nei e tattara ma, Anau ko te Tuku na Jiu.’ ” 
\p  
\v 22 Kito Pailat ki meake, “Hea anau e taataa tiaki ki mmau peenaa.” 
\p  
\v 23 Na soldia raa e ttii roo Jisas no oti, tena laatou ki too na hekau Tama raa no vvae e haa na tuhana ki tau ma laatou tokohaa, te soldia hokotahi e too te tuhana aia. Na soldia raa e too hoki te kaukahu roroa tera e ttui koi te paamaro hokotahi, se hai kina e huhukui raa.  
\v 24 Na soldia raa e tattara hokolaatou ma, “Taatou se lavaa te saesae te kaukahu nei, taatou ki ttahao huhu na hatu ki mmata ma koai e me ki too te kaukahu nei.” Te mee nei e kapihi mai ki mee na tattara te Launiu Tapu raa ki hakamaoni: 
\q1 “Na tama raa e vaevae na hekau Anau raa ma laatou, 
\q1 tena ki ttahao huhu na hatu ki too te kaukahu roroa Anau raa.” 
\m Teenei hea na soldia raa e ppena. 
\p  
\v 25 Te tinna Jisas raa, te taina te tinna Aia raa, Meri te avana Klopas raa, tena Meri te tama i Makdala raa e ttuu taapiri ake te kros Jisas raa.  
\v 26 Jisas e kite te tinna Aia raa laaua ma te disaipol Aia e hihhai mahi raa e ttuu i te kina raa, tena Aia ki meake te tinna Aia raa ma, “Teenei he tama Akoe.” 
\p  
\v 27 Tena Aia ki meake te disaipol raa, “Teenei he tinna akoe.” Tena kaamata te saaita naa te disaipol raa ku too Meri no nnoho laaua i te hare Aia raa. 
\s1 Te mate Jisas 
\r (Matiu 27.45–56; Mak 15.33–41; Luk 23.44–49) 
\p  
\v 28 Jisas e iroa pera ma te saaita nei na mee roo hakaatoa ku oti, tena ki mee hea e mmau i roto te Launiu Tapu raa ki hakamaoni, tena Aia ki meake ma, “Anau hiunu.” 
\p  
\v 29 E isi te kumete e tuu i te kina raa e pii roo na wain e mmara; na soldia raa e too te spans raa no ttoki i roto te wain raa, tena ki haihai te spans raa i te mata te laakau te hisop raa, tena ki ssau ake no tuku ake na maihu Tama raa.  
\v 30 Jisas e mmiti te wain raa no pakupaku, tena ki meake, “Ku oti hakaatoa!” 
\p Tena Aia ki huru te pohouru Aia raa no mate. 
\s1 Te vahi manava Jisas raa ku vvana ria 
\p  
\v 31 Tena na tama hakamattua na Jiu raa ki meake Pailat ki hakattana laatou ki oo no kkoti na vae na tama e tottoo i aruna na kros raa, tena ku turi iho na tinotama raa i taha ma na kros raa. Na tama hakamattua raa e meake e mee teeraa he aho rima, tena laatou se hihhai ma na tinotama raa ki tottoo te aho te Sabat raa, e mee te Sabat raa he aho e tapu.  
\v 32 Kito na soldia raa ki oo no kkoti na vae te tama kaamata raa, tena ki oo no kkoti na vae teeraa tama hoki tera ni ttii ria i teeraa vahi Jisas raa.  
\v 33 Emeia te saaita laatou ni oo atu iaa Jisas raa, na soldia ku kkite pera ma Jisas ko na mate roo, tena laatou ni se kkoti na vae Tama raa.  
\v 34 Tena he soldia hokotahi e taro te hika aia raa i te vahi manava Jisas, tena te saaita naa koi na toto ia ma na vai raa ku kkoo iho i taha ma te vahi manava Tama raa.  
\v 35 (Te tama ni kite te mee nei raa ku haere tattara roo te mee nei ma ki lavaa kootou te hakattina. Hea te tama raa e tattara raa e hakamaoni, tena aia hoki e iroa pera ma aia e tattara te hakamaoni.)  
\v 36 Te mee nei e kapihi mai ki mee na tattara i roto te Launiu Tapu raa ki hakamaoni: 
\q1 “Se isi na ivi Tama raa e me ki kottia ria.” 
\m  
\v 37 Tena e isi teeraa kina hoki e mmau i roto te Launiu Tapu e mee ma, 
\q1 “Te kanohenua raa e me ki kkira ake te Tama laatou ni ttoki raa.” 
\s1 Josep ku too te tinotama Jisas 
\r (Matiu 27.57–61; Mak 15.42–47; Luk 23.50–56) 
\p  
\v 38 Tena ki oti, Josep te tama te matakaina Arimatea raa ku haere no meake Pailat ma aia e lavaa te too te tinotama Jisas raa. (Josep he tama e tautari hemuu na tiputipu Jisas, maitaname aia e mataku na tama hakamattua na Jiu raa.) Tena Pailat ki meake tama raa ki too te tinotama Jisas raa, tena Josep ki haere no ssau te tinotama Jisas raa i taha ma te kina raa.  
\v 39 Nikodimas, te tama ni haere kaamata no mmata Jisas i te poo raa e oo laaua ma Josep, tena aia e too na sanda e hilo ma na rehu mannoni e taapa ma ni aloo raa no haere ma aia; te mmaha na mee raa e tae tipu toru na kilo.  
\v 40 Tokorua na taanata raa e too te tinotama Jisas raa no amuhi na lloo e hilo ma na rehu manoni raa, tena ki mmini te tinotama Jisas raa ma na paamaro. Teenei he tiputipu na Jiu raa te saaita laatou e tanattana ki tanu te tama.  
\v 41 E isi te paupaku e tuu i te kina Jisas ni taia ria no mate raa, ia e isi hoki te taruma e tuu i roto te paupaku raa tera se hai tama ni tanu i roto i mua.  
\v 42 Maitaname teenaa ko te aho i mua te Sabat, ia e mee te taruma raa e taapiri hoki, tena tokorua raa ki oo no ppono te tinotama Jisas raa i roto te taruma raa\f + \fr 19.42 \ft te taruma nei e keri te vahi te mouna hua\f*. 
\c 20  
\s1 Jisas ku ora muri 
\r (Matiu 28.1–8; Mak 16.1–8; Luk 24.1–12) 
\p  
\v 1 Tahata roo te aho te latapu, te saaita te mee raa koi maru pouri, tena Meri te tama te matakaina Makdala raa ku haere i te taruma raa no kite pera ma te hatu ni ppui te taruma raa ku oti te hakatupe ria i taha ma te totoka te taruma raa\f + \fr 20.1 \ft na henua raa e kkeri na taruma laatou raa i na kina e hatu e mmotu hua\f*.  
\v 2 Tena te hine raa ki tere no mmata Saimon Pita laaua ma te disaipol tera Jisas e hihai mahi raa, tena aia ki tattara ake tokorua raa ma, “Na tama raa ku oti te too te tinotama TeAriki raa i taha ma te taruma raa, tena maatou ku se illoa i te kina na tama raa e tuku te tinotama Tama raa!” 
\p  
\v 3 Kito Pita laaua ma teeraa disaipol ki oo i te taruma raa.  
\v 4 Tokorua raa e hai ma te huro, e meia teeraa disaipol e nahoro roo i aruna Pita, tena aia e tae kaamata i te taruma.  
\v 5 Tama raa se uru i roto te taruma raa hoki, e meia aia e haatiu koi no kite na paamaro ni mmini Jisas raa.  
\v 6 Tena Saimon Pita e tere mai i muri no haere tahi roo no uru i roto te taruma raa. Pita e kite na paamaro ni mmini Jisas raa e mmoe i te kina raa,  
\v 7 ia te paamaro hoki na tama raa ni uhi te pohouru Jisas raa. Te paamaro raa se mmoe hakapaa ma na paamaro ni mmini te tinotama raa, e meia te paamaro raa e minimini no moe te kina aia hokoia.  
\v 8 Tena teeraa disaipol, te tama ni tae kaamata i te taruma raa ku uru atu i roto te taruma raa no kite te mmoe na mee raa, tena ki hakatina.  
\v 9 (Emeia tokorua raa se illoa hakaraoi na tattara e mmau i roto te Launiu Tapu tera e mee ma te Tama raa e me ki ora muri i taha ma te mate raa.)  
\v 10 Tena tokorua na disaipol raa ki vakkai i hare. 
\s1 Jisas ku tuu ake iaa Meri te hine i Makdala 
\r (Matiu 28.9–10; Mak 16.9–11) 
\p  
\v 11 Meri e haere no tuu no tanitani i aho te taruma raa. Aia koi tanitani koi, tena aia ku huru atu no kkira i roto te taruma raa  
\v 12 no kite e rua na ensel e uru na hekau makkini, tokorua raa e nnoho i te kina te tinotama Jisas raa ni moe. Tokorua e noho, te tama i te kina te pohouru, tena teeraa tama e noho i te kina na vae raa.  
\v 13 Kito tokorua raa ki vahiri ake, “Akoe e tanitani naea?” 
\p Tena Meri ki meake, “Na tama raa e too te tinotama TeAriki anau raa i taha, tena anau ku se iroa i te kina laatou e tuku te tinotama Tama raa!” 
\p  
\v 14 Tena aia ki hakatike no kite Jisas ku tuu i te kina raa; e meia aia se iroa ma teeraa ko Jisas. 
\p  
\v 15 Kito Jisas ki vahiri ake ma, “Akoe e tanitani naea? Akoe e sesee aii?” 
\p Meri e kkahu ma teeraa ko te tama te paupaku raa, kito aia ki meake te Tama raa, “Tama hakanaaniu, kame akoe e too te tinotama Tama raa i taha, tena akoe ku hakari mai anau i te kina akoe e tuku te tinotama Tama raa, ki haere anau no too te tinotama raa.” 
\p  
\v 16 Kito Jisas ki kanna ake te hine raa ma, “Meri!” 
\p Tena Meri ki hakatike no kkira ake Jisas, tena ki meake, “Raboni!” i na tattara hakaHibru. (Te tattara nei e mee ma, “Tisa”.) 
\p  
\v 17 Kito Jisas ki meake Meri, “Auu se ttaohi Anau, maitaname Anau se ki haere i aruna i te Tamana Anau raa. Emeia haere no tattara ake na taina\f + \fr 20.17 \ft na tama Jisas e tattara ma ko na taina Aia raa ko na disaipol Aia\f* Anau raa pera ma Anau e me ki vaakai i TeAtua te Tamana Anau ia ma te Tamana laatou raa, ia TeAtua Anau ia ma TeAtua laatou raa.” 
\p  
\v 18 Kito Meri ki haere no tattara ake na disaipol raa pera ma aia e kite TeAriki, tena aia ki tattara ake na disaipol raa na tattara Jisas ni tattara ake aia raa. 
\s1 Jisas e tuu ake i na disaipol Aia 
\r (Matiu 28.16–20; Mak 16.14–18; Luk 24.36–49) 
\p  
\v 19 Te mee raa ku hiahi roo te aho te latapu, tena na disaipol raa ku hakkutu i hare, tena ki pupui na totoka raa no hakapikapi, maitaname laatou e mattaku na tama hakamattua na Jiu raa. Tena Jisas ki haere ake no tuu i te kina na tama raa e kkutu raa no meake, “Te noho laoi ki nnoho ma kootou!”  
\v 20 Jisas e tattara ake no oti, tena Aia ki huri ake na rima ia ma te vahi manava Aia raa. Na disaipol raa ku hihhia roo e mee laatou ku kkite TeAriki.  
\v 21 Kito Jisas ki meake hakaraoi hoki ma, “Te noho laoi ki nnoho ma kootou. E ssau pera ma te Tamana e kauna ria mai Anau, tena Anau e me ki kauna hoki kootou.”  
\v 22 Tena Jisas ki iri ake na tama raa, tena ki meake, “Too TeAnana Tapu.  
\v 23 Kame kootou e ssirihia na hai sara na tama, tena na hai sara na tama naa e me ki ssirihia; kame kootou se ssirihia na hai sara na tama naa, tena na hai sara na tama naa se lavaa te ssirihia.” 
\s1 Tomas ku kite Jisas 
\p  
\v 24 Tomas he disaipol i roto te sanahuru ma rua na disaipol raa (na tama e kakanna hoki aia ma te Kokoa raa), e seai i te kina raa te saaita Jisas ni haere ake.  
\v 25 Tena alaa disaipol ku tattara ake Tomas ma, “Maatou e kkite TeAriki!” 
\p Kito Tomas ki meake na tama raa, “Anau e me ki hakatina koi kame anau e kite na kina na katana raa ni uru na rima Aia raa, tena ku taaro te matarima anau nei i roto na kina na katana raa ni uru raa, tena ku taaro hoki te rima anau nei i roto te vahi manava Aia raa.” 
\p  
\v 26 He latapu hakaatoa e haere no raka, tena na disaipol raa ku kkutu hakaraoi i hare, tena Tomas ku nnoho ma laatou te saaita naa. Na totoka raa e puipui hakammate roo, e meia Jisas e haere ake koi i hare no ttuu ma na tama raa, tena ki meake, “Te noho laoi ki nnoho ma kootou.”  
\v 27 Tena kito Jisas ki meake Tomas, “Taaro te mata rima akoe raa i te kina nei, tena akoe ku kkira mai na rima Anau nei, tena haaro mai hoki te rima akoe raa no ppono i roto te vahi manava Anau nei. Hakaoti te mamaanatu tammaki, tena ku hakatina!” 
\p  
\v 28 Kito Tomas ki meake Jisas, “TeAriki ia ma TeAtua anau!” 
\p  
\v 29 Tena Jisas ki meake Tomas, “Akoe ku hakatina e mee akoe ku kite Anau? Na tama se kkite Anau no hakattina raa e me ki hakatapu ria!” 
\s1 Te hakataakoto tera e mee Jon ki taataa te launiu nei 
\p  
\v 30 Jisas e ppena tammaki alaa mirakol hoki i mua na karemata na disaipol raa tera se tattaa i roto te launiu nei.  
\v 31 Emeia na mee nei e tattaa i roto te launiu nei ki lavaa kootou te hakattina pera ma Jisas ko te Mesaia, te Tamariki TeAtua raa, tena na hakattina kootou Tama raa e me ki mee kootou ki too te ora hakamaoni. 
\c 21  
\s1 Jisas e tuu ake tokohitu na disaipol 
\p  
\v 1 Tena ki oti, Jisas ku tuu ake hoki i na disaipol Aia raa i te kina te Namo Galili raa. Te mee nei e kapihi ake peenei. 
\p  
\v 2 Saimon Pita, Tomas (te Kokoa raa), Nataniel, (te tama i Kana i roto Galili raa), tena tokorua na tama Sebedi raa ia ma alaa tokorua hoki na disaipol Jisas raa e kkutu hakaatoa.  
\v 3 Tena Saimon Pita ki meake alaa disaipol ma, “Anau e me ki haere no pupui.” 
\p Kito na disaipol raa ki meake ma, “Maatou e me ki oo taatou.” Tena na tama raa ki too te manaui raa no aro, e meia te poo naa hakaatoa na tama raa se isi na ika e mmau.  
\v 4 Te saaita te laa raa ku hopo ake, Jisas ku tuu i te taunatai, e meia na disaipol raa se illoa ma teeraa ko Jisas.  
\v 5 Kito Jisas ki vahiri ake na tama raa, “Eaa, kootou se isi na ika e mmau?” 
\p Tena na disaipol raa ki meake, “Seai roo hokotahi.” 
\p  
\v 6 Kito Jisas ki meake na tama raa, “Ppehi te kupena naa i te vahi laaua te manaui naa, tena kootou e me ki mmau na ika.” Kito na tama raa ki lletu te kupena raa, tena laatou ku se lavaa te hhuti ake te kupena raa i aruna, maitaname te kupena raa ku mmau na ika tammaki roo. 
\p  
\v 7 Tena te disaipol tera Jisas e hihai mahi raa ku meake Pita, “Teenaa ko TeAriki!” Ia te saaita koi Pita ni rono ma teeraa ko TeAriki raa, tena aia ku rii te kaukahu aia raa areha te tinotama aia raa (e mee aia ni ui na kaukahu aia raa), tena aia ki llee no kkau i uta.  
\v 8 Alaa disaipol ku aro ake te manaui raa i uta no hhuti te kupena ku pii roo na ika raa. Na tama raa se mmao roo i taha ma te taunatai, kame peeraa huitarau na mita te mmao laatou.  
\v 9 Te saaita na disaipol raa ni ttae i uta, na tama raa ku kkite te ahi e malla ma na ika e mmoe i roto te ahi raa ia ma na haraoa hoki. 
\p  
\v 10 Tena Jisas ki meake na disaipol raa, “Kou mai ni ika na ika kootou e mmau te kupena raa.” 
\p  
\v 11 Kito Saimon Pita ki haere atu no kake i roto te manaui raa no horoo ake te kupena raa i uta; te kupena raa e pii roo na ika e llahi; na ika raa hakaatoa e tae huitarau tipu rima ma toru; niaina na ika raa e tammaki roo, e meia te kupena raa se mahaa.  
\v 12 Tena Jisas ki meake na tama raa, “Oo mai no kkai.” Emeia se isi te disaipol e hihai ki vahiri ake Tama raa ma “Akoe koai?” maitaname laatou e illoa ma teeraa ko TeAriki.  
\v 13 Kito Jisas ki haere atu no too na haraoa raa, tena ki vaevae ake na tama raa, tena Aia ki too hoki na ika raa no vaevae ake. 
\p  
\v 14 Teenei ko te hakatoru na vahao Jisas ku tuu ake i na disaipol Aia raa i muri Aia ni mate no ora muri. 
\s1 Jisas e tattara laaua ma Pita 
\p  
\v 15 Te saaita na tama raa ni kkai roo no oti, tena Jisas ki vahiri ake Saimon Pita, “Saimon te tama Jon, te laoi akoe Anau raa e raka i aruna ma na laoi na tama nei i Anau raa ma seai?” 
\p Kito Pita ki meake, “Noo TeAriki, Akoe e iroa pera ma anau e laoi roo Akoe.” 
\p Tena Jisas ki meake Pita, “Rorohi hakaraoi na punua sipsip Anau raa.”  
\v 16 Tena Jisas ki vahiri ake hakaraoi hoki iaa Pita ma, “Saimon te tama Jon, akoe e laoi Anau ma seai?” 
\p Kito Pita ki meake, “Noo, TeAriki, Akoe e iroa pera ma anau e laoi roo Akoe.” 
\p Tena Jisas ki meake Pita, “Rorohi hakaraoi na punua sipsip Anau raa.”  
\v 17 Jisas ku vahiri ake hoki te hakatoru na vahao ma, “Saimon, te tama Jon, akoe e laoi Anau ma seai?” 
\p Pita ku se hihai e mee Jisas e vahiri ake e toru na vahao ma, “Akoe e laoi Anau ma seai?” kito aia ki meake, “TeAriki, Akoe e iroa na mee roo hakaatoa; akoe e iroa pera ma anau e laoi roo Akoe!” 
\p Tena Jisas ki meake, “Rorohi na sipsip Anau raa.  
\v 18 Anau e tattara atu te hakamaoni: te saaita akoe ni paamee raa, akoe e tanattana no haere he kina peehee akoe e hihai ki haere raa; e meia te saaita akoe ku tanata matua raa, akoe e me ki ssora na rima akoe raa, tena teeraa tama e me ki haihai akoe, tena ku too akoe no kkave i te kina akoe se hihai ki haere raa.”  
\v 19 (Jisas e tattara ake peenei ki huri ake te tiputipu te mate Pita tera e me ki huri ake na mahi hai mmahi TeAtua raa.) Tena Jisas ki meake Pita, “Tautari mai Anau!” 
\s1 Jisas ia ma teeraa disaipol 
\p  
\v 20 Pita e hakatike no kite te disaipol tera Jisas e hihai mahi raa e tuu i muri aia; teenaa ko te disaipol tera ni hakapare ake te vahi Jisas te saaita laatou ni kkai raa no vahiri ake ma, “TeAriki, koai te tama e me ki hakari ake Akoe i na tama hakamattua naa?”  
\v 21 Pita ni kite te disaipol raa, tena aia ki vahiri ake Jisas ma, “TeAriki, kaa te tama nei?” 
\p  
\v 22 Kito Jisas ki meake Pita, “Kame Anau e hihai ma te tama nei ki noho roo ki tae te saaita Anau e vaakai mai raa, tena kaa hea akoe e me ki mee? Tautari mai Anau!” 
\p  
\v 23 Tena te tattara nei ku tere no llono na tama tauttari Jisas raa ma te disaipol raa ku se lavaa te mate. Emeia Jisas se meake ma te disaipol raa se lavaa te mate; Jisas e meake ma, “Kame Anau e hihai aia ki noho roo ki tae te saaita Anau e vaakai mai raa, tena kaa hea akoe e me ki mee?” 
\p  
\v 24 Te disaipol naa ko te tama tera ni tattara na tattara nei, ia te tama hoki tera ni taataa na mee nei i roto te launiu nei raa, tena maatou e illoa pera ma hea aia e tattara raa e hakamaoni. 
\s1 Na tattara hakaoti 
\p  
\v 25 Tena e tammaki roo alaa mee hoki Jisas ni ppena. Kame na mee nei hakaatoa ni tattaa i roto te launiu nei, tena anau e maanatu ma te maarama nei kame se lavaa te isi na kina ki hakatau na launiu nei hakaatoa.